INSERT  IGNORE INTO `person` VALUES (1,'Adam Robitel','Adam James Robitel','Adam Robitel graduated from the University of Southern California\'s School of Cinematic Arts, a double major in film production and acting.<br><br>Robitel is currently in post on a <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5886046?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Escape Room</a> (2019) which he developed and directed for producer Neal Moritz\'s Original Films and Sony Pictures Studios, slated for theatrical release on January 4th, 2019.<br><br>Robitel recently made headlines after being tapped to direct Blumhouse\'s creep-fest franchise <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5726086?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Insidious: The Last Key</a> (2018) (2017). The Last Key opened on January 5th, to stellar domestic box office, grossing 30 million dollars on its opening weekend and more than 167 million dollars worldwide, making it the most lucrative Insidious to date.<br><br>Robitel made a big splash in the genre world as a horror auteur having co-written, directed and produced <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3387648?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">The Taking of Deborah Logan</a> (2014) (2014) a found-footage horror thriller. The Taking of Deborah Logan was named a \"Netflix Horror Gem\" by The Wrap and won an iHorror Award for best direct release of 2014. Paramount Studios then hired Robitel to do some rewrites on <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2473510?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Paranormal Activity: The Ghost Dimension</a> (2015) (2015).<br><br>On the writing side, Robitel\'s original supernatural thriller idea <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5664144?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Liminal</a> sparked a bidding war and sold to Fox2000 with Nina Jacobson producing. Robitel will serve as executive producer with Chris Landon writing the screenplay and directing. The scribe has also written a gritty reinvention of the slasher genre with <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4046014?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Cropsey</a> based on the infamous maniac who has haunted the imaginations of campers for over a hundred years for <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0004906?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Peter Facinelli</a> A7SLE Seven films.<br><br>On the television side, he\'s developing a character driven Private Eye procedural with co-writer Gavin Heffernan, director Jusin Lin and show runner Nick Stoller as well as an original horror series executive produced by Darren Aronofsky\'s Protozoa.<br><br><br><br>On the acting side, his motion picture debut was in Fox\'s smash success <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0120903?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">X-Men</a> (2000) where he was thrown like a rag-doll by an eight-foot mutant. Since then Adam has worked on music videos the likes of <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0005453?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Britney Spears</a> and \'Smashmouth\', appeared in \"Spin City\" and \"Angel\" and starred in a national commercial for Paul Mitchell. Adam then landed a leading role in Tim Sullivan\'s <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0264323?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">2001 Maniacs</a> (2005), a comedy-horror remake of the 1964 drive-in classic, starring alongside <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000387?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Robert Englund</a> and <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0005417?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Lin Shaye</a>. Robitel would go on to appear in \"Field of Screams\", \"Chillerama\", and Paul Ward\'s Stephen King adaptation of \"One For The Road\", alongside Reggie Bannister.<br>\n         ','1978-05-26 00:00:00',NULL,'Boston, Massachusetts, USA','0733263','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjE5NTAxMDI2Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwNjQ0MjY5OQ@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(2,'Bragi F. Schut',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0776885','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNmUyNDdmZTUtYzI4Ny00NjlhLThiZjYtMDhlYWE1MjkyZDg0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTEwNzY2NTk@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(3,'Maria Melnik',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3481322','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(4,'Ori Marmur',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1506459','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(5,'Neal H. Moritz',NULL,NULL,'1959-06-06 00:00:00',NULL,'Los Angeles, California, USA','0605775','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BODY1MDY0NDk5Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTg4ODMwNzE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(6,'Donovan Roberts-Baxter',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1750269','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(7,'John Carey',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4980516','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNWQ2Mjg3ZTQtZTdjNC00M2JkLWFiZjgtZjIzMTE3YzE5ZGY3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzQ2MDE5MzA@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(8,'Brian Tyler',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0003911','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTU3NzcyMjUzM15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwOTc5NDI2OQ@@._V1_UY317_CR3,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(9,'Deborah Ann Woll',NULL,'Deborah was born in 1985, in Brooklyn, New York, from Irish and German heritage. She took acting, piano and dance classes. She went to high school at Packer Collegiate Institute and graduated from the BFA program at the USC School of Theatre at the University of Southern California.<br><br>Deborah started to work as an actress on television and her breakout was in the highly-acclaimed HBO vampire drama, <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0844441?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">True Blood</a> (2008), as a young and fierce vampire girl, \"Jessica Hamby\". From that moment, she gained roles in such films as <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1434435?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Mother\'s Day</a> (2010), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1699147?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Seven Days in Utopia</a> (2011), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1703125?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Someday This Pain Will Be Useful to You</a> (2011), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1886493?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Catch .44</a> (2011), opposite <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000246?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Bruce Willis</a> and <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0001845?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Forest Whitaker</a>, and <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1839492?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Ruby Sparks</a> (2012). Woll\'s boyfriend, Edward <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2907034?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">E.J. Scott</a>, is a comedian and his family are afflicted with choroideremia, which is a condition that slowly blinds its victim. She uses her celebrity status to help advocate for them and others with the disease. She has been quoted as saying that her boyfriend\'s bravery in fighting his disability has inspired her own battle with Celiac disease, which makes her body intolerant to foods containing gluten.<br>\n         ','1985-02-07 00:00:00',NULL,'Brooklyn, New York City, New York, USA','2832695','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjE2NjA4NzYyMV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwODEwNjQyMw@@._V1_UY317_CR26,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(10,'Taylor Russell',NULL,NULL,'1994-07-18 00:00:00',NULL,'Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada','5347988','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYWYyNDcwNGQtNTQ1MS00YjZmLWJjYTYtZmU2YTZkOGJhMjkyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzcyMzAzNzk@._V1_UY317_CR35,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(11,'Tyler Labine',NULL,NULL,'1978-04-29 00:00:00',NULL,'Brampton, Ontario, Canada','0479527','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZjVmNTZkNWYtOGIyNy00MTZjLWJlMWUtOGMzNWZmOTNiMTBmXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTExNDQ2MTI@._V1_UY317_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(12,'Logan Miller',NULL,NULL,'1992-02-18 00:00:00',NULL,'Colorado, USA','2383250','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTUzOTM2NTY2N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODAwMTczODE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(13,'Nik Dodani',NULL,'Nik Dodani is an actor and comedian, known for Atypical (2017), Murphy Brown (2018), and Alex Strangelove (2018). His first stand-up set trended on BuzzFeed in 2016 and he made his network television debut on The Late Show with Stephen Colbert in September 2018. Reporting on his date of birth and age is unconfirmed.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'6516135','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNjgyYmQ0ZWMtYmQ1Zi00ZGI4LWE5ZTEtOTc5NGFmMTg1ODczXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTQ5NjkyNDU@._V1_UY317_CR2,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(14,'Jay Ellis','Wendell Ellis Jr.','Jay Ellis is a television and film actor, philanthropist, and entrepreneur. Born in Fort Sumter, South Carolina, Ellis spent the majority of his childhood traveling with his military family. His father completed over 15 years of service in the Air Force while his mother was an accomplished finance executive and former board member of the Consumer Advisory Council for the Federal.<br><br>Jay graduated Suma Cum Laude at Concordia University in Portland, Oregon where he also played basketball and held the position of student body president. Ellis interned briefly with the Portland Trailblazers and also joined AmeriCorps to provide care and resources to disadvantaged students of Portland.<br><br>Ellis made the move to Los Angeles to pursue his passion for acting before landing his first role on the BET series THE GAME which ran for 147 episodes. Over the years Ellis has been featured on critically acclaimed series MASTERS OF SEX, GRACE AND FRANKIE, HOW I MET YOUR MOTHER, GREY\'S ANATOMY and NCIS.<br><br>Ellis lives in Los Angeles, CA and can currently be seen on the new HBO comedy series INSECURE.<br>\n         ','1981-12-27 00:00:00',NULL,'Sumter, South Carolina, USA','1337350','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTUyNzY4Mjc5OV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTI5OTI2NDM@._V1_UY317_CR112,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(15,'Jessica Sutton',NULL,'Jessica Sutton recently completed production on the Freeform pilot Motherland, from Gary Sanchez Productions. She could last be seen as \"Mia\" in the Netflix hit The Kissing Booth. Prior to The Kissing Booth, she could be seen in National Geographic\'s four part mini-series Saints & Strangers. Jessica will next be seen in the Sony feature, Escape Room.<br><br>Jessica is a South African actress who trained through ACT Film Academy, where she was coached by some of South Africa\'s top industry professionals. She continues her training with acting coach Matthew Harrison at the Actors Foundry.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7571075','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNTNiN2U2ZTQtMThjYi00ZjM0LTgwYTQtMmI4MTViOTA0ZTdkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjI4OTQ4ODY@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(16,'Yorick van Wageningen',NULL,NULL,'1964-04-16 00:00:00',NULL,'Baarn, Utrecht, Netherlands','0905691','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjI5OTM4MTg0Ml5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwNDc3MzYxNw@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(17,'Jamie-Lee Money',NULL,'Jamie-Lee Money is an actress born and raised by her two parents, in Johannesburg, South Africa. She moved to Cape Town (in 2013) after finishing High School at St Mary\'s School, Waverley in Johannesburg, in order to study a BA in Theatre and Performance at the University of Cape Town, South Africa. She received her BA Honours Degree after four years of study, graduating (at the end of 2015). Jamie-Lee works as a stage, film and television actress. She lives and works in Cape Town, South Africa. (2017)<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'8249698','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMGExZGIzNDktMWMwNS00OTAyLTllMjItMjljNzQ2ODY3YjVjXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjc4MjQwODQ@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(18,'Vere Tindale',NULL,'Vere is an intense theatre, film and television actor. He has primarily performed outside of his native accent in a range of contemporary and period productions and has worked in the USA, New Zealand and South Africa. Vere has a background in stand up comedy and is equally competent in dramatic and comedic roles.<br><br>He can be seen playing John Howland in the award winning miniseries <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4705002?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Saints &amp; Strangers</a> (2015) with <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2319871?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Anna Camp</a>, <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0440229?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Vincent Kartheiser</a> and <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0515296?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Ron Livingston</a>, and more recently playing Bob Ashton opposite <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0262635?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Chris Evans</a> in the soon to be released <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt6675186?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">The Red Sea Diving Resort</a> (2019).<br><br>Vere is a graduate of The Neighborhood Playhouse in New York where he received a partial scholarship in his final year of study.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'4227608','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYzg4NjA4OTktOTI2MC00Nzk0LWI0NDctYTBmZGM3YTVlNjM1XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjE4MDA1ODg@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(19,'Kenneth Fok',NULL,'After establishing himself on local small and big screens, South African actor Kenneth Fok has worked his way into roles reaching a mainstream audience worldwide in Safe House (2012) and Eye in the Sky (2016). His versatility has led him to performances with William H. Macy in The Deal (2008) to Idris Elba and Matthew McConaughey in The Dark Tower (2017), as well as Alicia Vikander in Tomb Raider (2018). Whilst still working on homegrown projects playing the formidable villain Chang in Night Drive (2010) and Wei in Five Fingers for Marseilles (2017), he has been cast in several TV series including Strike Back (2011), Dominion (2014), Homeland (2014) and The Looming Tower.<br><br>Son of a vegetable farmer and housewife and the youngest of seven siblings, Kenneth was born on May 21, 1974 in Germiston, Johannesburg. After turning down the opportunity to partake in the family business he studied acting then moved to London where he landed a role as an extra on the Bond movie Die Another Day (2002). After his return he worked with the well-known South African icon Pieter-Dirk Uys in his successful stage play Macbeki playing four different characters. He also tried his luck in the long running local magazine programme Top Billing for their new Presenter Search Competition beating 8000 hopefuls and making it to the top four.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'3022996','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNWE0Nzc3ZmUtY2RiMC00Y2NiLWIxNWEtMGM2YWMwM2Y0NzAxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTk5NTExNzg@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(20,'Cornelius Geaney Jr.',NULL,'Cornelius was born in Queens, NY and made his professional debut in Tracy Letts\' Superior Donuts at Capital Repertory Theatre, which set him on his path as a professional actor. Cornelius moved to England in 2013 with his wife and son. Since then he has worked all over the UK and Europe starring in Commercials, Short /Feature Films, Corporate Films, Immersive/Physical Theatre, Voiceovers, and much more! Cornelius is extremely passionate about the arts, comic books and coffee. In his spare time he writes his own comic strips and builds inventions/costumes with his son and Labrador.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'6353637','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOWViMzU0ZjItOGZmYi00YzJhLWJlYjItMWM0M2Y0OTNmZmYzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(21,'Paul Hampshire',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2518215','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZjVlYTZhNTItZmZmMS00ZTE5LTlmNDgtNDk1N2Y2ZTAxYTU0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR40,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(22,'Pete Sepenuk',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0784614','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(23,'Dan Gruenberg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3263178','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(24,'Gino Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7933818','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(25,'Adam Garnet Jones',NULL,'Adam Garnet Jones is a Canadian writer, editor and director of Cree and Métis heritage whose work includes over 20 short films that have been broadcast on television and the big screen, and have received positive international response. Jones grew up in Alberta and British Columbia before moving to Toronto, Ontario to study at Ryerson University, from which he received a B.F.A. in film studies. \"Fire Song\" was his feature length directorial debut.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2049672','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(26,'Sarah Kolasky',NULL,'Sarah Kolasky is an award-winning actor, writer, and producer from Toronto. She starred in the feature film Great Great Great, which she produced and co-wrote with her long-time collaborator, Adam Garnet Jones. The film was selected as one of the Top Ten Canadian Films of 2017 by Canada\'s most-read newspaper, The Globe and Mail, and Kolasky and Jones were co-nominated for Best Original Screenplay at the 2018 Canadian Screen Awards. Great Great Great premiered at the Canadian Film Fest in March 2017, and won Best Feature, Best Screenplay, and Best Performance in a Feature (for Sarah Kolasky). She also produced and acted in the short film, LIAR, which premiered at the prestigious 2012 South by Southwest Film Festival in Austin, TX. Other producing credits include the short films A Small Thing (TIFF \'08) and Cloudbreaker (TIFF \'06). She is an alumnus of the Toronto International Film Festival\'s Talent Lab.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1443428','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZTMxMDA5M2QtYzNkZi00ODliLTgxMmUtMjE5MGZjOTZiY2U3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTkzNTY1NTU@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(27,'Isabelle Pilon',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3549838','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(28,'David Arcus',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2058658','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(29,'Dan Beirne',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1222461','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDM4NDk4ZTMtNTU4Yy00ZDljLTgxZmQtNzY2YzllMGEyMWY5XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(30,'Richard Clarkin',NULL,'Richard Clarkin was born in Aurora, Ontario, Canada. He is a graduate of The National Theater School of Canada. Even though he is busy in TV he still continues to act in many theater productions across Canada. Richard is also an ensemble member of The Company Theater of Toronto. His theater credits almost equal in number his TV credits. Some of these are, The Fighting Days, The Price, Waiting For Godot, Sherlock Holmes, Red River Rebellion, VideoCab, The Lion King, Death of a Salesman, plus many more at other theaters across Canada. Has also done voice-over work. Known for his reoccurring roles on The Murdoch Mysteries (TV Series) as Chief Constable Davis / Inspector Jeffrey Davis, Naturally, Sadie (TV Series) as Walter Hawthorne, and played the part, of an American President, in The War of 1812 a TV Mini-Series, and that President was Andrew Jackson.<br><br>In his early career, Clarkin wanted to be a sportscaster, and spent a year working at The C.B.C. But the acting bug bit and he joined a theater company and the rest was history. He has been steadily working for over 20 years. In an Interview with theater director Philip Riccio, Richard talked about his passion and love of the theater. In another interview with Katie Chats, He stated he likes camping and canoeing. Also stated jokingly, that he is so into his work, that he did not have time, for Facebook or the like.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'0165067','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjA1MjM4MTQ2NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwODk5NzkxNA@@._V1_UY317_CR12,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(31,'Meredith Cheesbrough',NULL,NULL,'1983-12-24 00:00:00',NULL,'Saskatoon, Saskatchewan, Canada','2856339','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(32,'Lindsay Leese',NULL,'Lindsay is a professional actor, director, improviser, trainer and an alumnus of world renowned sketch comedy theatre The Second City. Lindsay and her partner Lee Smart provide creative services for the entertainment industry in Toronto, Canada. <br><br>Lindsay began her career by training at The National Theatre School of Canada, graduating in 1981. She has been seen and heard in many roles on stage and in film, television, animation, radio and TV commercials. Some selected credits include The Prizewinner of Defiance Ohio, Ginger Snaps, Comfort & Joy, Coast to Coast, Tommy Boy, Three to Tango, The Wrong Guy, Brain Candy, & Mr. Headmistress.<br><br>Lindsay is the founder, director of The Tim Sims Encouragement Fund, (a charitable organization administered by the Ontario Arts Foundation) which has supported up and coming comedic performers with an annual cash prize of recognition since 1996. She is the executive producer of Cream of Comedy, the nationally broadcast award show for the TSEF on The Comedy Network since 1998.<br><br>Lindsay began teaching improvisation in 1989, and continues to work as a corporate trainer specializing in the application of improvisational techniques to improve business success. She also provides business presentation coaching services and training with PitchCraft.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'0498757','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYzFlMTk3NzItMzNhOS00YTcyLTgyMTctNzUyZTUzMWQwODk5XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTU5MTAwNzY@._V1_UY317_CR91,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(33,'Ian Fisher',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3965339','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjZkYjNiYTYtOTg3OS00NmY0LTlhYjgtNWY5YzBmNTBhMWMxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(34,'Farah Merani',NULL,'Farah is a graduate of the Drama Centre London and trained at the Vakhtangov Theatre in Moscow.<br><br>In addition to being an actor, she started producing in 2013 and has worked on over 14 films with her company, Lifeguard Productions. She is one of the co-founders of Women on Screen and also serves as the Actra Toronto Diversity Committee co-chair.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'4011678','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYmVhYjc4MTQtOWY3Zi00MTBlLTgxNDgtOTZhZWMyNmU3MmM2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTY0OTA4Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR91,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(35,'Gillian Ferrier',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3090960','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTg1ODgwMzI0NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODYzNTU0MjE@._V1_UY317_CR19,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(36,'John Jarvis',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3150672','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(37,'Neil Burger',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Greenwich, Connecticut, USA','1139726','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjE3NDc5NjAwN15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTYwNDIzODg2._V1_UY317_CR138,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(38,'Jon Hartmere',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1768281','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(39,'Éric Toledano',NULL,NULL,'1971-07-03 00:00:00',NULL,'Paris, France','0865918','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTY4OT