jects Schiller co-financed and produced at BSFG include \"Escape Plan,\" starring Arnold Schwarzenegger and Sylvester Stallone, and \"Jane Got A Gun\" starring Natalie Portman, Joel Edgerton and Ewan McGregor. Schiller is also developing an action/comedy feature adaptation of the long-running television series \"Cops\" with Ruben Fleischer attached to direct.<br><br>Prior to BSFG, Schiller worked for Garry Shandling on the commercially successful \"What Planet Are you From?\" and for Doug Belgrad, President of Sony Pictures Entertainment Group, before transitioning to work for Adam Sandler at his production company, Happy Madison. At Happy Madison, Schiller actively engaged in the behind the scenes development and production of the feature films \"Anger Management,\" \"Mr. Deeds,\" \"Big Daddy,\" \"8 Crazy Nights,\" and \"Grandma\'s Boy\". In 2011, Schiller financed and produced the film \"Son of Morning\" starring Heather Graham and Bob Odenkirk.<br><br>Schiller earned his BA from Columbia University.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1496779','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZThkNDg2YTQtYjZlZS00MTYwLTgxYzgtMDExMjA5MTk3MzYzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjk3OTcwNQ@@._V1_UY317_CR130,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(46,'Steve Tisch','Steven Elliot Tisch',NULL,'1949-02-14 00:00:00',NULL,'Lakewood, New Jersey, USA','0005494','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjE4OTQ3ODU0NF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTYwMDcwMDY1._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(47,'Harvey Weinstein',NULL,'Harvey Weinstein was born on March 19, 1952 in Flushing, Queens, New York City, New York, USA. He is a film producer, known for <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0110912?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Pulp Fiction</a> (1994), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0138097?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Shakespeare in Love</a> (1998) and <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0217505?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Gangs of New York</a> (2002). He is now separated from his wife <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1312338?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Georgina Chapman</a> and was previously married to Eve Chilton Weinstein.<br>\n         ','1952-03-19 00:00:00',NULL,'Flushing, Queens, New York City, New York, USA','0005544','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTAwMTkwNTQ2NTdeQTJeQWpwZ15BbWU2MDA0MzU5Nw@@._V1_UY317_CR8,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(48,'Rob Simonsen',NULL,'Rob Simonsen has had a thread in the fabric of some of the most noteworthy and prestigious films of the past decade. He collaborated with director Bennett Miller to underline the unsettling atmosphere of the Oscar-nominated drama Foxcatcher, and spanned an eternity of star-crossed romance with The Age of Adaline, also co-writing the film\'s end credits song. He scored the Steve Carell-starring dramedy The Way Way Back with sensitivity, sympathized with the coming-of-age The Spectacular Now, and sweetened Zach Braff\'s coming-of-middle-age film Wish I Was Here. Also under his belt is the horror-comedy The Master Cleanse, Roland Emmerich\'s political drama Stonewall, and the Weinstein Company\'s Burnt starring Bradley Cooper, Uma Thurman and Sienna Miller. His work in television has included the Joss Whedon Fox drama Dollhouse and the CBS ratings juggernaut Blue bloods, led by Tom Selleck.<br><br>Prior to flying solo, under the apprenticeship of composer Mychael Danna, Simonsen contributed additional music to the scores for Ang Lee\'s Life of Pi and Bennett Miller\'s Moneyball - as well as Catherine Hardwick\'s The Nativity Story, Sony Pictures Animation Surf\'s Up, and Terry Gilliam\'s The Imaginarium of Doctor Parnassus. With Danna, he co-composed the score for Marc Webb\'s hugely popular indie romance (500) Days of Summer.<br><br>Simonsen\'s compositional voice is the product of an education in jazz, electronic and traditional orchestral music. In 2013, he co-founded The Echo Society, a collective that provides a platform for composers to experiment and create for live performances around Los Angeles.<br>\n         ','1978-03-11 00:00:00',NULL,'St. Louis, Missouri, USA','1387379','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjEyNjYyNDkzNF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTM0MDAxMTE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(49,'Nicole Kidman','Nicole Mary Kidman','Elegant blonde Nicole Kidman, known as one of Hollywood\'s top Australian imports, was actually born in Honolulu, Hawaii, while her Australian parents were there on educational visas.<br><br>Kidman is the daughter of Janelle Ann (Glenny), a nursing instructor, and Antony David Kidman, a biochemist and clinical psychologist. She is of English, Irish, and Scottish descent. Shortly after her birth, the family moved to Washington, D.C., where Nicole\'s father pursued his research on breast cancer, and then, three years later, made the pilgrimage back to her parents\' native Sydney in Australia, where Nicole was raised. Young Nicole\'s first love was ballet, but she eventually took up mime and drama as well (her first stage role was a bleating sheep in an elementary school Christmas pageant). In her adolescent years, acting edged out the other arts and became a kind of refuge -- as her classmates sought out fun in the sun, the fair-skinned Kidman retreated to dark rehearsal halls to practice her craft. She worked regularly at the Philip Street Theater, where she once received a personal letter of praise and encouragement from audience member <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0001005?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Jane Campion</a> (then a film student). Kidman eventually dropped out of high school to pursue acting full-time. She broke into movies at age 16, landing a role in the Australian holiday favorite <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0085282?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Bush Christmas</a> (1983). That appearance touched off a flurry of film and television offers, including a lead in <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0085204?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">BMX Bandits</a> (1983) and a turn as a schoolgirl-turned-protester in the miniseries <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0140770?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Vietnam</a> (1987) (for which she won her first Australian Film Institute Award). With the help of an American agent, she eventually made her US debut opposite <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000554?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Sam Neill</a> in the at-sea thriller <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0097162?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Dead Calm</a> (1989).<br><br>Kidman\'s next casting coup scored her more than exposure. While starring as <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000129?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Tom Cruise</a>\'s doctor/love interest in the racetrack romance <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0099371?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Days of Thunder</a> (1990), she won over the Hollywood hunk hook, line and sinker. After a whirlwind courtship (and decent box office returns), the couple wed on December 24, 1990. Determined not to let her new marital status overshadow her fledgling career, the actress pressed on. She appeared as a catty high school senior in the Australian film <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0101898?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Flirting</a> (1991), then as <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000163?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Dustin Hoffman</a>\'s moll in the gangster flick <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0101453?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Billy Bathgate</a> (1991). She reunited with Cruise for <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0104231?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Far and Away</a> (1992), the story of young Irish lovers who flee to America in the late 1800s, and starred opposite <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000474?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Michael Keaton</a> in the tear-tugger <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0107630?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">My Life</a> (1993). Despite her steady employment, critics and moviegoers still had not quite warmed to Kidman as a leading lady. She tried to spice up her image by seducing <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000174?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Val Kilmer</a> in <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0112462?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Batman Forever</a> (1995), but achieved her real breakthrough with <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0001814?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Gus Van Sant</a>\'s <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0114681?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">To Die For</a> (1995). As a fame-crazed housewife determined to eliminate any obstacle in her path, Kidman proved that she had an impressive range and deadly comic timing. She took home a Golden Globe and several critics\' awards for the performance. In 1996, Kidman stepped into a corset to work with her countrywoman and onetime admirer, <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0001005?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Jane Campion</a>, on the adaptation of <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0416556?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Henry James</a>\'s <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0117364?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">The Portrait of a Lady</a> (1996). A few months later, she tore across the screen as a nuclear weapons expert in <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0119874?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">The Peacemaker</a> (1997), adding \"action star\" to her professional repertoire.<br><br>She and Cruise then disappeared into a notoriously long, secretive shoot for <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000040?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Stanley Kubrick</a>\'s sexual thriller <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0120663?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Eyes Wide Shut</a> (1999). The couple\'s on-screen shenanigans prompted an increase in public speculation about their sex life (rumors had long been circulating that their marriage was a cover-up for Cruise\'s homosexuality); tired of denying tabloid attacks, they successfully sued The Star for a story alleging that they needed a sex therapist to coach them through love scenes. Family life has always been a priority for Kidman. Born to social activists (mother was a feminist; father, a labor advocate), Nicole and her little sister, <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1159418?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Antonia Kidman</a>, discussed current events around the dinner table and participated in their parents\' campaigns by passing out pamphlets on street corners. When her mother was diagnosed with breast cancer, 17-year-old Nicole stopped working and took a massage course so that she could provide physical therapy (her mother eventually beat the cancer). She and Cruise adopted two children: Isabella Jane (born 1993) and Connor Antony (born 1995). Despite their rock-solid image, the couple announced in early 2001 that they were separating due to career conflicts. Her marriage to Cruise ended mid-summer of 2001.<br>\n         ','1967-06-20 00:00:00',NULL,'Honolulu, Hawaii, USA','0000173','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTk1MjM5NDg4MF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwNDg1OTQ4Nw@@._V1_UY317_CR10,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(50,'Kevin Hart','Kevin Darnell Hart',NULL,'1979-07-06 00:00:00',NULL,'Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, USA','0366389','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTY4OTAxMjkxN15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODg5MzYyMTE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(51,'Bryan Cranston','Bryan Lee Cranston','Bryan Lee Cranston was born on March 7, 1956 in Hollywood, California, to Audrey Peggy Sell, a radio actress, and <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0186510?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Joe Cranston</a>, an actor and former amateur boxer. His maternal grandparents were German, and his father was of Irish, German, and Austrian-Jewish ancestry. He was raised partly by his grandparents, living on their poultry farm in the Canoga Park neighborhood of Los Angeles, California. Cranston\'s father walked out on the family when Cranston was 11 years old, and they did not see each other again until 11 years later, when Cranston and his brother decide to track down their father.<br><br>Cranston is known for his roles as Walter White on the AMC crime drama <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0903747?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Breaking Bad</a> (2008), Hal on the Fox situation comedy <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0212671?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Malcolm in the Middle</a> (2000), and Dr. Tim Whatley on five episodes of the NBC situation comedy <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0098904?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Seinfeld</a> (1989). For his role on \"Breaking Bad\", he won the Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actor in a Drama Series four times (2008-2010, 2014), including three consecutive wins. After becoming one of the producers during the series\' fourth and fifth seasons, he also won the Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Drama Series twice.<br><br>In June 2014, Cranston won the Tony Award for Best Actor in a Play for his portrayal of <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0425696?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Lyndon Johnson</a> in the play \"All the Way\" on Broadway. He reprised the role of Lyndon Johnson in the television adaptation <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5632572?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">All the Way</a> (2016), which earned him widespread praise by critics. For the biographical drama <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3203606?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Trumbo</a> (2015), he earned widespread acclaim and was nominated for the Academy Award for Best Actor. Cranston also appeared in several acclaimed films, such as <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0120815?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Saving Private Ryan</a> (1998), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0449059?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Little Miss Sunshine</a> (2006), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0780504?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Drive</a> (2011), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1024648?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Argo</a> (2012) and <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0831387?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Godzilla</a> (2014).<br>\n         ','1956-03-07 00:00:00',NULL,'Hollywood, California, USA','0186505','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTA2NjEyMTY4MTVeQTJeQWpwZ15BbWU3MDQ5NDAzNDc@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(52,'Julianna Margulies','Julianna Luisa Margulies','Julianna Margulies was born on June 8, 1966 in Spring Valley (near New York City), as the youngest of three daughters of Francesca (Goldberg), a teacher and dancer in American Ballet, and Paul Margulies, an advertising writer and philosopher. She is of Ashkenazi Jewish heritage (from Romania, Austria, Hungary, and Russia). Until beginning high school in New Hampshire at age 14, she lived several years with her family in Paris and in England. She obtained a B.A. degree in liberal arts from Sarah Lawrence College, where she appeared in several plays on campus. She jobbed as a waitress until her first role as a prostitute looking to go straight in <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0102614?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Out for Justice</a> (1991). It took more than a year to find another role; during that time, she managed to support herself from several regional theater productions and national TV ads. Until she became a regular in <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0108757?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">ER</a> (1994), she guest starred in several television series and a pilot. Since then, she has starred in several films, including <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0288477?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Ghost Ship</a> (2002), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0298856?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Evelyn</a> (2002), and <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0417148?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Snakes on a Plane</a> (2006), and headlines the CBS drama <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1442462?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">The Good Wife</a> (2009), for which she has won both an Emmy and a Golden Globe.<br>\n         ','1966-06-08 00:00:00',NULL,'Spring Valley, New York, USA','0000523','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTQ2MTgxOTgxMl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMzIxOTAwMDE@._V1_UY317_CR12,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(53,'Golshifteh Farahani',NULL,'Golshifteh started her acting career in theater at the age of 6 and has always kept a strong link with theater, but it was at the age of 14 that she acted in her first film <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0187809?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">The Pear Tree</a> (1998), for which she won the prize for the Best Actress from the international section of the Fajr film festival, immediately making her one of the stars of Iranian cinema. Since then she has played in more than 15 films, many of which have been screened or awarded at international festivals. Amongst her latest films are <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0315842?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Bahman Ghobadi</a>\'s <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0847050?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Half Moon</a> (2006) (winner of the Golden Seashell at the San Sebastián film festival 2006), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0576529?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Dariush Mehrjui</a>\'s controversial <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0385277?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">The Music Man</a> (2007), still banned in Iran, and the late <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2202052?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Rasool Mollagholi Poor</a>\'s <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1113810?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">M for Mother</a> (2006), which after a huge success in Iran was chosen to represent Iran for the Best Foreign Film at the Academy Awards in 2008. After playing in <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0758774?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Body of Lies</a> (2008) by <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000631?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Ridley Scott</a>, Golshifteh became the first Iranian star to act in a major Hollywood production. Subsequently she was banned from leaving her country. Her last film in Iran <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1360860?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">About Elly</a> (2009) won a Silver Bear in Berlin and the Best Narrative Feature at Tribeca (2009). Golshifteh graduated from music school, she sings and plays the piano amongst other instruments. She is also fluent in French and English and lives in Paris now.<br>\n         ','1983-07-10 00:00:00',NULL,'Tehran, Iran','0267042','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjA5MDAwMDUzNV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjQ4NDE2MDE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(54,'Tate Donovan','Tate Buckley Donovan','Tate Buckley Donovan began making television appearances while still in his teens, most often cast as angst-ridden high schoolers in such made-for-TV films such as <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0089705?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Not My Kid</a> (1985) and <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0092416?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Nutcracker: Money, Madness &amp; Murder</a> (1987).<br><br>Donovan was born to a large family in Tenafly, New Jersey, the son of Eileen Frances (McAllister) and John Timothy Donovan, a surgeon. He is of Irish descent. Donovan moved to Los Angeles to be closer to the television industry while he attended college at USC, where he also met several fellow actors who became longtime friends, such as <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0381416?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Grant Heslov</a> and <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000123?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">George Clooney</a>, with whom he still parties with to this day (he also had a fairly substantial part in their smash film, <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0433383?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Good Night, and Good Luck.</a> (2005). Although not quite as active as his friend Clooney in the romantic arena, confirmed bachelor Donovan has been engaged to both film star <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000113?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Sandra Bullock</a> and television icon <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000098?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Jennifer Aniston</a>, and has dated a diverse group of women such as socialite Plum Sikes (2000), stage actress <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0021157?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Whitney Allen</a> (2001) and television actress <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0334179?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Lauren Graham</a>, whom he met when they both appeared in the play \"Once in a Lifetime\" at the Williamstown Theater Festival in 2002. After graduating from college, Donovan gained prominent notice for his portrayal of the charismatic yet self-centered co-pilot in the ensemble period drama <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0100133?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Memphis Belle</a> (1990). Prior to that, Donovan had appeared as the cocky elder camper in <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0091993?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">SpaceCamp</a> (1986) and as a recovering drug addict in <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0094884?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Clean and Sober</a> (1988). His first leading role was in the charming but minor <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0102343?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Love Potion No. 9</a> (1992), costarring Bullock, to whom he became engaged (their relationship ended in 1994). He then appeared in several independent features as sullen, withdrawn types before following up with a role in the Disney family comedy, <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0110044?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Holy Matrimony</a> (1994). He returned to Disney for perhaps his highest-profile effort to date, the animated <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0119282?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Hercules</a> (1997), for which he provided the voice for the adult version of the title character. His small-screen work has included a Cable ACE-nominated turn in the HBO series Vietnam War Story II (1988) (V). He joined the parade of film stars who turned to sitcoms, heading the cast of <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0112118?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Partners</a> (1995) opposite <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0001083?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Jon Cryer</a>. When that failed to catch on, he joined with his \"Memphis Belle\" co-stars <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000655?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Eric Stoltz</a> and <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0224703?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Reed Diamond</a> to play three brothers in a memorable episode of NBC\'s <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0106028?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Homicide: Life on the Street</a> (1993) and had a recurring role as a client and potential love interest for <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0001222?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Calista Flockhart</a>\'s titular lawyer <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0118254?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Ally McBeal</a> (1997). Switching networks, he had a recurring role as a love interest opposite his then-girlfriend <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000098?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Jennifer Aniston</a> in NBC\'s <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0108778?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Friends</a> (1994) and donned clerical garb to play the priest son of a large Irish Catholic family in the short-lived NBC drama <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0157245?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Trinity</a> (1998). More recently he has appeared as a guest star in several shows such as <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0285370?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">The Guardian</a> (2001), as well as <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0348966?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Mister Sterling</a> (2003) and in the new show <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0362359?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">The O.C.</a> (2003).<br>\n         ','1963-09-25 00:00:00',NULL,'Tenafly, New Jersey, USA','0004883','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTkyNzUxMTMwM15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwNDQ1Mzc1MQ@@._V1_UY317_CR14,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(55,'Aja Naomi King',NULL,'King appeared in several short films before landing guest roles on the CBS procedurals Blue Bloods and Person of Interest. Her big break came in 2012 when she was cast as new surgical intern Cassandra Kopelson on the CW drama Emily Owens, M.D. The series was canceled after a single season in 2013. She later starred in the Amazon Studios comedy pilot The Onion Presents: The News. King also played Wendell Pierce\'s daughter Abigayle in the independent film Four, released on September 13, 2013. Along with her castmates, she won a Los Angeles Film Festival Award for her role in this movie.<br><br>In 2014, King had a recurring role in the ABC drama series Black Box, and was later cast as one of the leads in the Shonda Rhimes\' legal thriller How to Get Away with Murder.<br>\n         ','1985-01-11 00:00:00',NULL,'Los Angeles County, California, USA','3813115','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTUyMjc5Mjg1OV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTE5NTgyMDI@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(56,'Genevieve Angelson','Genevieve Rose Angelson',NULL,'1987-04-13 00:00:00',NULL,'New York City, New York, USA','3017448','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjE0MDI5MDI5M15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjAxOTM1MDI@._V1_UY317_CR19,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(57,'Amara Karan',NULL,'Amara was born to Sri Lankan parents who had moved to England from Zambia to further her father\'s work opportunities. She went to the Wimbledon High School and, although she enjoyed drama, she regarded acting as a risky profession and studied Politics, Philosophy and Economics at Oxford University, graduating with a 2:1 degree. She then spent two years working in the City of London dealing in mergers and acquisitions. Whilst at Oxford she had directed and appeared in plays and finally decided to go to drama school. Within a month of graduation she was auditioning for Wes Anderson\'s film \'The Darjeeling Limited\'.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,'Wimbledon, London, England, UK','2496312','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNjkzMzcwNzY5M15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDA0MDcwMTI@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(58,'Jahi Di\'Allo Winston',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8091769','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZDU1MmJhZDktOTUzMC00MDhhLWFmYTktMTI4MDM3MmFkMjA5XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(59,'Pia Mechler',NULL,'Of German, Chilean, Polish and Scottish heritage, Pia Maria Patricia Mechler speaks 4 languages and graduated high school as an honor student while also modeling as a teen. At 19 she moved to Denmark after applying and being one of the very limited students accepted to attend the European Film College, where she completed a two-year curriculum focusing on performance and writing, but which also included Film History and editing intensives. Upon her return to Berlin after graduating, she was approached while literally walking down the street one day, to read for a highly rated German television series. She was offered and took, the large recurring guest role.<br><br>Pia decided to explore her performing nature even further and took up an invitation to join an all male, 5 member band who was gearing up in Portugal and subsequently got signed to Universal Music. The band toured and gained radio and MTV airplay. In 2006, returning to Germany, the ever-more-worldly Pia joined the (Special Coaching) Actor\'s Studio in Berlin. She applied and was accepted by the Stella Adler In mid 2007 she landed her first role in a movie for television in London alongside Sean Astin and Jeremy Irons. A mere couple of months later,was then cast in the lead role of the British indie film \"Invisible Eyes\". Since 2010 she has been living in working in the USA where she also ventured out into writing, producing and directing.<br>\n         ','1983-02-19 00:00:00',NULL,'Germany','1987331','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BM2IyZmQ4NzUtMDRkMC00Y2YzLWE5NjQtMTAyY2I2ZDRkZDYzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTQ5MDIwNDY@._V1_UY317_CR134,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(60,'Kristina Aponte',NULL,'Kristina Aponte was born and raised in South Philadelphia, Pennsylvania and is the oldest of four children. Kristina is of Filipino-American descent and born to parents who were raised in Manila, Philippines. Kristina has always enjoyed the performing arts and was a professional cheerleader/dancer for several Philadelphia sports teams. Kristina initially developed her passion for acting by attending one of the finest acting schools in the Philadelphia area in which she then discovered this craft. She will be appearing in a few features given Principal and Executive Producer roles for the horror/thriller feature, \"The Listing\"(2017), and the upcoming indie drama film, \"Michael\" (2017). Kristina was also featured as background in the movie, \"Creed\" (2015), as one of the girlfriends for a rap artist.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'6680643','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOTkxNThjYTItMGNhNC00MWEwLThkYWUtNDdhYzc0NWM4NDE4XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(61,'Ursula Triplett',NULL,'Ursula Triplett was born in up-State New York. Her mother, Carol Knoll, is from a large German family, and her father, Brian Triplett, is of a Scottish/English descent. Ursula has two sisters and a brother. Although very shy as a small child, working experiences in her teenage years contributed to her becoming the outgoing and energetic person she is today. Ursula has been cast in several roles in both major and minor motion pictures. With a blossoming acting career, Ursula shows natural on-screen talent and brings life to an array of characters.<br>\n         ','1985-03-21 00:00:00',NULL,'New York','5182914','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYTU1ZTQ4OWEtMDY3Zi00NjJlLWIyZjMtOTVjYmY4YzkxMWRmXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR12,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(62,'Suzanne Savoy','Suzanne Hélène Savoy','Born in Wilmington, Delaware, Suzanne Savoy moved with her family to Montreal at the age of five and lived in Canada until the age of 23. She studied design at the National Theatre School of Canada and began her acting career in her late twenties after she had moved to Houston. She studied acting at the Royal National Theatre of Great Britain and various other schools and colleges. While living in Texas, she had principal and starring roles in many commercials, films, TV shows and plays, had a thriving career as a voice-over actress, and co-founded Mercury Studio, which provided on-camera training for actors until 2005. She was married to James Black (of The Alley Theatre) for seven years; they have one daughter. Having moved to New York City in 1996 with her daughter following divorce, Ms. Savoy became a mainstay of The Shakespeare Project (Artistic Director Scott Cargle), which toured New York City\'s park and public spaces. She variously performed, designed sets and costumes, built puppets, and created and ran TSP\'s education division over a period of nine years. In 2005 Ms. Savoy moved to Harlem and continued her work appearing in and doing voice-over in numerous national commercials. After a hiatus from film and TV for a number of years while raising her daughter, she has resumed her work in those areas.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'0767929','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTYyNzYzMTg2M15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNjEzMTUxMzE@._V1_UY317_CR13,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(63,'Jennifer Butler','Jennifer Lynn Butler',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2592686','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYzM4NmRlYTEtMWM1NS00NWIzLTk2NGYtOTA5NWJjYjJlMjViXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTMyNjQ4NzM@._V1_UY317_CR8,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(64,'Lyman Chen',NULL,'Lyman Chen is an American Born Film and Television actor of Chinese heritage.<br><br>Lyman\'s break came when he was cast in Martin Scorsese\'s, The Departed as Jack Nicholson\'s Chinese Interpreter. The film premiered in October 2006 and went on to win 4 Academy Awards including Martin Scorsese\'s sole Best Director Academy Award.<br><br>Since then, Lyman has enjoyed working on various film and television projects with a diversity in both dramatic and comedic venues. Roles as a recurring Guest Star on CBS\' Rush Hour as MSS Agent Joseph Yun and also as Xun of The Dark Army on the Golden Globe Award Winning Mr. Robot on USA Network show Lyman\'s versatility in dramatic roles and showcase his language skills, while conversely, comedies like It\'s Always Sunny in Philadelphia show Lyman\'s comedic ability. Lyman can be next seen as Mr. Liang on Season 2 of Mr. Mercedes, The Upside starring Bryan Cranston, Kevin Hart, and Nicole Kidman, and Fox\'s medical drama, The Resident.<br>\n         ','1971-10-12 00:00:00',NULL,'Wilmington, Delaware, USA','1938820','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjM2ZjM5NDgtOTc1MC00NWEwLTliZjMtZThkNzAzYzEzZDg4XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTMxNjY1NA@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(65,'Brian Gallagher',NULL,NULL,'1972-12-15 00:00:00',NULL,'Pennsylvania, USA','3125601','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNzljNzcwNjQtMjQwOS00ODEyLWI5ODMtYTE0YTg5MGJlYzcxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR131,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(66,'Jeffrey Mowery',NULL,'Jeff has a background in Camera work and traveled the world filming/directing small projects in India and Canada. Then in 2005 he jumped into Acting and then joined SAG. Soon after that he had a small part on a TV show called \"Six Degrees\" as \"Howie\". Then Jeff had a small role as \"Lenny the Hoagie Vendor\" on the TV Series Cold Case. He worked with the Coen Brothers in their feature film \"Burn After Reading\" as a \"Suspicious Man\". Jeff worked on \"The Lovely Bones\" as the \"Crime Scene Photographer\" and was given direction by Peter Jackson. He had a Recurring Role on AMC\'s \"Rubicon\" as a \"Cafe Staffer\". He also worked on HBOs John Adams Mini Series as a Senator from NC. Jeff has continued to focus on auditioning for National/Regional Commercials and had one Super Bowl Commercial audition. He enjoys cycling, running and working out. Creed 2 is his 100th Union gig!<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5886517','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTk0NDgyMDg2Nl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwMDE2NjI4Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR131,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(67,'Mark Kochanowicz',NULL,'Mark Kochanowicz is an actor and the owner of Liberty Bell Films.<br><br>Mark Kochanowicz began making movies in Philadelphia when he was 12 years old after his neighbor lent him an 8mm camera to make short films. During his college years in the 1990s, Mark played in several indie-rock bands and graduated from Pennsylvania State University. In 2003 he joined SAG-AFTRA and shortly thereafter booked a day player role on the critically acclaimed HBO show \"The Wire\".<br><br>Over the years Mark has played principal roles in film, television and theater and also has had the privilege of being a stand-in for many of Hollywood\'s A-listers in dozens of movies and TV shows.<br><br>Mark\'s behind-the-camera work has been successful too. Having films screen in over 25 film festivals, he has twice been Greater Philadelphia Film Office\'s grand prize finalist for Set-In-Philadelphia (SIP) screen-writing award and won the \"Best Director Award\" from the 2015 Winter Film Awards for \"Assumption of Risk\".<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1269046','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZDYyZDI1M2ItMjUxOS00NTgzLWIzMmMtYmE5NTlhNWU2Zjc2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQ0NDA0NQ@@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(68,'Julie Stackhouse',NULL,'A Philadelphia native, Julie Stackhouse has been acting on film and stage since the age of 10. She studies acting at Playhouse West-Philadelphia under the instruction of Tony Savant. Julie has also trained at Arthur Murray Dance Studios, providing her with the knowledge and skills to perform ballroom, Latin, and modern dance.<br>\n         ','1986-01-18 00:00:00',NULL,'Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, USA','6212900','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDVlMzNjYTYtMjIyNS00OGYxLTg3YzctYTRmZTgxZGYxMzZjXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTAyMzM5MzE@._V1_UY317_CR24,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(69,'Alisha Poland',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9111800','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BN2ZhMzI3YWMtNDkxOC00ODdmLTlhNjMtMWYyMDE4MmM0Nzg2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzUxNDU2MjA@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(70,'Rachel Alana Handler',NULL,'Rachel Handler is an actor known for Smothered (Chunks) and Law & Order: SVU. Handler was born in Philadelphia and has appeared at Carnegie Hall and Off-Broadway. She won the 2014 best actor award in the 48 Hour Film Challenge and is touring her solo show, Inspiration Whore. Since losing her leg in a car accident, Handler has become an advocate for performers with disabilities.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5846654','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZjY5YjdjZGItYTU5My00NDA0LWI5NzgtMTkwY2FmZjQ4MWExL2ltYWdlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTM1MTEzODM@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(71,'Kevin D. Benton',NULL,'Kevin D. Benton is a Multi Award-Winning, \"Best Film Actor\" and T.V. American Actor who was born in Philadelphia, Pa. He is the middle of three children of Patricia and David Benton Sr. also from Philadelphia, Pa. Kevin caught the acting bug early while appearing in student stage plays in grade school, in which he really enjoyed. As an adult, Kevin got his passion for acting renewed while spending some time with his family in Florida during the summers. During this time, Kevin made his way down to Orlando, Florida where he was frequently cast as a featured extra (Jack\'s Dying Scene) and as an extra in the Cairo Street Scene in the \"Indiana Jones Epic Stunt Spectacular.\" Kevin was regularly cast as an Evil Lab Worker in \"Disaster! A Major Motion Picture Ride ... Starring You,\" a dark ride attraction at Universal Studios Florida. The ride, set on a soundstage of a fictitious movie company, Disaster! was based on the park\'s former Earthquake: The Big One ride, which comically illustrates how special effects are filmed for use in movies. Kevin was also cast in a featured role as the Sea Captain in \"The Backlot Tour\" (Nautica Battle Scene) at Disney\'s Hollywood Studios as well. Kevin played his first notable role as the Casino Security Guard in the Multi Award-Winning Short Film, \"Misfits\" (2015). Kevin\'s first paid acting role was when he was cast as a ring side Fight Fan in the MGM featured film, \"CREED\" (2015), starring Michael B. Jordan and Sylvester Stallone. \"CREED\" was produced by Sylvester Stallone and written and directed by Ryan Croogler, who also wrote and directed \"Fruitvale Station.\" The film was regarded as a \"Rocky\" spin-off movie where Rocky Balboa, played by Sylvester Stallone, is now training and mentoring his late friend Apollo Creed\'s son, Adonis Creed, played by franchise newcomer, Michael B. Jordan. This experience reignited Kevin\'s passion for acting from a professional standpoint and he immediately enrolled in acting classes and continues to take classes in order to hone his craft. Afterwards, Kevin purposed to accept the life long journey of constantly learning, growing and developing as an Actor and to pursue Film, T.V. and screen opportunities in earnest. He is most known for his roles in \"Jason\'s Letter\" which premiered on the STARZ Network, in the TV Series, True Crime Epic Mysteries, House of Cards, many feature films, many short films and the list goes on. Among other acting awards, Kevin won the (2018) \"SPIRAL Film & Music Awards\" \"Best Film Actor\" award for his role as Bobby Mason in \"Emergency Landing\" which won Film of the Year at the Rodney L. Cherry Productions \"Blossom Awards.\" \"Emergency Landing\" can be seen on Amazon Prime, Xfinity X1 on Demand on Comcast. In all of his accomplishments, with more on the way, Kevin continues to focus on the honor and privilege it is to serve the art of acting well and use his gifts, talents and abilities to help other people, especial kids, while doing so.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7273876','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZDczMjIyNGEtMDkwMS00NDgxLWExOTgtNWMxMzUwN2NjN2M4XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjAxMTMyNjU@._V1_UY317_CR12,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(72,'Jon Douglas Rainey',NULL,'Jon Douglas Rainey is a writer, actor, director, host and producer at Letter 8 Media. He loves to perform live or for film and television. His career started when he played Tony at the Venice Plaza for the live production of \"Tony N Tina\'s Wedding.\" He went on to host shows such as \"The Morning Show\" on Radio Vision Network and \"It Takes a Thief\" for the Discovery Channel. Jon has written scripts for film and television and continues to produce productions with his studio partners at Letter 8 Media in Somerdale, New Jersey.<br>\n         ','1970-01-27 00:00:00',NULL,'USA','1909028','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZjdhNmU5MTYtZmE4Ny00NTNlLTg5MWItZjlkNjdhNjBhYWQyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjMxNjUwOQ@@._V1_UY317_CR18,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(73,'Robert Benn',NULL,'West Philadelphia is the birthplace of Robert Edward Benn his Father was Robert Benn Sr. And Mother Linda Bynum the brother of 5 siblings strives hard to be different from the rest of the THE FAMILY So he learned to sing from the guys on the street corner. Songs From The Temptations, The Four Tops, The Ojays, as well as Frank Sinatra and Sammy Davis Jr. A graduate of the Philadelphia school system as well as many trade school degrees. Got his first Start in the Acting world in 2006 as an extra in Rocky Balboa since then was hooked, had to take time off to be a dad but eventually came back to the craft and took it by storm.<br><br>You can catch Actor Robert Benn in movies such As Equity The Gift You Forgot to open THE UPSIDE----COMING OUT MARCH 9 2018 THE NOBODY\'S WATCHING SHOW SEASON 1&2 OF DELAYED GRATIFICATION ON AMAZON PRIME<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7799952','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BM2JiNzc1NTgtYjNkOC00NjA1LWFmOTAtZjcyODYwYTJhMmMyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(74,'Christine Chang',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5575130','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTQ2MjY4MzIzMV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDg1NjU3NzE@._V1_UY317_CR130,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(75,'Mathew Darcy',NULL,'Matthew Mark (Mathew Darcy) D\'Arcy is an American actor and a younger cousin of actress <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm4161755?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">D\'Arcy Fellona</a>. After graduating from Drexel University, Mathew traveled to South Korea for the Department of State\'s Critical Language Scholarship and Fulbright Fellowship.<br><br>Mathew spent two years in South Korea, making his entry into the Korean entertainment industry in his second year. His film debut came when he was cast as General MacArthur\'s scribe officer in <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4939066?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Battle for Incheon: Operation Chromite</a> (2016). Working with Director <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0497565?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">John H. Lee</a> alongside <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000553?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Liam Neeson</a> solidified Mathew\'s interest in acting, and he soon after made appearances on South Korean TV Networks including TVN - <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3294962?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Saturday Night Live Korea</a> (2011), KBS \'Good Morning\' - Haphazard Neighborhood Travel, web and TV commercials, as well as in the Korean drama and KPOP sectors.<br><br>Mathew returned to the States in 2016 and booked a lead role in Kai Liang\'s Philadelphia-based student short \'The Bandaged Heart,\' followed by a featured role in <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1139726?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Neil Burger</a>\'s <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1987680?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">The Upside</a> (2017).<br><br>During the latter half of 2017, Mathew was cast in a supporting role in the upcoming Korean tap-dancing drama <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt7046974?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Swing Kids</a> (2018), directed by <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm3292009?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Hyeong-Cheol Kang</a>.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'8376569','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjAzOTMyNDcyOF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODA4OTk5OTE@._V1_UY317_CR4,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(76,'Gary Ayash',NULL,'Gary is an actor known for House of Cards (2012-2015), Slow Learners (2015), Creed (2015), Sally Pacholok (2015), Jackie (2017) and Imperium (2016). After 38 years working in the healthcare diagnostic business and retiring as a Senior Global Product Education Specialist in 2012, Gary took a recommendation from a friend to go to an open audition for a new Netflix series, House of Cards, Season 1, and was happy he did. After submitting and being cast as a background actor in this series shortly after, he became hooked and looked forward to pursuing this venture as a new hobby. As a result, he has enjoyed being in over 85 productions since from 2012 to July 2016 so far, including several different TV series, major motion pictures, Independent films, government training industrial films and also appearing in a music video promoting the 2014 World Cup Soccer Championships. After only 2 ½ years enjoying these opportunities, he was fortunate to become SAG-AFTRA eligible after appearing in the Sylvester Stallone and Michael B. Jordan\'s major motion picture, CREED, and joined the Guild in March, 2015. Gary has had speaking roles in independent films and historical reenactments, such as National Geographic\'s TV series American Genius, episode Edison vs. Tesla, as an example. He\'s had recurring roles on House of Cards with Kevin Spacey as a White House Press Corp Reporter and VEEP with Julia Louis-Dreyfus. His acting age range is 50\'s to 60\'s years old and has had other roles as a senator, police officer, reporter, still photographer, a WWI Treaty of Versailles French Delegate, WWII German Industrialist, murder suspect, murder victim, father of a murder victim, 1860\'s businessman, and a 1700\'s witch hunter to name a few. Needless to say that this has not only been a wonderful hobby for Gary, but also a wonderful second career enjoying these exciting experiences, meeting so many fantastic actors and fellow acting friends along the way, and looking forward to more future opportunities in the business.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7111794','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTU1MDEwODI5Ml5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTAzOTk1OTE@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(77,'Laura Hart',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4464653','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMmY1Nzk3MmMtMDg0YS00MGE4LWI2NzEtOGFhYmJhODU1NTY2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjAzNzE2NDU@._V1_UY317_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(78,'Annie Pisapia',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7607949','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYWQ2NzhkNzMtYzQ4ZS00OWM0LTljYzItMWE0NmI3YzA3ZWFjL2ltYWdlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjg3MzUwMjU@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(79,'Nikki Corinne Thomas','Nicole Corinne DiTizio',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2237400','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDRmMjc5MTItOTU2Mi00NTFlLWE3NmEtOGMzNTkwN2RkZGVhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyOTc0MTczMA@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(80,'Nikee Warren',NULL,'Nikee is a 2018 SPIRAL Film & Music Awards, American \"Best Film Actress\" recipient and TV and Theater Actress. Nikee is who was born and raised in West Philadelphia and is the third oldest of seven siblings. Nikee graduated from South Philadelphia High School where she studied Business Law. Nikee continued her education at the University of Phoenix where she received both, her Bachelor\'s Degree in Business Management and her Masters in Human Resource Management.<br><br>In 2013, Nikee joined Inspired Arts at Love Kingdom Fellowship where she performed in the following productions: \"Mary the Mother of Jesus,\" \"When the Past Meets the Present\" and \"A Gossiper in the Empty Tomb.\"<br><br>In 2014, Nikee joined the Wilmington Drama League and landed the lead role as Daya in \"Nathan the Wise.\" Also in 2014, Nikee joined the Spring Lake Theater in Spring Lake New Jersey and landed the role as Chiffon (Urchin) in \"Little Shop of Horrors.\"<br><br>Nikee would go on to accept another role in \"Little Shop of Horrors,\" as Ronette (Urchin), at The Barnstormer\'s Theater in Ridley Park, Pennsylvania.<br><br>Nikee grew up singing with her father in his gospel band. With training from her father, years later she would use her voice in many musical productions.<br><br>In 2015, Nikee discovered that a career in TV/Film was what she really wanted to pursue and so turned all her focus to these areas of acting. Since 2015, Nikee would land roles in many films such as Cookeville, which was her first film, Emergency Landing, Thanksgiving with the Moretti\'s; The Good Wives Club; Second Sight, Second Chance and a many, many more.<br><br>Nikee has been nominated Best Actress for her role in the Web Series, Faith vs. Mountains.<br><br>Nikee received her acting training from Inspired Arts in Philadelphia, PA, Actor\'s Models and Talent for Christ (AMTC) and Aiken Acts Performing Arts.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'8133003','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZTU0NTYyZDEtZGZlYy00MjVmLTkxMmUtM2EyYmY3ZDA0OTI5XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(81,'Dennis P. Marburger',NULL,'I have been acting and singing since I was a child. My love of both art forms lead me to achieve a Theater degree in college.<br><br>I\'ve performed in numerous community theater organizations throughout my life with over 40 theatrical stage credits to my name. Nearly all of these productions were musicals, as I love using my strong baritone voice to enhance the roles I\'m playing. In August of 2016, I began doing on-camera work and immediately fell in love with this new genre. I am now working on a full-time TV, Film, Commercial, Industrial, & Voice-Over career!<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9259643','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNWQzNGM4ODUtYWZhZC00MThiLWI1ODAtOTEzZWM4MGRjY2Q0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzY4OTA0NjI@._V1_UY317_CR26,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(82,'Ricky Garcia',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2049403','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNjBlZjBmMWMtYmQ2Ny00MWQwLWFmYmEtY2ZmYmRjYWUwZWRjXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(83,'Fernando Mateo Jr.',NULL,'Born and raised on the Lower East Side of Manhattan, Fernando Mateo Jr. is a former college football player at the University of Albany. A lifelong athlete, he then became a Krav Maga instructor post college while working for the family business.<br><br>With performing always being something he wanted to do, he finally caved into the desire and started acting at the age of 26. He began taking classes in NYC and started his journey doing showcases and plays for two years. He then moved on to do a year and a half at the William Esper Studio.<br><br>After Esper, Fernando began to focus on film and television. In 2013, he finally got his first network credit in LAW AND ORDER: SVU. Since then he has appeared in numerous films and television shows. Most recently you can see him in the last episode of BLACKLIST: Redemption, THE UPSIDE (feat. Bryan Cranston and Kevin Hart), season 2 of JESSICA JONES and this upcoming season of ORANGE IS THE NEW BLACK.<br><br>Fernando currently resides in NYC with his rescue dog, Hal Jordan and when not acting enjoys photography and videography.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2708472','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDk5OTAyZDAtMjlmZi00NDgxLWFjZWYtNWIyMGI4N2ZkNGI4XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjEzMTk5NTI@._V1_UY317_CR131,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(84,'Glen Macnow',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2407691','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(85,'Rick Irwin',NULL,'Rick Irwin was born and raised outside of Philadelphia. He became interested in acting when he started going to the movies with his father. Irwin was accepted into the Syracuse University School of Drama, whose alumni include Aaron Sorkin, Frank Langella, Vanessa Williams, Taye Diggs, Vera Farmiga and Tom Everett Scott.<br><br>After completing his time at Syracuse, Irwin moved to New York City, where he continued his training and worked on stage regionally and on tour. Irwin soon relocated to Los Angeles and started working continuously in film, TV, theater and commercials.<br><br>On the big screen, Irwin has worked with Orlando Bloom on The Good Doctor, Jesse Eisenberg and Aziz Ansari on 30 Minutes or Less and James Gandolfini on Mr. Gandolfini\'s last completed film, Enough Said, also starring Julia Louis-Dreyfus. Tommy Lee Jones cast Irwin in The Homesman, starring Mr. Jones, Meryl Streep and Hilary Swank, which premiered at Cannes. Irwin plays the lead in the first-ever virtual reality feature film, Career Opportunities in Organized Crime, which debuted at South by Southwest. Irwin will appear in a number of upcoming films including The Upside starring Bryan Cranston, Kevin Hart and Nicole Kidman. He also plays the main character in the psychological thriller The Luring, about a man with dissociative amnesia.<br><br>Rick is married to actor Deborah Lynn Meier.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'0410444','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNmJhZGRhNmItYzAxNC00MmIzLWE2OWQtZGJlYTNlOGYyNWNmXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR7,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(86,'Gemma McIlhenny',NULL,'Gemma McIlhenny born Gemma Smith is a Philly born Singer & Actress. Born to parents, The Late Barbara Smith an Educator and Dance & Drama Instructor, and James Smith a skilled Mechanic. Gemma was raised in the West Philadelphia area with her sister, and attended Overbrook High School as a Fine Arts Major. Under the instruction of her mother and The Philadelphia Arts League Gemma developed a love of theater and acting, performing in various productions around the city. During her teenage years she volunteered in various community service based Artistic Endeavors. The primary focus was allow inner-city youth a safe environment to express themselves through the Arts . She later majored in Fine Arts at Philadelphia Community College before pursuing a career in law enforcement. Since then, Gemma has taught dance and drama, is a recording artist on various projects and continues her acting career.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'8086679','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOGM2YzBjZjUtOGQzZS00YmY3LTliMDgtMGM5YWI0MzRkMjJkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjY5ODgzMjY@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(87,'Les Price',NULL,'Les Price is an actor/stuntman who was born and raised in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania.<br><br>He is best known for his stunt work on the One Plus 5T Android smart phone commercial, his voiceover work on (SECTION 9) and narrator of (Highway 666) as well as his acting roles in Elementary (2015) Death House (2016) Alpha Rift (2017) and The Upside (2017).<br><br>Upcoming roles include: STRAY (2018) SOLAR (2018) CREED 2 (2018) and NOCTURNAL (2019)<br><br>Les got his start coming from an entertainment background, having been raised by a family of local entertainers. The apple doesn\'t fall far from the tree! Les\'s witty personality and vast knowledge in everything from fitness to film provided the tools necessary for him to transition into the internet personality he is today. Although he has always had artistic endeavors, his move into the acting realm occurred when he became nationally recognized as Vin Diesel\'s double. Tapped to become a celebrity look alike, he began hosting Red carpet premieres as \"The Fast the and Furious\" franchises lead character \"Dominic Toretto,\" and expanded his presence by traveling as a Cosplay guest to various conventions throughout the United States. Due to his over the top costumes and his engaging personality, as well as being known as the \"man with a thousand voices,\" he quickly became a fan favorite.<br><br>Les uses his ability to mimic various accents and dialects in his acting roles as well as his physical prowess from many years of training in MMA/stunts to break the mold. With his unique skill set, and consistent dedication to perfecting his craft, Les has easily become someone to lookout for in 2018.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9451983','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNTdlZGVlNzItODNmZC00MjA1LTlkYzYtNTBhOTBjZWQ0ZjIxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(88,'Tyrone Mitchell Henderson',NULL,'Born in Geneva, New York. Tyrone is considered one of the most prominent African American theatre actors in the country. Tyrone attended the school of hard knocks... AADA, Hobart College and SUNY Stony Brook included. Highlights include, the National Tour of Bring in Da\'Noise Bring in Da\' Funk, as well as work with Phylicia Rashad, Patrick Stewart, Suzanne Bertish and Anthony Stewart Head. Tyrone has worked extensively on works of William Shakespeare. He\'s been honored with The Leon Rabin and Dallas Theatre Critics awards, and an AUDELCO award nominee. He\'s worked with theatre directors George C. Wolfe, Kenny Leon, Timothy Douglas, Liesl Tommy, Scott Schwartz, and James Lapine.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2060865','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDA3MzUzMDgtMzc0Ni00M2VmLThlMmMtZGM2M2Q3ZmM4OTAwXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzE2ODIyNQ@@._V1_UY317_CR131,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(89,'Madeleine Woolner',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7371673','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BY2ZmZWZlMjUtYThkNS00MmJjLTkxZjAtNGRhMGE1OWNkOGM2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjAxMzQwOTY@._V1_UY317_CR138,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(90,'Julie Potter',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5453212','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMGYyMWNmOWYtYzFkZC00NWJlLThlNTEtYjc1NzBmNWVlNmNmXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzQyOTgyOTQ@._V1_UY317_CR19,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(91,'Charles W Harris III',NULL,'Charles W. Harris III is a Philadelphia, Pennsylvania native born and raised. Charles is a film, television, and theatre actor who has made his presence known in various films like Creed, Glass, Creed2, Stomp the yard 2, House of cards and many more. He began acting while in college, where he then graduated with a BA in criminal justice, where he continued his work as a law enforcement officer of Pennsylvania. Charles recently resigned from his Law Enforcement career to pursue acting full-time.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7585473','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BY2RhNWZlODItZjRhMS00MTc0LTk4ZTUtNzdmZTM3NDY1OTI0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR53,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(92,'Tom Schmitt',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4352078','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzYwNzA2MzczMV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTA3MTI1NjE@._V1_UY317_CR91,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(93,'Diego Aguirre',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3605070','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZjZkNTk0Y2UtZjNhMy00OGM1LTgzMDAtMTcyZWFhM2M0YzUyL2ltYWdlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjAwMjI4NDk@._V1_UY317_CR131,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(94,'Nekoda Phillips',NULL,'Nekoda Phillips was born on December 14th in Cherry Hill, New Jersey to Edward Phillips, a chemical engineer and Mary Ann Vilenica, a high school chemistry teacher. He largely has English, Irish, German, and Croatian ancestry. He is the youngest of two children, his sister is Deborah, who were raised in Medford Lakes, New Jersey. He fathered two sons: Phoenix Phillips and Sydney Phillips. Nekoda is not married.<br><br>Nekoda began playing the piano at age four and picked up the guitar at age fourteen. He mainly listened to old Elvis Presley and The Beatles records to teach himself to sing which ultimately earned him a unique crooning pop sound.<br><br>Nekoda means it when he says, \"I have an IQ like the inside of a triangle...\" and then sighs saying \"... and it\'s been both a blessing and a curse which has prodded me my entire life like a dark twister filled with lit up flying question marks and exclamation points.\"<br><br>After founding several businesses throughout his life, his funnest business activity is Equity Options Investments, and occasionally starting a new business venture.<br><br>Although Nekoda was invited but declined to audition for a lead role in the Twentieth Century Fox film Taps while attending Admiral Farragut Naval Academy, and although many years later, he serendipitously landed a lead role in a TV Pilot, he did not enthusiastically pursue acting until 2017.<br><br>He works with the utmost professionalism, expertise and humor, and is especially interested in Principle and Specialty roles in film. He is a SAG/AFTRA member.<br><br>As a Philotheist & Philanthropist, Nekoda has spent many years studying all the arts, sciences and religions of the world to discover the true meaning of life. His answer is \"Love\" and so he always desires the best for everyone.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9800039','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYTIxYzNjZmQtMDk5ZS00OTA3LTg3ZjgtZjM4ZGZiYmIwMmVmXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzkyMTczMTE@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(95,'Jayson Williams',NULL,'Jayson Ward Williams, originally a product of Harrisburg, PA, discovered at the age of 8, that acting was to be his lot in life. Even after being discouraged by many, he decided to set forth a course of action, to obtain this dream.<br><br>After graduating from the Harrisburg Arts Magnet, he was accepted to The Carnegie Mellon School of Drama, where he received a BFA in Acting. Upon graduation, Jayson headed for New York, where he continues to have success as a working actor.<br><br>His credits include guest starring and supporting roles on HBO\'s VEEP, White Collar, Law & Order, The Sopranos, NYPD Blue, and the TNT movie Word of Honor. He is soon to begin production on his first big screen role in the upcoming Richard Gere/Dakota Fanning picture \"Franny.\"<br><br>He has done principal work in numerous national commercials, some of which include Burger King, Subway, Lowes, Fed -Ex and KFC, along with stage work in various places.<br><br>Jayson has also taught acting at the world renowned Freedom Theater of Philadelphia and at the prestigious Pennsylvania Governors School for the Arts.<br><br>He has recently begun his journey into the directing realm. Directing a Music Video, a spec commercial for Doritos and The Philadelphia based talk show, \"The Hype.\"<br><br>Along with these ventures, Jayson has also just finished writing his first sitcom entitled \"Paid Parking.\"<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1426873','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjlmMTVjY2EtNTViOC00ZWNjLWFmNjItYWUxMzdmNmUyY2ZiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTk4NDEwMTg@._V1_UY317_CR6,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(96,'Adriana Alveario',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2281512','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMWYzZjExMTktNDkxMy00YzhlLWIxYzQtZmRiNTgzYTRkMmE1XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzg5MTI3MA@@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(97,'Damian Muziani',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2049635','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDdmMjM1NzUtYmQyZi00MmFlLTg2NDYtNzllNmRlODRiM2Q4XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTExODMxMzM@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(98,'Charmar Jeter',NULL,'Strikingly handsome Charmar Te\'King Jeter is an model actor writer with and edgy eye for creativity. The heart of the Steel City is where his creative instinct and determination was born. This blossomed into theater and voice overs that helped him shine bright on film TV and the big screen. Magnetically drawn to acting he has starred in films such as Creed, Quantico, Billions Homeland, Madam Secretary, The Good Fight and several others. Being the farther of 2 beautiful children he lives to inspire and is very determined to show that the unbelievable is just a myth. This empathy came to life when his commercial was an still is on the back of 35 city publications transits and climbing. He lives to grow teach and inspire believing his blessings will becoming others stepping stones.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'6968214','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(99,'Michael Quinlan',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0703727','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(100,'Christopher Rex Stone',NULL,'Raised in rural Meyersdale, Pennsylvania, Christopher Rex Stone attended Cornell University where he earned a BS in The College of Architecture, Art, and Planning. Christopher has done a range of stage, film, TV, and commercial work.<br><br>He is based in New York City, works with bi-coastal representation, and is interested in collaborating on both early-development and in-production projects.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'6107672','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTQxMzZkZGUtMjFlNy00YTNhLWFmNTgtYzE0YjE1NmJkY2RiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDMyNjE3NTg@._V1_UY317_CR135,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(101,'Rachel Christopher',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7708788','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTE4ZDg4ZDMtNmUxYS00N2FjLWEyZWYtYzNhMGQyMjBhYmQ2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjU5MjMxNTE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(102,'Marco Rosario',NULL,'Marco Rosario is a Philadelphia based actor. A recent graduate of Temple University in Philadelphia, PA, he is also a mental/behavioral health therapist. He began his acting career in 2014 by incorporating a film student into his vision of recreating the end scene of Charlie Chaplin\'s Modern Times for him and his wife\'s wedding reception intro. From there he has worked in over 15 student and independent films and continues to build his resume.<br><br>He has expanded his acting career along the east coast and has amassed several featured commercials, including a national spot for Mattress Warehouse and regional work for Carmax, Camelback Mountain Resort, and H2OBX. Along with film and commercial work, he has appeared on various television shows, including House of Cards, 40 North, and Million Dollar Settlement.<br><br>Aside from acting and working as a therapist, Marco has been a DJ for 20 years and thoroughly enjoys incorporating all of his passions into new and exciting avenues in order to expand his career. He intends to branch into writing and create multiple projects in the future.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7098753','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNWUwMTM3ZGItNmE3OC00ZTczLWFmMTQtOTE0OGM0M2MwM2YyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjcyNzI5MjM@._V1_UY317_CR17,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(103,'Dave Ferrier',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4665138','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BM2FlNjliOGUtMWJlZi00YjEzLTkwOGItYjk5MzIxYWY1ZDdjXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(104,'Phillip Chorba','Phillip-James Manfredini Chorba','Phillip was born in New York City and grew up in Allendale, New Jersey. His mother, Celeste (Manfredini), is Italian-American and is a professional still life artist, and his father, Thomas A. Chorba, is Hungarian-American and works as an executive recruiter.<br><br>He graduated from St. Joseph Regional HS in Montvale, NJ where he competed in Football, Lacrosse and Powerlifting. He then graduated from Union College in Schenectady, NY where he majored in Theatre, played college football and was a member of Chi Psi fraternity. Phillip took his first acting class while nursing a football injury in his sophomore year. He only took the class because of the theatre\'s proximity to his dorm room, and was immediately hooked.<br><br>Upon graduating, Phillip moved to New York City to pursue an acting career. He studied improvisation at The Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre from 2005-2008. On September 6th, 2008 he married his high school sweetheart, Dawn Olejarz. A short time after returning from his honeymoon he met Steve Beauchamp on the set of \"Ugly Betty.\" Steve is now Phillip\'s acting coach and mentor.<br><br>Phillip now resides in Astoria, Queens.<br>\n         ','1983-03-14 00:00:00',NULL,'New York, New York, USA','4585077','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(105,'Valerie Logan',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3811818','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYzM5MTc5NDQtOGEzMy00ZTM1LWI4MWItYzc3MzQ1NjczNzBkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR130,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(106,'Erin Shann',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8497121','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZTllOTAxNTQtZDg4Mi00NDI0LWFhZGItNTBkNDliNDUxYTE0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQzMDc4MDc@._V1_UY317_CR130,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(107,'Michael J. Lyons',NULL,'Michael Lyons began his acting career as a child while living in Paris, France. He appeared in commercials and the film \"Paris When It Sizzles\" with Tony Curtis, Audrey Hepburn and William Holden. He also did dubbing for both French and American movies using his bi-lingual abilities. Upon his return to the U.S., he performed in a variety of theatrical roles and worked on the stage crew of the Valley Forge Music Fair (outside Philadelphia), working side by side with legends such as Gordon MacRae, Carol Lawrence, Robert Morse and Chita Rivera. After graduating from the University of Notre Dame, he went to work in the business world, bypassing an opportunity to pursue his acting vocation. Fifteen years later he resurrected his dormant acting career while living in New York and landed a national TV spot for \"Honey Bunches of Oats\" cereal. From there he joined SAG and began to book commercials, TV roles and other jobs on a regular basis including \"All My Children\" and an Advil commercial that ran on national TV for 4 years. All the while, he kept his day job until 2014 when he turned all of his efforts full time to acting and motivational speaking. Mike has garnered numerous roles in films,TV shows, commercials and more than 350 live appearances on home shopping network QVC as a product host. Credits include speaking parts in \"The Sixth Sense\", \"All My Children, \"Veep\", \"What Would You Do\", Arrest & Trial\", \"Outsiders\" and as Speaker of the House in Season 4 of House of Cards.<br>\n         ','1951-08-10 00:00:00',NULL,'Darby, Pennsylvania, USA','0529130','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTk5MzU5MjI3MF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTEyOTMzNzE@._V1_UY317_CR46,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(108,'Scott Martin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6097612','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNjA0YzUwMDUtYWU5Ny00N2M0LThiMjUtMjM2M2JhNTViYjYxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzgzMzMwNzI@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(109,'Jibril Goodman',NULL,'Jibril Ali Goodman was born in Philadelphia April 2, 1985 in Philadelphia Pa. He is the eighth and last child by his father Jimmie Murphy who is a business owner and mechanic in Philadelphia, and he is the second oldest of five children by his mother Michele Goodman who was a CNA. Jibril always wanted to act but instead went to college for Networking Systems Administration and graduated on the dean\'s list. His first movie he was in is creed as a boxing spectator.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7171099','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(110,'Kittson O\'Neill',NULL,'Kittson grew up in Connecticut and Australia. She is a Philadelphia actor with extensive New York and Regional credits including: The Public Theater, Philadelphia Theater Company, People\'s Light, Lantern Theater, and Boise Contemporary Theater. She is the Artistic Director of Shakespeare in Clark Park and a freelance theater director. She has worked as a literary manager and dramaturg for InterAct Theater Company, New Jersey Repertory Company and PlayPenn. She has worked in dozens of commercials, industrials, experimental works and voice overs as well as the movies and television shows listed here.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'0642230','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZTUyODM2YjEtYTcyYS00ODQ2LTg3MTAtODgyZGEyZWI1YjUyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODI2MzY0NzA@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(111,'Kimberly S. Fairbanks',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2718408','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(112,'Dominique Janelle',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8587153','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDRiYzcwMjktYTIwYS00YzdhLWE0OWYtODczZjIxNWVkYzNkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(113,'Nancy Sokerka',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1115301','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNmNjMjIxMzctMTZkYS00ZGY3LWJiMmMtY2QzZWE1MjRlMjc2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTkwNjUzNTI@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(114,'Aleksandra Svetlichnaya',NULL,'EARLY LIFE Aleksandra Svetlichnaya was born in Kharkov, Ukraine and later relocated to Philadelphia, Pennsylvania with her family. She is fluent in both English and Russian.<br><br>Aleksandra showed an interest for the creative arts at a remarkably young age. She began taking art and dance classes before the age of seven and at ten started training in martial arts. It was clear that she was meant to one day work in the entertainment industry.<br><br>Having a strong mind for business as well, Aleksandra wanted to go to college and attain a creative, yet practical degree. Within three years she earned, with Honors, a Bachelor\'s of Science in Fashion Design, with a minor in Fashion Marketing and Business. She then began working as a costume designer for large-scale entertainment attractions, dancesport, theater and, eventually, independent films. That was where she found the opportunity to professionally try something she had always wanted to do - acting.<br><br>CAREER Aleksandra appears in lead roles in feature films \"The Bates Haunting\" (2012) as \"Lily Hanson\" and \"OFF-Time\" (2016) as \"Bridget,\" opposite Adam LaVorgna. She was also cast in the featured role of a \"Supermodel\" in the new installment of the \"Rocky\" franchise - \"Creed\" (2015). As a life-long action fan, working on set with Sly Stallone himself, as well as talented actor Michael B. Jordan and professional boxer Tony Bellew, was a dream come true.<br><br>In the spring of 2016, Aleksandra was cast in the role of a female prison guard captain in the highly anticipated film \"Death House\" (2016), which is billed as the \"Expendables of Horror.\" She is also part of the \"Death House\" Stunt Team, performing tactical and fight stunt work. And in the summer of 2015, Aleksandra was cast as a series regular in a new TV sitcom pilot. By then she has already appeared in NBC\'s \"Do No Harm\" (2013) as featured \"Ian\'s Girl\" in episode 7; in Bio Channel\'s \"Killer Profile: Bobby Joe Long\" (2012) as victim \"Elizabeth Loudenback\" and she was cast in a featured part as an ex-girlfriend of the former United States President in USA Network\'s award-winning \"Political Animals\" (2012).<br><br>Her other credits include various commercials, TV promos, short films and major feature films Paranoia (2013), Dead Man Down (2013) and SAFE (2012). As a model, Aleksandra has worked with NIKE, MARS Drinks, Dove Hot Chocolate, Alterra Coffee,Confrontational Clothing, Shop Sixty Five, Pamela Ptak and has been published in The Philadelphia Inquirer and national magazines\"Aspira\" and \"Obscurae\".<br><br> WRITING, PRODUCING, DIRECTING In the fall of 2014, Aleksandra made her first foray into screenwriting, producing and directing with a short film titled \"DINNER\" in which she also starred in. \"DINNER\" (2015) was chosen as an Official Selection at CON Film Festival and screened at Wizard World Philly, The Philadelphia Geek Awards Film Fest and Diamond on the Rough Cut. The film was called \"a delicious slice of genre filmmaking\" by Geekadelphia and a \"badass\" \"quirky action comedy\" by PhillyVoice. James Bamford, Stunt Coordinator/Fight Designer/Director on Arrow, The Flash & DC\'s Legends of Tomorrow, called the movie \"fun\" and praised its\' monster make up and effects. \"DINNER 2\" (working title) - also written, produced, directed by and starring Aleksandra - is currently in production and is slated to premiere in late summer of 2016.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'4303879','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(115,'Katia Crivellari',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8277110','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzRiMDRiNTAtZDk2Yy00MjY5LWE2N2MtMWY4ODljNmJkNDZlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDY5MTYyNTQ@._V1_UY317_CR6,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(116,'Ricky Roma',NULL,'Ricky Roma was born in the city of Philadelphia. He\'s been acting since he was a kid but got his first real taste of the camera in 1999 when he landed a supporting roll in Blair Cobbs (writer of \"Next Day Air\") short film \"sins of a father\"aka\"Blaze Of Glory\".He\'s worked on television shows like\"Hack\",\"Cold Case\",\"The Simple Life,\"Do No Harm\"and feature films such as Safe and Creed.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2684879','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545847337),(117,'Chuck Rayner',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3961553','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BODNhY2JjMmUtZTQxMC00MzVhLWEyOTYtZDQ2Nzc0NjE5ZTIwXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR108,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(118,'J.J. Phillips',NULL,'J.J. Phillips is an accomplished and award winning theatre, film, and television actor from San Antonio, Texas, residing in New York City. He has performed in countless feature films, TV shows, and commercials, as well as New York and Regional Theatre.<br><br>In addition to acting on screen and stage, J.J. has had the opportunity to perform for thousands of people as a performer/announcer at SeaWorld San Antonio. During his tenure at SeaWorld, he hosted several events and large music concerts, including Kumbia All-Stars, Pat Benatar and Bret Michaels. J.J. continues to host and emcee for numerous corporate and private events including the 2008 NCAA Men\'s Final Four and as the In Arena Host for the San Antonio Stars for the WNBA in 2012.<br><br>On stage, J.J. has had the good fortune of flexing his acting muscles in shows like Brighton Beach Memoirs (Eugene), The Boys Next Door (Arnold), Guys and Dolls (Benny), and Metamorphoses to name a few.<br><br>J.J. is excited to have had a recurring role on Nashville on ABC, working along side series regulars Connie Britton, Will Chase, Clare Bowen, and Sam Palladio, and with series regulars Tracy Spiradakos and David Lyons in the season 2 premiere of Revolution on NBC. Other credits include The Lying Game and The Affair. J.J. can also be seen sharing the screen with Vin Diesel and Paul Walker 