siness Administration. Got his start after attending a casting call for \"House of Cards\" in 2013. Since then has appeared in over seventy TV shows, industrials, commercials and movies.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'6518022','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545856201),(588,'Adam Zebediah Joseph','Adam Abad','Adam is a SAG / AFTRA, AEA college educated actor, self-taught professional artist, and children\'s book author/illustrator from the United States. He has always immersed himself in many creative pursuits from theatre, film, television, commercials, music & dance to visual art and illustrations. He is a graduate of the Southern NJ Academy of Performing Arts ( 2002 Valedictorian). He earned a Presidential Academic Scholarship and a Presidential Talent Scholarship to Rowan University, College of Fine & Performing Arts (2005). As an artist, he has sold artwork to many private collectors around the world and his work has also been selected to appear as part of the set décor on national television for ABC Studios in California. His work as an author has gained attention in the UK and his first children\'s book \"Lillee Can Be\" has been released in London. It is a Gender Equality book encouraging young girls to surpass preconceived expectations about their gender. For more information about it, check out the promotional video on Youtube. Simply type \"Lillee Can Be\" into the search bar. \"Lillee Can Be\" is available as paperback and e-book at Waterstones in England, Hodges Figgis in Ireland, Bokus in Sweden, Barnes & Noble in the US, and Amazon internationally. He is enjoying his unanticipated success as an author and he has many more books to come! He looks forward to every unexpected endeavor and relishes each experience to the fullest. As always, he thanks his mother for all of her support and is excited to support her on all of her endeavors. He is estranged from his father and much of his paternal extended family with no interest in reconciliation. Aside from all things creative, Adam adores animals and wildlife, and has a particular affinity for ferrets. Live life to the fullest and never be afraid to stare down an obstacle because there is nothing but greatness on the other side.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7662127','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjY1ZWViNzAtZTE0Mi00ODAxLWE4MmUtYTAyZjRmMTVlNGQ2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjMyNzIwOTE@._V1_UY317_CR16,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(589,'Natalie Pellegrino',NULL,'Natalie \"Tilly\" Pellegrino is a 15 year old actress in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. She is best known for Glass (2019) directed by M. Night Shyamalan. In addition to being an actress she is also a singer and instrumentalist. Natalie also loves to create short films and skits with her friends at her high school. She is coming out with another short called \"Weirder Stuff\" in 2018.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9320112','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545856201),(590,'Robert Shropshire',NULL,'Born in Richmond, Virginia, in 1990 at MCV. In 2008, majoring in Philosophy at Virginia Commonwealth University while also acting in student films and modeling, eventually discovered an opportunity appearing as a background extra in season 2-4 of AMC\'s \"TURN: Washington\'s Spies\" 2014-2017 and PBS\'s \"Mercy Street.\"<br><br>In 2015, moving to Philadelphia, Pennsylvania in order to focus on film & music production, as well as figure modeling at UArts and Fleisher Art Memorial while also developing a noise label \'Echo Options.\' Currently helping produce various local Philly-based projects, recently the 48 hour film project and South SillyCam.<br><br>\"Alroy Mellor\" is an alternate pen/professional-name crafted by Robert in 2014 while living in the attic of the gatehouse in Hollywood Cemetery located in Oregon Hill, Richmond, VA. The name is more-or-less a simple phonetic combination of both Parental units names and is attributed to the many various musical and sound-based art projects based in South Philadelphia established by Shropshire/Mellor while also taking over as a completely new creative entity/individual. Bordering on a Philosophy experiment exploring personal identity and an esoteric performance piece based on experimental postmodern theory/new age spirituality, it\'s resulted in a new social media presence, thus Alroy continues to exist as a recording artist and producer of noise/music.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'4741866','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545856201),(591,'Marcelo Martinessi',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Asunción, Paraguay','3308584','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BN2FlODIyMjQtMTUzMi00N2ZiLTgzODMtY2U2Yjc0NDQxMWRkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTU0NjEzNzY@._V1_UY317_CR131,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545856201),(592,'Hilde Berg',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0073783','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545856201),(593,'Tito Cabrera Vendeuvre',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0092560',NULL,0),(594,'Agustina Chiarino',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1887162','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545856201),(595,'Fernando Epstein',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Uruguay','0258459','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545856201),(596,'Christoph Friedel',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0295016','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545856201),(597,'Júlia Murat',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0613580','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545856201),(598,'Marina Perales',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4252459','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545856201),(599,'Sebastián Peña Escobar',NULL,'Sebastian Pena Escobar (Asuncion, 1973). Producer, writer and independent researcher. He studied Economics in Paraguay and got a Master in Business Administration from The University of Kansas. During the last decade, he developed, produced and managed several cultural ventures and projects. From Pomelo Editorial he led the creation of magazines, books, and audiovisual content. From El Ojo Salvaje (EOS), he has been organizing the Photography Month in Paraguay since 2007. He has published essays, prose, and poetry as well as numerous op-eds, articles, and columns in local magazines. As a producer in Puatarara Films S.A, he has co-produced the documentary-film Chicas Nuevas 24 Horas (Spain, 2015) about global human trafficking (nominated Best Documentary, Goya Awards, Spain 2016). He has also co-produced the feature film Guarani (Argentina, 2015), winner of Best Foreign Film (Festival do Gramado, Brasil, 2016) and Vision Europea Award at Ventana Sur (Buenos Aires, 2014). From La Babosa Cine, he produced The Heiresses, from Marcelo Martinessi (Berlinale Competition 2018, double Silver Bear and Fispresci winner). He was also the executive producer and director of production. In 2015 he participated in Framework, Torino Film Lab (2015) where The Heiresses won a Production Award. In 2017 he participated in Interdoc Documentary Masterclasses (Serbia). Attended Doc Montevideo 2017, Dok Leipzig 2017 and Documenta Madrid 2018. Sebastian is currently developing a creative documentary and setting up a local distributing strategy for films produced and co-produced in Paraguay.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7809897','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545856201),(600,'Xavier Rocher',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3620445','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1