ascinated in martial arts and gymnastics. He found a sport that combines martial arts and gymnastics, it is called tricking. He used to train a lot by himself, but after he went to San Jose, California in 2008 where he met one of the best trickers out there, he started to train with Guillermo \'KJER\' Bongers (team StreetTrickz). Since then he has progressed his skills, while learning from the best. Tricking put him in touch with many different people, from stunt performers to actors and a lot people alike. These people helped him get in to the film industry.<br><br>That is how he came in contact with stunt team Hammy de Beukelaer. After training with this amazing stunt team he got the opportunity to do this line of work at the age of 22. Stunt team Hammy de Beukelaer is the best Dutch stunt team there is. They provide national and international stunts of the highest level, with over 50 years of combined expertise in this industry lead by Willem de Beukelaer and Marco Maas. Nick still works closely with stunt team Hammy de Beukelaer. With their support he is still is growing in the stunt industry.<br><br>In 2013 discovered that there was a British Stunt Register in the United Kingdom, after a lot of consideration he decided to train for it. The requirements were that you need to have 6 certified qualifications and at least 60 days in front of camera as an actor or supporting artist. It took 1 year and 4 months to complete his training. That means almost everyday was dedicated to training and work as an supporting artist. The different disciplines he trained for were: <ul><li>Karate</li><li>High Diving</li><li>Gymnastics</li><li>Trampoline</li><li>PADI Dive Master</li><li>SPA (Rock Climbing)</li></ul><br><br>On 9th of July 2015 Nick managed to get on the British Stunt Register, and now he is a proud member of the British Stunt Register.<br><br>Nick\'s first T.V appearance was on a Dutch T.V show, a small part with big consequences. From that day on he has appeared national (The Netherlands) and international production for films, live theatre, commercials and many more as a stunt performer.<br>\n         ','1987-08-06 00:00:00',NULL,'The Hague, Zuid-Holland, Netherlands','4706514','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYzgzNTZjYTMtYzY5OC00Y2M0LTk0MjAtNjgxZWQ5OGM0YWVlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjc1NzQ1MTg@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1013,'Patrick Brammall',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1669772','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjE3OTE4MjA1NF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDQxODg5NjE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1014,'Charles Robert Barrett',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1019257','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTMzZGFhMzUtNmQwZS00MmVhLThiZDAtYzA5N2RkZmNjZjEwXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyOTAzMjExMjg@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545881626),(1015,'Adam Collins',NULL,'Actor / stuntman / Director from Nottingham, England. Served six years as a commando in the Royal Marines, spending two operational tours including Afghanistan. Trained specialist in military skills including helicopter abseiling / fast roping, amphibious training, unarmed combat and firearms training. Holds a black belt in Karate and kickboxing. After his Royal Marines service, began his film career in 2012. Appeared in films including <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1961175?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">American Assassin</a> (2017), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4649466?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Kingsman: The Golden Circle</a> (2017), and M:I 6 - Mission Impossible (2018), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3371366?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Transformers: The Last Knight</a> (2017), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5013056?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Dunkirk</a> (2017) and <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0974015?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Justice League</a> (2017).<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5143645','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZmYxY2Y