\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2300975?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Jessabelle</a> (2014), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1408253?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Ride Along</a> (2014), and <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2869728?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Ride Along 2</a> (2016) with notable television roles in <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1390543?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">The Wronged Man</a> (2010), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0773264?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">House of Payne</a> (2006), <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1845866?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Teen Spirit</a> (2011), HBO\'s <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1279972?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Treme</a> (2010), NBC\'s <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt2070791?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Revolution</a> (2012), and Showtime\'s Emmy Award winning series <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1796960?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Homeland</a> (2011). Most recently the landmark min-series <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3315386?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Roots</a> (2016), Netflix\'s <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4574334?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Stranger Things</a> (2016), FX\'s Golden Globe winning series <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4288182?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Atlanta</a> (2016), and OWN\'s hit show <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4419214?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Queen Sugar</a> (2016).<br><br>Lucius is an extraordinarily talented and versatile entertainer and producer. He now lives in Atlanta, GA.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2137633','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTkxOTcyNTQzOV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwNTcwMjE2Nw@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1088,'Patricia French',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0294170','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjIwODk1NzMyMF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzk4NDczOTE@._V1_UY317_CR6,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1089,'Victor McCay',NULL,NULL,'1971-04-22 00:00:00',NULL,'Alabama, USA','1035730','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNWE4NDEzMjMtNzM5Yi00MTIxLTk5ZDgtNmYwOTRmMzlhNjI2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTQ4MTA2MDQ@._V1_UY317_CR6,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1090,'Scott Deal',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4183406','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjMxNTQ5NTI5MV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwOTIxMTY1MDI@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1091,'Carrie Walrond Hood',NULL,'Carrie Walrond Hood is an accomplished actor and producer who thrives as a performer. She has been cast in coveted film roles on Warner Brothers\' \"The Accountant\", 20th Century Fox\'s \"Keeping Up With The Joneses\", and Tyler Perry\'s \"Single Moms Club\" as well as TV roles on such popular shows as ABC\'s \"Kevin (probably) Saves the World\", MTV\'s \"Finding Carter\", The Sundance Channel\'s critically acclaimed \"The Red Road\", as well as roles on \"Survivor\'s Remorse\", \"Satisfaction\", and \"Drop Dead Diva\", and in the recurring role of Dr. Romero on Lifetime\'s \"Devious Maids\". She starred in Kenneth Lin\'s \"Warrior Class\" at Atlanta\'s Tony Award-winning Alliance Theatre. Hood has also had a great deal of commercial success with spots airing consistently over the years both regionally and nationally.<br><br>Carrie brings joy to the most difficult circumstances, while also brainstorming ways to overcome obstacles. She has an openness and enthusiasm that makes her a joy to work with among her colleagues. And Hood has a perseverance to flourish in the ever challenging entertainment industry so that she can tell the stories that touch your heart.<br><br>Carrie\'s love for performing and being in the spotlight started at a young age... dressing up in heels, grabbing a microphone and serenading her family and guests in her home when she was a child. Hood\'s first play was in kindergarten, called \"The Doll and the Scarecrow\". Her grandmother made her doll costume for the show, which was a patchwork of different colored gingham fabrics that Carrie still remembers vividly. She also remembers being embarrassed about holding the scarecrow\'s hand throughout the first song. In adulthood, one of her most memorable roles on stage was in the play \"Warrior Class\", written by Kenneth Lin, the same creative writing force involved in the dynamic Netflix drama \"House of Cards\". The play was directed by Eric Ting and performed at the Alliance Theater in Atlanta. She loved getting to play the multidimensional character, Holly Lillian Eames, every night. The joy of playing this character was that she could not be deemed right or wrong, bur rather varying shades of gray, as the audience weighed whether Eames was virtuous or scandalous. Hood also loved her comedic role in Tyler Perry\'s \"Single Moms Club\' as it was one of her first major opportunities to fully improvise a comedic character in a film.<br><br>But there were twists and turns on Hood\'s road to being a professional actor. She enjoyed theater through high school, but the responsibilities of adulthood called by the time she was in college. Carrie decided to get a \"real job\" working at CNN upon her move to Atlanta. She quickly sought out theater opportunities and began performing weekly with a local improv troupe. The turning point to pursuing acting professionally would come years later, after reading a book called Dream Giver, by Bruce Wilkinson. Not long after hearing this author speak, Carrie took a giant leap of faith and quit her corporate job to become a full time actor... with no agent and a mortgage. But her driving force was her conviction that she had to give acting her all or risk leading an unfulfilled life. And that big risk had a big payoff. Six months later, she got an agent and booked her first commercial role. She also began working in production which eventually led to work as a producer. Carrie has been with the same agency, Houghton Talent, for over 10 years, enjoying both commercial and theatrical success as an actor. She is happily married with two young kids and works hard to balance family and work life, all of which bring her immeasurable joy.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'0909508','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYTcyOTQ0YzktY2E2Zi00NmU4LWJjM2EtZWI5ZDhmZjZkNDE0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1092,'Joanne Clendining',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4364014','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1093,'Tony Scott',NULL,'From Detroit Mi, Tony (Atlanta, The Front Runner, Into the Ashes, Gemini Man) is a Veteran US Army Ranger and Ranger school instructor for the Department of the Army. He served eight years as a non commissioned officer for the US Army. He studied acting in high school and then later in Palo Alto Ca. After ending time served in the military he returned to studying acting in Atlanta Ga with The Company Acting Studio and Drama Inc while attending GSU, earning a BA in Religious Studies, and operating his own ballroom dance studio for 13 years. He still teaches ballroom dancing to senior citizens in Atlanta.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'6922229','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTgyNDA5NDM0Ml5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjgwMjcwNjE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1094,'Christen Orr',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5114585','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1095,'David Dillon',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4955701','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNWFmMmVlZDktZTMwNi00YmFjLWEzNzUtMTg2MzUyYzRjOTU2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1096,'Cristina Figarola','Cristina Rodriguez','Cristina Figarola was born in New York raised by Cuban American parents. She has over 15 years in experience and is SAG AFTRA bilingual actress, spokesperson for various companies, voice-over artist, on air-reporter for Telemundo 51 and writer/ reporter at NBC6. She earned a Bachelors Degree in Finance (minor in Theatre), an MBA, and a MS in Journalism.<br><br>Cristina resides in Miami with her family where she continues the diligent pursuit of her many artistic endeavors. Her latest television and film projects include: Netflix\'s Bloodline, Lifetime\'s Devious Maids, and the film Shadow Fighter. She was also in two Spanish productions in a recurring role in 2016 - Eva La Trailera and Bajo El Mismo Cielo.<br><br>Through her production company, Beaumont Films, she is currently in development of the feature film \"The Mariposas,\" a web series titled \"Cafe Mi Ami,\" and an untitled feature film. She also writes / produces part-time for the live show 6 in the Mix for NBC.<br><br>Be inspired.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'3076103','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNjRkMjBhMmEtNzhhZS00ZDMwLWJmMWQtZTVmZGE1YTk2MTAzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjM2MzU0MDE@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1097,'Kristopher Charles',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6981808','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzIzYTEyOWMtYzQ2NS00ZWY5LTkxMjEtOGZiMDk0NGE3ODRiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR12,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1098,'Jason Edwards',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7490595','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMThkNTMzNTQtNDQxMy00Y2JjLWIzY2EtNGY2YWM2ZGRkMjAxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR15,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1099,'Gara Coffey',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7997055','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTQwZDgzYjMtMDA4ZC00ODEwLWFjOGItZTUxZjQ2MjQ5MzllXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjU4NTUwNjI@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1100,'Monica Mears',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9684777','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjY0MjMzNDQtOGVhZS00ZWMyLWI5MGItZTBlMmUzZmY1NDAzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODYyNDExNDk@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1101,'Kendrick Cross','Kendrick N. Cross',NULL,'1971-05-01 00:00:00',NULL,'Louisville, Kentucky, USA','1366703','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMWUzMzg3OWEtOWU4NS00ZGFmLWEyMTItODhhZDkxZDc0MzYyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR54,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1102,'Ryan Davenport',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8178570','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1103,'Collin Sutton',NULL,'Collin Sutton is a native of the beautiful tropical island of Newfoundland. Born in St. John\'s and raised in Calgary, Collin pursued acting out of high school. After traveling with a theater company around Alberta and appearing in films and commercials, he set his sights on Hollywood. Since being in California, Collin has had much success in pursuing his career. Studying under the talented Coach Clay Banks, he has learned the art of film acting and what it takes to work not only in the ECU but all other areas of film. He has also been fortunate to work under the eyes of Elizabeth Huffman and Kent Skov. Collin has been cast in many films from shorts to features and been on the stage in many a play. Some of his notable performances include Ernest in \"The Importance of Being Earnest,\" Waitwell and Sir Rowland in \"The Way Of The World\", and Juror #8 in \"12 Angry Men,\" where he appeared along side his very talented wife Lola Corwin. Collin has been seen in front of the camera in the features Dracula, Bobby Fischer Live and most recently in No Saints For Sinners, where he starred along side Keith David and rising Irish actor Rick Crawford. He also has made roads into television with the pilots Sentenced For Life, Hollywood Handyman, and being cast this year in the opening sequence for Fox\'s American Horror Story. Collin continues to make headway in the pursuit of his career with hard work, dedication and more importantly the love and support of his wife and two children.<br>\n         ',NULL,NUL