arian Ravager. He recently appeared in Variety and Rolling Stone\'s review of the movie Tag.<br><br>John was given his first speaking role by Oprah Winfrey in her production of The Immortal Life of Henrietta Lacks. He was one of 10 Ravagers from Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2 selected to attend a 2016 Comic-Con surprise celebration in San Diego. The event was filmed and is now airing on CONtv. Further, art featuring John\'s likeness as a Ravager was included in Marvel\'s Guardians of the Galaxy Vol. 2: The Art of the Movie.<br><br>John\'s involvement in the Birmingham cosplay community ignited his interest in acting, and he can frequently be found around town volunteering at charity events as Batman, The Joker, and Green Arrow. He refers to himself as \"Trick Talking Meat\" as coined by the late Carrie Fisher in an interview she did with CNN in 1997. In the interview, she explained that the cast had shirts made with \"Trick Talking Meat\" printed on them, as they felt that is how George Lucas treated them on the set of Empire Strikes Back.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9187687','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZDM5YjZlYTItNGM4OC00NjJhLWI0NDEtYzVkY2Q5MDAzMTM0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1110,'Kathi Binkley',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8797576','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZjA1OWYxYWYtOTEzNy00ZGYzLTk1ZjEtNTIyNjliZDE5MmRiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzMwOTY3MzM@._V1_UY317_CR4,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1111,'Fred Bobbitt',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8060640','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1112,'Braden Bunch',NULL,'Braden Bunch is an American actor who has worked on both stage and screen in addition to performing commercial voice-over work. A former journalist, speechwriter and radio personality, Bunch brings with him an extensive background from various fields to inform his performances. As a child, Bunch lived in several locations throughout the United States, eventually graduating from MacArthur High School in San Antonio, Texas. After graduation, Bunch attended Texas Lutheran College (now University), where he studied theatre and journalism.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9809931','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZDExNDU1MDMtNjk5MC00Y2YyLTkzZWEtN2Y3ZGM1MDZmOTRmXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTQ5NzA0OTM@._V1_UY317_CR12,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1113,'James Burns',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5561059','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1114,'Xander Call',NULL,'Xander Call is a British-American actor and musician, known for Love, Simon (2018). Born in Bangor, Wales, Xander was Meisner trained by Atlanta-Hollywood mentor David A. Cox. He is principal double bass with the Georgia Youth Symphony Orchestra, and plays bari sax with the GYSO Jazz Ensemble. He currently resides in Atlanta.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'8921709','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZjJiMDcwZTItYjI2MC00Yzg4LWFiNzAtM2RmMmJlMzA2ZmFmXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzUwMDE0MDE@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1115,'Lucie Carroll',NULL,'Lucie Carroll is an actress, known for Captain America: Civil War (2016), Novitiate (2016) and Alvin and the Chipmunks: The Road Chip (2015) , is a native of Nashville, TN who lived in Aix-en-Provence, France, in her twenties.<br><br>A graduate of the University of North Carolina in Chapel Hill, NC, Carroll was previously Vice President of a national, publicly-held brand identification company, and was later Development Director for social services charities. She has been a featured extra on the ABC (now CMT) TV series \"Nashville,\" the CMT TV series \"Still the King,\" and several major full-length movies.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'8336192','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMWRiYzAxNmUtMTRjZi00MWJiLWEyNGEtYzlmOTUwMzU0YzY4XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjgyMTIyNDQ@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1116,'Charles Casey',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4120526','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1117,'Tony F. Charles',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9305743','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMWJhMTFhZmYtMWE4MS00YmY1LTkwYjYtMDhkNTEyYzQ2MGU2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR131,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1118,'Chris Codding',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8828726','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1119,'Vinny Costa',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6017509','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1120,'Olivia De Paux',NULL,'Olivia DePaux was born in Fort Campbell, Kentucky, to Lucy and Billy Poteete (DePaux) then moved back to Georgia at 6mo old and grew up in North Atlanta with her parents and little brother. Her mother was of English descent and her fathers family was of Native American and French. After graduating from Berkmar High School, Olivia got an associates degree in engineering and CAD and worked as a CAD engineer while she attended So. Polytech for Chemical Engineering and Kennesaw State for Marketing. While attending Kennesaw State she met and married Scott, who she has been married to for 23 years. They have three children, Jordan, 21, a singer, writer, graphic artist; Lauren 18, a high school senior who will be heading to nursing school; and Brandon, 17, a junior, who is a thespian leader in high school. Starring in many plays as the lead, singing, dancing, playing the piano and composing the music for performances. Olivia started acting in middle school for drama. This continued on to church plays and later commercials and eventually she decided to dive full force into the real true calling she had been denying. She started out in Background acting to get familiar with the industry and how the TV/FIlM set rolls. Quickly learning the ropes and moving on to do stand-in and feature background work, she started getting roles in local film projects. She has been taking 3 acting classes a week for over 2 years to train and learn as much and as fast she can that includes Improv, Meisner, Scene study, Stanislavski, Strasberg, Adler, and more. Realizing after the death of her father that you only live once and life is short, so, you have to do your dreams or you just are a dreamer.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9357043','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNTY0ZGM3YmUtNTZhYy00ZjdkLTk5MTAtNzgyZGYxNTdkYmI2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODU2MjY3MzY@._V1_UY317_CR11,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1121,'Marc Demeter',NULL,'Marc Andrew Demeter is an actor known for his roles in Baywatch (2017), Pitch Perfect 3, The Walking Dead (2017), The Front Runner (2018), the WGN television series Underground, and the IFC channel series Brockmire (2017) as well as many other movies and television shows. Born and raised near Pittsburgh, PA, he currently lives in Jacksonville, FL.<br>\n         ','1972-09-13 00:00:00',NULL,'Uniontown, Pennsylvania, USA','8176720','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZWQ5NTA1ZTItNWVlMS00MzJkLWFlOTgtYmI2N2E2ODk2OGIyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR19,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1122,'Robin Dyke',NULL,'Robin Dyke was raised in the Louisiana & Texas as the All American Girl. After college, she quickly married a Cleveland, OH native. After living there for 10+ years, she now resides in Atlanta, Georgia. Today, you can find Robin managing her family of 6, volunteering with charities, consulting for fortune 500 companies, acting in Feature Films, Television and Stage, and behind the camera collecting content and gathering research for her documentary series.<br>\n         ','1975-11-26 00:00:00',NULL,'Bluefield, West Virginia, USA','7429941','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYjYxOTUxN2YtYmJmZS00ZjFmLTk4YmItOTE5MTE1ZWRkMzU3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjYxMTE2OTY@._V1_UY317_CR6,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1123,'Christine Marie Evans',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9469955','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYTA1ZTc2NTAtNWNjYS00YzVlLTgyNTAtZTE2MGIyY2E1NDRiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODMwMjk3MDU@._V1_UY317_CR43,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1124,'Matthew Ewald',NULL,'As an actor, Matthew Ewald\'s extensive experience and career in the industry began in 2001 when he completed not only his first feature film \"Terminal Error,\" but in the same year was fortunate enough to have portrayed Nicholas Bluetooth on the highly popular FOX science fiction/adventure television series \"Galidor.\" The franchise, an international hit, spawned Matthew his own action figure through the LEGO brand, as well as merchandising rights through Cap\'N\'Crunch cereal, McDonalds Happy Meal Toys, XBOX and Playstation video game consoles, among many others.<br><br>This year alone, Matthew has landed one of the lead roles--as the scarred platoon leader James Edward Sutter--in the upcoming 2017 Vietnam War feature \"Point Man,\" as well as a role in the upcoming fourth and final season of \"TURN: Washington\'s Spies,\" along with the feature film \"White Lilies\" shooting later this year in Italy.<br><br>He has wrapped production on over sixty-plus films, he was a part of the highly acclaimed video game web-series \"Mario Warfare,\" as well as the episode \"Lolani\" for the equally acclaimed \"Star Trek: Continues.\" He has also had the great honor to have filmed the serious-minded remake of the 1959 classic Edward D. Wood, Jr.\'s magnum opus, \"Plan 9 From Outer Space.\" Matthew has also won the prestigious Macabre Faire Film Festival\'s Best Actor in a Feature Film award for his role as Carl in the motion picture \"Athena.\"<br><br>Matthew is a member of the HWA, as well as a published author with numerous horror stories, and four horror novels already to his credit. With an impressive body of work and a slew of upcoming projects in 2017 and well into the next year, Matthew is looking to continue his career in the genres that he so greatly loves.<br>\n         ','1982-10-13 00:00:00',NULL,'Minnesota, USA','0970866','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDYzNzAxYjEtMTM0Ni00NjBhLThiN2UtNWExMzc5NTdjYmEyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzA2NzgzNA@@._V1_UY317_CR28,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1125,'Martin Feigen',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8691672','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1126,'Enya Flack',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0280801','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNzAwMjQ1NjYxOF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwMTkwMzUzOA@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1127,'Gavrielle Anne Fontanilla',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1002058',NULL,0),(1128,'Shawron Gaffney',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7705677','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1129,'Sandy Givelber',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9327131','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYmE4ODdhNjktNWVmOS00NjU5LWI3NzktZDY4ODc2NzA0MTM1XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODEwODcwMTA@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1130,'Jevocas Green',NULL,'Jevocas \'Java\' Green was born on July 18 in Atlanta, Georgia, USA. He is an actor and filmmaker and is no stranger to being in front of the camera, as well as on the stage. Jevocas started his pursuit into acting from elementary school. Being in several plays and musicals on through his High school career. He attended Tri-Cities High School of Visual and Performing arts in East point GA, and went on to attend the Art Institute of Atlanta for film. While in Tri-Cities, he graced the stage in such musicals as \'Pippin\', \'Little Shop of Horrors\', and \'The Wiz,\' to name a few, and continued into stage in his adult acting life with \'La Cage aux Folles,\' \'Big River: The Adventures of Huckleberry Finn,\' \'Cabaret,\' \'Hedwig and the Angry Inch,\' and more. It was around this point he decided to make the jump over to film, after getting the great opportunity to land a speaking role in the independent suspense horror film \'The Remnant.\' And other lead roles in \"ACE: The Zombie,\" \"Three Rookies\" and \"Atlanta Vampire Movie.\" He has also co-produced and produced several independent fanfims and web-series, Such as \"Uncanny X-Men\" and \"Doctor Who: The Forgotten Doctor\".\' Java went on to land other roles and made his way on to television as a Walker on \'The Walking Dead\', and several other television shows. He has since gone on to launch his own independent production company Jymeni Productions, LLC and hopes to continue in his acting and film making endeavors. Java is best known for his long running stint at Dr. Frank N Furter with Atlanta\'s own live cast of the Rocky Horror Picture Show, Lips Down On Dixie, Fridays at Midnight for an amazing 14 of the 16 years the show has been running. LDOD (Lips Down On Dixie) is the longest running theatrical event in Atlanta and Java has definitely made his stamp on Atlanta performing with them. He has also been the headlining Frank N Furter for 13 of the 15 performances of the show for Dragon Con. Java is also a published author, with several erotica fiction stories with Wilde City Press.<br>\n         ','1983-07-18 00:00:00',NULL,'Atlanta, Georgia, USA','2191608','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNjRlYjNhNzQtNjI4ZC00ZDI2LTg3ODctZDRiNzBmN2JlYmVjXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1131,'Apollo GT',NULL,'Apollo GT came from Vietnam as one of the boat people escaping the communist country in 1981. He was the young artist attending the fourth grade in Arlington, VA. Key School was his first school in America. Though he had to learn English as fast as possible to keep up with his classmates, his artistic ability was soon to be noticed by his fourth grade homeroom teacher and his classmates and that propelled him to the front of popularity. He was a shy boy from a large family but his mother had passed away before he was taken by his older siblings out of Vietnam. His father was left behind with 2 of his oldest brothers. Being the youngest, he had to endure the abuse from his 4 remaining sisters and brothers in America without the protection from his parents. Barely a teenager, he started his new life in America not knowing where he will end up. He had only one wish through out his childhood and that was to see his father again. With that wish held dearly to his heart, he must endure all the abuse from his older siblings.<br><br>He put himself through college and in 1994 as he was graduating, his wish came true, his siblings managed to sponsor their dad over to America directly from Vietnam. Apollo GT came back home to live at his oldest sister\'s house since that was where his father was staying. All was good until one year later his father died and his abusive oldest sister acted up again. But now he\'s much older and no longer had a father. He had no reason to put up with her or anyone else. Being a Rooster and a Leo, his personality shines brightly. He retaliated against his siblings from mistreating him and set out to be the man he is today.<br><br>Apollo GT is a photographer, pastel portraiture, magazine publisher, runway coach, poet and actor.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'6872257','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1132,'Alex Hargett',NULL,'Alex Hargett is a film, television, and stage actor from Tupelo, Mississippi. Born Alex is an advanced actor combatant with the Society of American Fight Directors. While most of his work has been on stage, Alex has recently been adding more film and television work, fight choreography, and stunts to his resume.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9248966','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1133,'Thomas Mark Higgins',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4531318','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1134,'Kyle Jackson',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9128025','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1135,'Annie Jamison',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8008669','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1136,'Nicole Jamison',NULL,'Nicole Jamison, born February 21, 1980, is a graduate of The International Academy of Design & Technology, and resides in sunny Florida. She is an artist, and enjoys writing, painting, sewing, theater and making jewelry. Nicole recently published her first novel; \'The Dragonfly Kingdoms: Discovery\' book one and is hard at work finishing book two of the series. Besides being an author, Nicole is discovering other passions with Screenwriting and Producing.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'3886304','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1137,'Bob Jennings',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0421114','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BN2U4ZmZjZDMtN2JiZS00NDA3LTk2NjYtZjliZTBjNTI2NWJjXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTE3MTA4OTI@._V1_UY317_CR12,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1138,'Flanagan John',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9278338','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZWI5YjhiNWMtMDExNS00N2JmLWI2ZTItOGVmNWU5Y2U4ZDUwXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1139,'Shannon Kirk Johnston',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8564133','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1140,'Jay D. Kacho',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7383710','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1141,'John Kaler',NULL,'John Kaler is an American actor known for his appearances in \'The Walking Dead; SEASON 8\'(2018) & \'Stranger Things; SEASON 2 (2017). John was born and raised in Texas, but has worked all over the USA the past several years working in Film & Television. John has also produced several short films / 48 hours with friends. He\'s currently working as \"JEFF CONRAD\" on the indie grind house film \'The Dark Side of Being Kind\', which will hit the film festival circuit next year.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'8309549','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZGNjMTk0ZjItZDc3YS00NWQ4LWI3ZjAtYTQ1NTkxOGNhYTBiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjgwODM0MTQ@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1142,'Donald J. Koko',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4559910','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjMxNjE2NzY1OF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODUxMTIzNTE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1143,'Eric Lahr',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7160955','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1144,'Demetri Landell',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9201765','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1145,'Chuck Laws','Charles Edward Laws',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9528793','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYzg0NTM5MzEtZTYzYS00YmU3LWIzMzYtMWEwYzI5ZWYyNmI1XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzgwMDgyMjc@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1146,'Elgin Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9177465','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1147,'Serene Lee-Sng',NULL,'Serene Lee-Sng was born in Singapore as Serene Mei Lan Lee. She started her career in Advertising from scratch in the late 90s rising from Secretary to Account Executive to Account Director working on blue-chip accounts. In 2006 she was headhunted to China where she took up the role of Senior Group Account Director where she continued to focus on her specialty in Skincare working on Procter & Gamble\'s Regenerist, L\'Oreal and later on to GlaxoSmithKline\'s Sensodyne - all of which are China\'s biggest brand names. After over 20 years in Advertising in Singapore & China, she gave it up to move to Atlanta with her husband of 7 years, whom she met in Shanghai. Missing the fast-paced lifestyle. Serene continued onto being an actor.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9165612','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1148,'Alejandro Lievano',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9714768','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1149,'Roy Luke',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7472654','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1150,'John Archer Lundgren',NULL,'Screen work comprises national distribution and television network movies; a variety of indie features and shorts,including a number of festival favorites; TV episodes(domestic and foreign); and industrials, as well as film school productions. Film/TV production locations have included Ethiopia, New York, Los Angeles, Florida, Georgia, North Carolina and Tennessee.<br><br>Screen productions have ranged from gripping drama to farcical comedy and sentimental tear-jerkers. A wide variety of character roles has included the loony, pathetic and mean; the wicked, heroic and devious; the victimized, authoritative and outrageous; the sage, destitute and debonair. As one casting director put it: \"Jack\'s acting persona is less vanilla, than chocolate with sprinkles.\"<br><br>Several decades of continuous foreign residence in Latin America, France and divers countries throughout Africa facilitated a raft of stage performances in English and Spanish language productions in various countries, including works by Anderson, Anouilh, Axelrod, Chekhov, Gilbert & Sullivan, Lerner & Loewe, Roussin, Shaffer, Wilde, Wilder and Wouk; as well as voice-over recordings for the French Foreign Legion in Djibouti.<br><br>Sporadic visits to the USA included study in the Performing Arts at the Boston University Theater Institute, as well as a number of stage performances in Florida and Georgia, including works by Albee, Friel, Lerner & Loewe, and Miller. For more than ten years, in various countries and states, in a wide variety of venues, Jack staged his one-man show based on the works of Edgar Allan Poe; his current stand-up repertoire resurrects an old-timey vaudeville routine featuring a variety of short silly patter songs.<br><br>In recent years, Jack has performed regularly in theaters throughout North/Central Florida, interpreting, among others: works by Chekhov, Shakespeare, Simon, Woldin, Sondheim, Letts and Gelbart; musical shows for school children; and non-singing performances with the Orlando Opera Company.<br><br>Jack played Rabbi Furtado in the South-Eastern USA premiere of \"The King of Schnorrers\" by Judd Woldin, winner of a Tony Award in 1974 for his score for the musical \"Raisin\". Jack has interpreted the Magistrate in two separate productions of Neil Simon\'s \"Fools\", as well as rocking the equally bizarre Congressman Salt in Michel Parker\'s \"The Sensuous Senator\",which was the comedy hit of Jacksonville, Florida\'s 2003-2004 theater season; then came the scandalous Marcus Lycus in \"A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to the Forum\". These outrageous characters were followed by Bud Todd, the lascivious lonely-wife chaser in Tracy Letts\' \"Man From Nebraska\"; as well as the outrageously rickety miser, Jethro Crouch, in \"Sly Fox\" by Larry Gelbart, the creator of \"M*A*S*H\".<br><br>Other favorite stage roles from yesteryear have included Captain Queeg in \"The Caine Mutiny Court-Martial\", Milo Tindle in \"Sleuth\", Lady Bracknell in \"The Importance of Being Earnest\", the psychopathic Jerry in Albee\'s \"Zoo Story\", and Father Jack in \"Dancing at Lughnasa\".<br><br>Education includes undergraduate study in Missouri, Colorado and Mexico; graduate study at the Ecuadorian Institute of International Law in Quito; and a Doctorate in Letters from the University of Lille in France, as well as the previously mentioned study in the Performing Arts at the Boston University Theater Institute.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1739959','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjE2MTYwMjI1NF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwOTQ1MjE0OTE@._V1_UY317_CR23,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1151,'Gabriel Manak',NULL,'Gabriel Manak was born in Richmond Hill, Queens, New York, USA. At age 11, his family moved to Plainsboro, New Jersey. Throughout his life, Gabriel has always been involved with the arts including concert choirs, school plays, college film program projects and independent film. As a self-taught musician who has blood relation to Russian composer, Sergei Rachmaninoff, he has professionally recorded two albums including a Rock Christmas album where he puts his own spin on many traditional carols. He is known for his work on Halt and Catch Fire (2015-2016), Marvel\'s \'The Gifted\', Mr. Mercedes (2017) and The Front Runner (2018).<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'6663377','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BODgyNzQyMDMtNGFhNC00ZjdkLWJkZDItOGYzM2NhYWU3MGVlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTQ1NDMwNjM@._V1_UY317_CR13,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1152,'Tweed Michael Manning',NULL,'Actor and Model Tweed Michael Manning is the middle son of Michael and Nannette. When Manning was a teenager he was spotted by a talent agent and embarked on his modeling career. His first print job was for GAP. Alongside modeling Manning began acting appearing in many various roles in different TV series, commercials and movie projects.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'6267863','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1153,'Trey McGriff',NULL,'Trey McGriff is an actor, composer, and filmmaker, based out of Atlanta, Georgia. Trey enjoys and respects all aspects of movie-making, and began participating in school plays and music at a young age, while growing up in Mississippi. Trey makes appearances in THE WALKING DEAD, STRANGER THINGS, BABY DRIVER, COBRA KAI, RING OF FIRE, SAME KIND OF DIFFERENT AS ME, FRANKENSTEIN CREATED BIKERS, YOUR PRETTY FACE IS GOING TO HELL, and many other shows and films. Trey wrote the theme songs for Steve Niles\' REMAINS and ALIEN OPPONENT.<br><br>McGriff has gained over twenty years of stage time performing his original music and was honored to perform at House of Blues, Jagermeister Music Tour, Coca-Cola Roxy Theater, Centennial Olympic Park, Walnut Creek Amphitheater, The Ritz, and many venues throughout Georgia. Trey\'s songs have aired on NBC, Showtime, World of Playboy TV, MTV, Comcast TV, NPR, and Red Bull Films.<br><br>Trey McGriff stars in, wrote and directed the films: GIFT THAT KEPT GIVING, KURIOSITY KILLZ, SPOOKY SNOW DAY, and SOMETHING IN MY ATTIC. Trey will direct, compose, and act in SHOVELHEAD THE MOVIE, a unique Horror/Thriller feature film, starring horror icon, Michael Berryman.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1380890','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BODQxOTQxNjU0MF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDY1MTIyMDI@._V1_UY317_CR12,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1154,'Timothy D. Montjoy','Timothy Montjoy','Tim Montjoy is a retiree of the United States Air Force and resides in Augusta, Georgia. His Air Force career spanned from 1996 - 2016, and took him to such overseas assignments as Osan Air Base, South Korea to Incirlik Air Base, Turkey and Zabul, Afghanistan. Tim managed Tier-1 technical support by monitoring and reporting services related to Command, Control, Communications, Computers, and Intelligence (C4I) for a 600 million dollar infrastructure and 2.4 billion dollars in Air Combat Command assets. These services included systems used by the 31 thousand Active Duty and Retiree population throughout the Carolina region.<br><br>Additionally, he excelled while performing with Base Honor Guard teams and was also selected to assist the U. S. Military All-Stars Baseball Team during the summer of 2009, a wonderful experience for a lifelong baseball fan.<br><br>Tim has completed his Community College of the Air Force degree in Information Systems and has received his CompTia A+ certification. He is a graduate of the Air Force\'s Airman Leadership School and the Non-Commissioned Officer\'s Academy.<br><br>Tim\'s military decorations include the Air Force Commendation Medal, Army Commendation Medal, Air Force Achievement Medal, Military Outstanding Volunteer Service Medal, Air Force Good Conduct Medal, the National Defense Service Medal, Armed Forces Global War on Terrorism Service Medal, the Korean Defense Service Medal, the NATO Medal and the Army Combat Action Badge.<br><br>Tim is a member of the Air Force Association, the Air Force Sergeants Association and the Armed Forces Communications & Electronics Association.<br><br>Furthermore, he is the recipient of the 2006 Communications and Information Non-Commissioned Officer of the Year award, the 2012 Air Force Sergeants Association\'s, Chapter 377, Volunteer of the Year award and was selected as the 2015 Air Force Sergeants Association\'s, Chapter 377, Non-Commissioned Officer of the Year.<br><br>Both Tim and his daughter have a passion for volunteering with various organizations throughout the military and local communities. This dedication directly supports the betterment of our military and civilian communities across our great nation.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'8937530','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545868802),(1155,'Andy Morales',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9938146','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOGVkZWIxNGYtZDU5My00ZTU5LTgzNGQtODI4NTNjMDU3OGY3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR28,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1156,'Connor Murdock',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9009414','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTk5Zjc1YTctMTY2OC00N2I4LTg3OTYtMGY1ZWVlMGQyNzcxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDY1NTI5NTU@._V1_UY317_CR52,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1157,'Donald K. Overstreet',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7506601','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDdhNTczZjAtNGQyOC00MGIyLWEzMzAtZWM0Y2E1MjQzNWNjXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTM3Nzg0MTQ@._V1_UY317_CR12,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1158,'Alejandro Pagan',NULL,'Alejandro was born in Salisbury, MD. He first started his love for acting when he was a freshman in high school (2012). He got to perform on stage in his first performance as Patrolman Harrington in Lizzie Borden of Fall River (2012). That\'s when he grew a love and appreciation for theater. It wasn\'t until his sophomore year of high school that he realized his main goal which was to be an actor for film and television. For his television debut he was given the opportunity to be a weatherman for a day (2013). The rush he felt from improvising what to say during his broadcast on WMDT only made him love performing even more and he ended up getting the chance to do that two more times after. When he was a senior in high school he was interviewed because he was starring in his school\'s performance of The Lion, the Witch, and the Wardrobe in which he was portraying Aslan the lion (2016). He was also performing in the Community Players of Salisbury\'s rendition of Mary Poppins as the Park Keeper (2016). He is pursuing a B.F.A. in Performing Arts at Savannah College of Art and Design (2018).<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9025355','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BN2YwZWZmZTItMzRhYi00OTk0LThjNWEtNjc3YTU3YmI4NTE0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjkxMjQxNTQ@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1159,'Carl Palmer',NULL,'Carl Palmer is a seasoned actor. He is not a lawyer. He was a History and Political Science major in his last semester at Louisiana State University, very intent on going to Law School. Then he got the last slot available for an Acting class and the acting bug bit. So long, law school. Hello, decades as a working actor.<br><br>After graduating Magna Cum Laude from LSU, Carl then went on to get a Masters of Fine Arts degree from Cal Arts. Having lived in New York for many years, he\'s also spent some time in L.A., but now resides primarily in New Orleans. In addition to a slew of Film and TV roles, Carl is a veteran of over 50 Off-Broadway and major regional theatre productions.<br><br>Carl\'s autobiographical one-man show, A Loss For Words, centers around his search for his birth-parents. It tells his story of growing up adopted in a small factory town outside of New Orleans, intertwined with the tale of his birth-parents\' romance as told through the actual letters they wrote to each other before, during and after the pregnancy. However, the play is actually about what happened after the search...<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'0658152','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDIwNTM3NDgtZjViNC00MmZkLWIzZWYtY2FkNmUyMjQxY2ExXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTUxMDU2MTM@._V1_UY317_CR104,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1160,'Mason Pike','Mason B. Pike','Mad Man Mason (Mason Pike) is an American Professional wrestling referee and actor. Born on December 27, 1995 in LaGrange, Ga, Pike attended a magnet school for the Fine Arts until high school (3rd-8th grade). For those five years, he was an active part of the Drama department, under the direction of Carol Cain. Pike has worked for Pro-Wrestling companies such as Hulk Hogan\'s Micro Championship Wrestling, Great Championship Wrestling (GCW), Global Championship Wrestling (GCW), World Wrestling Entertainment (WWE), Total Nonstop Action (TNA), Peachstate Wrestling Alliance (PWA), and more.<br><br>Pike started in the Professional Wrestling business in 2008, being trained by Chick Donavon. During high school, Pike was offered many \"extra\" roles in feature films and TV shows. He received his Bachelors in Political Science and Pre-Law from Georgia State University in Atlanta, GA in 2017. While in Atlanta, Pike worked as an extra, stand-in, and photo double in TV shows and movies to gain experience on set lacked in drama/theatre courses. Pike has appeared in two commercials: one for Zaxbys and another for ESPN. He has worked alongside with such stars as: Jack Black, Ike Barinholtz, Leslie Mann, <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm1374980?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Zac Efron</a>, Shaquille O\'Neal, John Cena, Robert Downey Jr., Vince Vaughn, Kevin Spacey, Dwayne \"The Rock\" Johnson, Steve Harvey, Jamie Foxx, Ice Cube, Charlie Day, Tracy Morgan, Steve Martin, Ed Helms, Jeremy Renner, Vin Diesel, Kristen Stewart, Chris Tucker, Owen Wilson, Katt Williams, Kerri Washington, Zach Galifianakis, and many more! Pike has also worked CLOSELY with directors Greg Nicotero, Tyler Perry, Jason Bateman, Ang Lee, and Brett Morgen. With many years of acting experience, Pike has appeared in many TV and movie roles, although hasn\'t been offered a principle role yet. Pike claims that after he finishes school he would like to pursue his interest in the professional wrestling business or law, rather than acting.<br>\n         ','1995-12-27 00:00:00',NULL,'LaGrange, Georgia, USA','4918316','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNjE2NjY0YjMtNDU4MS00OThmLWI5NjMtMTYwNTQyYjQ2MTg0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjA2MjQ4Nzc@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1161,'Grace Pippas',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8614604','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTI5N2I3NWQtNjA5OC00NDgxLWJmOTYtNTZmZjczZjAxNzBiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjk5NzAwMjM@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1162,'Jonathan Ragan',NULL,'Jonathan Ragan is an American actor living and working in the Atlanta, Georgia area. He is easily recognizable by his distinct bright red hair and blue eyes. Jonathan began acting in elementary school and continued through junior high and high school but studied to be in the ministry while in university. He moved to Georgia its his family in 2017 to pursue acting professionally.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5765145','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1163,'Henardo Rodriguez',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8713842','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZjBmYTE1ODItNDAzYy00ZTc0LWE2YTEtNDY1YzI1MjI2YTQ1L2ltYWdlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzEzNjkyNjA@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1164,'Josh Royston',NULL,'American actor/model Josh Royston began as a fashion model doing runway, print, magazines and various advertisements. His first cover was for a gun magazine called \"World of Firepower\". Since that time, he has gone on to grace other magazine covers, advertisements and commercials, as well as semi-recurring background roles on shows such as The Resident, Dynasty, Star and others. He has also had minor roles in films like First Man, The Frontrunner, American Animals and Pitch Perfect III.<br><br>He was born Joshua William Royston on October 22, 1976, in Greenwood, SC. He is the son of Leesa (Inabinet), a judge, and Tim Royston, a retired business owner. Josh was the oldest of three children. His ancestry is French Huguenot. He resides in Greenville, SC.<br><br>Josh has one daughter, Ava Grace Royston who is 8.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'8355178','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZmQ0Y2VkZjgtZWNjOC00MWJjLWE2YzktNDA3ZTI2M2IzZDY0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzEwNDU2MzE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1165,'Melinda Russell',NULL,'Born and raised in Atlanta, Ga, Melinda started entertaining family and friends with creative talents at an early age. Modeling, acting, singing and writing along with multimedia works of art was her passion. While studying for her MBA at KSU, her love of music and business landed her a position with an Atlanta record label where she knew art in all forms is where she belongs.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1382940','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOGUwMjFjNDUtYTBhOC00NWRiLTgyMzItYjU5ZTI3YWQ1ZjBkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzQ0MzgwMzg@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1166,'Milton Saul',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7900960','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNWNmMTk4YjgtZDVkMS00N2QwLWI2MmEtOTI5YTEyNzMxYzBkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjUyNjYxNjQ@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1167,'Patti Schellhaas',NULL,'Born in Minneapolis, MN, Patti was the eldest of 4 children. Her Father was a Draftsman and her Mother a Registered Nurse. The family moved to St. Petersburg, Florida, when she was just 6 years old and starting 1st grade. Patti continued Middle school at Azalea, and was a Majorette. In 9th grade, she attended Boca Ciega High School, was in Band, and nominated to be on the Homecoming Court. For grades10-12, Patti transferred to Northside Christian High School and was again nominated to be on the Homecoming Court. She was in Chorus, played the Oboe in Symphonic Band, and the Bells (as well as the Xylophone) in Marching Band. In her Senior Year, she was chosen to be on the National Honor Society, and was voted \"Business Student of the Year\". After receiving her Associate of Arts degree in Miami, FL, Patti became a professional Cosmetologist, managed 2 Hair Salons, and at one time was a makeup artist on location for Good Morning America. She and her siblings now own and manage the family business, Cottages by the Sea, St. Croix, in the US Virgin Islands. Married for 22 years, Patti and Mark raised 2 boys, and home-schooled them from 5th grade through to Graduation. They now reside in the Northwest Atlanta, Georgia area. Mark owns his own car building business called, Little River Hot Rods.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'6768665','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1168,'Donna Sexton',NULL,NULL,'1966-07-12 00:00:00',NULL,'United States','7280952','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjY1NDU1MGYtYjNiYS00NjMzLTk1Y2YtY2JjMDg2YTYzOGI4XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTk5Mzg2MzE@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1169,'Karl Siefken',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9488942','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1170,'Mickey Skizz',NULL,'Mickey Skizz is an American singer/songwriter and actor, born in Milwaukee, WI. He grew up in Plover, WI where he attended Stevens Point Area Senior High (SPASH), and was a freestyle state wrestling champion. He then attended college at the University of Wisconsin-Green Bay where, while pursuing a biology degree, he began his music career by performing in clubs around the state and soon, throughout the country. After finishing college, he enlisted in the army where after completing airborne school, he was selected for the elite Army Rangers, and then 20th Special Forces Group where he would eventually retire from the military. In 2002, he released his first single \"Holding Out For You\" and in 2006 was named by 11th Hour magazine as their Male Vocalist of the year. In 2012 he was diagnosed with End Stage Kidney Disease (forcing his retirement from the military), and would receive a transplant with a kidney donated by his sister in 2016. After a long and difficult recovery, he expanded his performing career into acting. In 2017, he appeared in the feature films \"15:17 To Paris\" and \"The Front Runner\", as well as the TV series \"Valor\", \"Snapped\", and \"Murder Comes to Town\". Mickey is a strong advocate for veterans\' issues and organ donation. He is also the nephew of Alaska\'s Hobo Jim, the official state Balladeer of the state of Alaska.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9365968','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BN2M0YjYwOTEtNzRiNi00N2ZjLWI3YzYtOWVhYjE1ZjViMWNkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODE5MTMwNDY@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1171,'Ellen Soderberg',NULL,'Born in Normal, IL and raised in East Helena, MT, Ellen studied theater at the University of Wyoming and Rhode Island College. Her professional career started in Boston, MA with numerous commercial, film and theater roles. Before leaving Boston, she appeared opposite Melvin Rodriguez in the dark comedy feature FAT, and relocated to Los Angeles in 2013.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'4408254','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNzk0OWEwYjAtN2Q0Mi00MDQyLTkyZmYtMTFlNDUzZTczYjM3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjU3MDU5MDM@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1172,'Devan Stewart',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9369216','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1173,'Michael Wayne Thomas',NULL,NULL,'1975-07-04 00:00:00',NULL,'Charleston, South Carolina, USA','2529627','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTUxMjY5MzgyM15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTkyNjQ4NDE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1174,'Joey Thurmond',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5731672','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BN2ZjZmJkMzctZjJlYy00NDAyLThiM2QtNmM2ZTM3NTFjMmYyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTQxMjU5NDc@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1175,'William Walker',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3507620','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1176,'Buddy Watkins',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9681551','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTUxNmYxOGYtZjUxNy00ZWUzLWIwODItOGZhMjM1ZTEwYmZiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODYxODEwODY@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1177,'Greg Wave',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9032834','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1178,'Benjamin Weaver',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5234677','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1179,'Amanda Marie Wilkinson',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9150896','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzZiMWQyNjItYTU2OS00ZjVkLWJhMDctZjI2NzdhODNiMWE1XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR11,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1180,'Jacqueline Marie Zwick',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4384848','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BY2FmMmI3MjItNzA0Zi00MDY5LTg0NWEtMDY0Zjc3MDcwZDdhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjUyNTE0NTQ@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1181,'Narcissister',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9172283','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1182,'Taryn Gould',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1975804','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BY2ZmNGFjNWMtNzE0Zi00MjMyLWE3MDItOTNjNjg5N2U2YWNiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTQxNzc5NTU@._V1_UY317_CR12,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545870601),(1183,'Luis Ortega','Luis Ortega Salazar',NULL,'1980-07-12 00:00:00',NULL,'Buenos Aires, Argentina','1166781','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzM3MzMzNDY0OV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNTg1NTk0NTM@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545870601),(1184,'Sergio Olguín',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9008596','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1185,'Rodolfo Palacios',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9171645','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1186,'Agustín Almodóvar','Agustín Almodóvar Caballero',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0021948','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNWJiN2VmNjgtODMwYS00MzI1LTg3OGUtZDBmZWRkNmJkYzI3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjUyNDk2ODc@._V1_UY317_CR150,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545870601),(1187,'Pedro Almodóvar','Pedro Almodóvar Caballero','The most internationally acclaimed Spanish filmmaker since <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0000320?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Luis Buñuel</a> was born in a small town (Calzada de Calatrava) in the impoverished Spanish region of La Mancha. He arrived in Madrid in 1968, and survived by selling used items in the flea-market called El Rastro. Almodóvar couldn\'t study filmmaking because he didn\'t have the money to afford it. Besides, the filmmaking schools were closed in early 70s by Franco\'s government. Instead, he found a job in the Spanish phone company and saved his salary to buy a Super 8 camera. From 1972 to 1978, he devoted himself to make short films with the help of of his friends. The \"premieres\" of those early films were famous in the rapidly growing world of the Spanish counter-culture. In few years, Almodóvar became a star of \"La Movida\", the pop cultural movement of late 70s Madrid. His first feature film, <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0081323?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Pepi, Luci, Bom and Other Girls Like Mom</a> (1980), was made in 16 mm and blown-up to 35 mm for public release. In 1987, he and his brother <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0021948?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Agustín Almodóvar</a> established their own production company: El Deseo, S. A. The \"Almodóvar phenomenon\" has reached all over the world, making his films very popular in many countries.<br>\n         ','1949-09-25 00:00:00',NULL,'Calzada de Calatrava, Ciudad Real, Castilla-La Mancha, Spain','0000264','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNTE0NTk3NTMxOV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTYwMzMxMjkz._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545870601),(1188,'Javier Braier',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1962181','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1189,'Micaela Buye',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0125547','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1190,'Leticia Cristi',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1345917','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1191,'Pablo Culell',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0191373','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1192,'Esther García',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Cedillo de la Torre, Segovia, Castilla y León, Spain','0306088','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1193,'Axel Kuschevatzky','Axel Vladimir Kuschevatzky','Axel Kuschevatzky is a movie producer, with an extensive background in film journalism, TV production and scriptwriting.<br><br>He was associate producer of Juan José Campanella\'s acclaimed feature \"The Secret in Their Eyes\" (El Secreto de sus ojos, 2009), Oscar-winner picture in the of Best Foreign language category in 2010. \"The Secret in Their Eyes\" sold more than 2.500.000 tickets in Argentina (breaking a 35 year old record) and 1.000.000 admissions in Spain. It also won two Goya awards; Best Latin-American Picture and Best Newcomer actress (Soledad Villamil), with seven other nominations including Best Picture and Best Director. Among other previous awards were nine Clarín(including Best Picture), thirteen Sur awards from the Argentinean\'s Academy of Motion Pictures, five awards at La Habana Film Festival (including the Audience Award), and a nomination an Ariel as Best Spanish-Speaking feature from Academia Mexicana de Artes y Ciencias Cinematográficas. The film was released in the US by Sony Pictures and it was sold to more than 15 countries including UK, Germany, Taiwan, Brazil, Mexico, France and Italy.<br><br>He was also associate producer of \"The Widows of Thursdays\" (Las Viudas de Los Jueves, 2009), Marcelo Piñeyro\'s thriller based on the best seller written by Claudia Piñeiro and starring Pablo Echarri, Leonardo Sbaraglia and Ernesto Alterio; and also produced the animated movie \"Plumíferos - Aventuras Voladores\" (2010), the first feature made with open source software featuring the voices of Luisana Lopilato and Mariano Martínez.<br><br>In March 2009 he became head of film production at Telefé, Argentina\'s biggest TV network.<br><br>Since 2004 Axel has been the co-host of CNN/TNT\'s Latin-American Oscar preshow along Ana Maria Montero. CNN/TNT\'s Latin-American Oscar preshow is seen by more than 120 million people in the region, from Puerto Rico to Tierra del Fuego.<br><br>Axel Kuschevatzky was born in the Almagro neighborhood in Buenos Aires in October 1972. His mother is a child psychologist and his father a pediatrician and piano player.<br><br>He studied copywriting and did appear as a teenager on TV answering about Horror Movies in a Quiz Show.<br><br>After that he was the host of a weekly movie series, Cine Bizarro in the local cable network CV 5, and was part of the prestigious interview show \"Los Hacedores\", focused on performing and visual arts.<br><br>Axel defines himself as a movie reporter and not as a film critic, more of a movie buff.<br><br>He also hosted movie shows in Argentina like \"Alucine\" (América TV), \"Cinescape\" (CVN), \"Apasionados: El especial\" (2002), \"Telefé Cortos\", and presented weekly series \"Terrormania\" (Telefé), and \"Nosotros También Nos Equivocamos\" (Telefé), two Oscar specials for Canal 9, and movie features in \"América Noticias\", \"Telefé Noticias\", \"Zoo\" (América TV), and \"Maru a la Tarde\" (Telefé), besides doing interviews and TV specials.<br><br>He also interviewed filmmakers like Martin Scorsese, Woody Allen, Clint Eastwood, James Cameron, George Lucas, Sam Raimi, M. Night Shyamalan, John Woo, John Lasseter; actors Nicolas Cage, Christian Slater, Anthony Hopkins, Cate Blanchett, Joaquin Phoenix, Willem Dafoe, Kurt Russell, Ewan McGregor, Will Smith, Viggo Mortensen, Chris O\'Donell, Adam West, Martin Landau, Robin Williams, Danny de Vito, Edward Norton, Dustin Hoffman, Samuel Jackson, Liam Neeson, Hugh Jackman, Tom Hanks, Daniel Radcliffe, Ruppert Gint, Richard Harris, Sharon Stone, Hugh Grant, Sandra Bullock, Mark Wahlberg, Guy Pierce, Brad Pitt, George Clooney, Cameron Diaz, Drew Barrymore, Keanu Reeves, Sean Connery, Catherine Zeta-Jones and Matt Damon, among many others.<br><br>He co-adapted the scripts for \"La Niñera\", based on the US hit show \"The Nanny\". It was the first sit-com made in Latin-America, co-produced by Sony y Telefé Contenidos, winner of the Clarín award as best TV comedy in 2004. For the same companies - Sony y Telefé Contenidos - he co-adapted \"Married with Children\" into the hugely successful \"Casados Con Hijos\", winner of the Martin Fierro award as best comedy in 2005 and also nominated for the Clarín Award. Both sitcoms were broadcasted in Venezuela, Spain, Perú and Puerto Rico.<br><br>He was Telefé\'s head producer for \"Fear Factor\" (Factor Miedo).<br><br>He also acted in small roles in shorts and features like \"Ceibo y Taba\" (2002), \"Plan\" (2000), \"Graciadió\" (1997) y \"No seas cruel\" (1996, both directed by Raúl Perrone), \"Who Is Alejandro Chomski?\" (2002, along Emir Kusturica, Julie Delpy and Jim Jarmush) and in the telefilm \"Manos libres - El caso del bebé de los Perales\" (2005, directed by Carlos Sorín).<br><br>He played the voice of the character \"Jay Limo\" in the Argentinean Spanish dubbing of \"Cars\" (2006).<br><br>Was interviewed for the documentary \"Biography - Adam West: Behind the Cowl\" (2000) for US cable network A&E.<br><br>Since 1995 have been editor and publisher of the movie magazine \"La Cosa\", the longest running of its kind in Spanish.<br><br>He also wrote for newspapers like \"Clarín\", \"La Nación\" and \"El Cronista Comercial\", and magazines like \"Playboy\", \"Miradas\", \"Veintitrés\", \"RSVP\", \"Madhouse\", and \"El Lápiz Japonés\" among others.<br><br>His radio work includes \"El León de la Metro\", along Bebé Sanzo and Ronnie Arias, \"La Cornisa\" with Luis Majul, and \"Cambio de Aire\", with Román Lejtman.<br><br>He also did research for the books \"Un Diccionario de Cine Argentino\" and \"Un Diccionario de Cine Argentino, Volumen 2\", written by Raúl Manrupe and María Alejandra Portela.<br><br>Axel won the journalism award TEA Estimulo, has been jury for the Clarín Cine awards, film and creative consultant for Telefé since 2000 and jury of the 3º Festival Nacional De Cine Con Vecinos in Saladillo.<br><br>Axel Kuschevatzky lives in Buenos Aires with his wife, son and daughter.<br>\n         ','1972-10-28 00:00:00',NULL,'Buenos Aires, Argentina','1098024','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDEyODA5MzkxN15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwMTk2MjA0OQ@@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545870601),(1194,'Matías Mosteirín',NULL,NULL,'1974-08-17 00:00:00',NULL,'Argentina','0609212','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1195,'Sebastían Ortega',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9184106','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTU1MDQ3ODI0MV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwOTk1NTk0NTM@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545870601),(1196,'Valeria Perez Delgado',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0673427','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1197,'Hugo Sigman',NULL,'Hugo Sigman is a producer, known for \"Relatos Salvajes\" de Damián Szifron (2014), \"Septimo\" de Patxi Amezcua (2013), \"Habi, la extranjera\" de Maria Florencia Alvarez (2013), \"Dias de pesca en la patagonia\" de Carlos Sorin (2013), \"El ultimo Elvis\" de Armando Bo (2012), \"Los Marziano\" de Ana Katz (2010), \"El pasado\" de Hector Babenco (2007), and others.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1962406','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BY2VlNDYyNGQtMWMyOS00YTZiLTg0NjUtMjg4N2U0NDA4Yzg2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDUzOTQ5MjY@._V1_UY317_CR163,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545870601),(1198,'Lorenzo Ferro',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9171644','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545870601),(1199,'Chino Darín','Ricardo Mario Darín Bas',NULL,'1989-01-14 00:00:00',NULL,'San Nicolás de los Arroyos, Buenos Aires, Argentina','3779182','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDc0MTU1MzYyM15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDk4NjE1NjE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1200,'Daniel Fanego