45843479),(1216,'Branden Cobb',NULL,'Branden has been successful with providing enjoyment to millions of people through contributing to feature films, short films, broadcasts, commercials, documentaries, music, events, and digital media. He has publicly stated a goal to provide enjoyment to billions of people.<br><br>Branden is able to employ business instincts and has the ingenuity to stay abreast of emerging trends and distribution technology, allowing delivery of fresh insight and solutions to overcome challenges and generate new opportunities. He is self-motivated with a passion for filmmaking and equipped with a masterful understanding of communications and marketing. His experience in managing multiple projects from concept through development to execution and delivery, enables him to be accountable for the material and make smart decisions based on the content.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7209295','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545872401),(1217,'Luke Daniels',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1149599','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZWMzNzAwMzktYTRiMS00NTVlLTkyYjAtMWQ5MDIxNzkyMmEyXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTYwNTQ4ODk@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545872401),(1218,'DJ Dodd','Daniel Dodd','D.J. Dodd is originally from Oxford, PA. He attended Drexel University in Philadelphia, PA, earning a degree in Business Administration with minors in both Law and Film and then Chapman University in Orange, CA, earning a MFA in Film and Television Producing.<br><br>D.J. has previously worked as a Development Executive for producer David Foster (The Mask of Zorro, The River Wild, The Thing, Short Circuit). He has also created, developed, and/or produced content for many major networks including Discovery Channel, TLC, Animal Planet, Investigation Discovery, Oxygen, Lifetime Movie Network, Food Network, Cooking Channel, Travel Channel, HGTV, and History Channel, among others. Among that content are several hugely-successful series including Breaking Amish on TLC and Amish Mafia on Discovery Channel. D.J. has also created and optioned over a dozen non-scripted television concepts to a variety of production companies.<br><br>D.J. has also ventured into the feature film development, packaging, and financing arena, having co-executive produced the critically acclaimed 2015 Sundance Film Ten Thousand Saints directed by Oscar nominees Robert Pulcini and Shari Springer Berman and starring Ethan Hawke and Emile Hirsch, as well as Wild Oats directed by Andy Tennant starring Jessica Lange and Demi Moore, among several others.<br><br>He has also executive produced several films including the eOne release Three Holes and a Smoking Gun, political documentary Imminent Threat, Smartass starring Joey King, Mothers and Daughters starring Courteney Cox, Christina Ricci, Sharon Stone, Mira Sorvino, and Selma Blair, and Warning Shot starring Tammy Blanchard, Frank Whaley, David Spade, Bruce Dern, and James Earl Jones.<br><br>DJ produced the Sony release Supercon starring John Malkovich, Mike Epps, Maggic Grace, Russell Peters, and Ryan Kwanten. He also has the upcoming River Runs Red, which he executive produced, starring Taye Diggs, John Cusack, George Lopez, and Luke Hemsworth.<br><br>D.J.\'s company, Future Proof Films, specializes in feature film and television development and production, as well as literary management. D.J. serves as President and has facilitated many deals for his clients including options, writing assignments, distribution, sales, and financing with many top production companies.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'4367815','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNTQzOTYwMjQyNV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMTYyMzEzODE@._V1_UY317_CR5,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545872401),(1219,'Charles Dorfman',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4074500','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545872401),(1220,'Jaqueline Fleming',NULL,'Jaqueline Fleming aka \"JAQ,\" was born in Copenhagen, Denmark to an African American father and a Danish-German mother. She was raised between New York, St. Louis, and Chicago. After high school, she went on to graduate from Columbia Film School in Chicago where she was a Theatre & Dance Major. After working many years as a Film/TV/Commercial Actress in Los Angeles she felt something was missing from her journey as an actor. She was considering moving back to Chicago in 2008 to pursue her first love Theatre but instead wound up going to New Orleans to work on a film. She always loved New Orleans and decided to stay. Post Katrina she felt a need to stick around and help rebuild the city. She began volunteering at the hospitals that were short staffed and someone saw one of her TV shows in rerun and asked did she teach acting. That led to her opening an Acting Studio. It all clicked and what had been missing on her own journey as an actor was being a mentor and helping others pursue their dreams of becoming an actor. Jaqueline knew there was a calling & purpose on her life and the journey was just beginning. Fast forward, Jaqueline continues to pursue her passion for acting and has become a mentor to kids, teens and young adults in Louisiana, where she has a home. Jaqueline is the founder of Jaq\'s Acting Studio, where she has been instrumental since 2008 in helping aspiring actors become working actors. She has had many success stories come out of her Acting Studio including Jason Mitchell who went on to Star as EazyE in \"Straight Outta Compton.\" She received a TrailBlazer award for her Mentorship work in New Orleans in 2014.<br>\n         ','1977-09-10 00:00:00',NULL,'Copenhagen, Denmark','0281693','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNGZhYWY4MjUtYmJiMC00MGEzLWJhMTMtYTc5ZjFlMGE0YTgwXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTk3ODQzMzE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1221,'BK Fulton',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9089888','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZDEwMDA4YjgtY2NjMy00M