3479),(1388,'Christopher Birks',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6891912','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjZjZWI3ZGYtMTgzZS00NGRjLThiMDUtYmMxNmJlODNhMDNmXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODEyMTY5NTE@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1389,'Simon Wan',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4854335','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545876001),(1390,'Ishola Akanni',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9157102','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNTExMjU5NjYtYzI2Zi00MzcyLWIzODMtYTUzMDM2NTgwM2EzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzkxOTI4MDg@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1391,'Deepak Anand',NULL,'Deepak Anand had a passion for films since his early days while at University in Mumbai, India - home to the Indian Film Industry - now known as \"Bollywood\", which had an influence on him. He now lives in London. After completion of Degrees in Economics and Law, he entered the Aviation Industry and after serving for 35 years, retired holding Senior Management positions in Marketing & Advertising. Post retirement, he re-kindled his passion for the creative field of Acting and soon entered the world of modelling and acting. He has, since had, a reasonable amount of experience both in Modelling and Acting in short and Feature films, Commercials / Music Videos in featured/speaking roles and enjoys facing the camera. Although now 63, he has a playing age around 50-55. Besides being an Ethnic Indian, due to his olive skin colour and a large walrus moustache, he has uncharacteristic looks which could suit South Asian, Middle Eastern, Mediterranean or South American character roles. In order to develop himself and enhance his skills, he has successfully completed an acting course and has been awarded a Diploma in \"Acting for the Camera\" by the London Academy for Media Film TV, UK in December 2015.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7605938','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjExNzFjYjYtZjliYy00ZTZiLTk5ZmUtMDg3YjAwN2NhN2ZiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjAzMzQ2MjE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1392,'David Barton',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9847481','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545876001),(1393,'Muireann Bird',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2537159','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545876001),(1394,'Andrew Blackall',NULL,'Andrew Blackall was born in St John\'s Wood, London; just around the corner from the Abbey Road Studios. He\'s a freelance producer, working in documentary, film and television. Educated in Harrow, he trained as an actor, working in everything from fringe to film, television and advertising; employed on projects as diverse as Eastenders and a North American cereal marketing campaign for Sultana Bran. In 1995 Andrew appeared on the David Frost show alongside Eric Clapton & John Cleese, He continues to contribute his unique wit and individual take on life with occasional appearances on radio and TV chat shows. Growing up in Stanmore, one of Andrew\'s neighbors was Roger Moore who Andrew\'s mum knew from her years working with Theo Cowan, chief publicist of the Rank Organisation. Roger would often give Andrew \'The Saint\' halo head and eye raise much to his amusement! He also cites seeing actor John Slater (Tom Stone in Z Cars) walking his dog as influencing his later career moves! Shouting out \"Look Mum! It\'s Tom Stone!\" in St John\'s Wood one Sunday, John said \"With a voice like that, you should work in the movies!\"<br><br>His professional influences are as varied as fellow Producers Hank Bargine and Brian Clemens, his favorite directors are Rachel Liebling, Stanley Kubrick and Robert Hamer. His is the unique ability to produce thought provoking documentary programming with mass appeal and huge marketing potential. Between 1996 and 2001 Andrew contributed his talents to over 40 productions. He has worked with fellow producers as diverse as Ron Zimmerman and Duncan Kenworthy and his good friend David Yates. Andrew has ghost written books for Paul Martin and has a number of projects awaiting commissioning. Andrew is also developing a reality show for a US Network and continues to indulge his love of history.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2692170','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545876001),(1395,'Annarie Boor',NULL,'Annarie Boor was born in South Africa, before spending her teenage years in Zambia. Having passed her dance teaching exams at the age of 15, she opened a dance school in Lusaka, Zambia where she taught for a number of years before moving to the UK in her early twenties. She subsequently spent a number of years in the Cayman Islands before returning to London to further her career and that of her actress daughter, <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm9244518?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Juliette Boor</a>. Her other daughter <a href=\"https://nullrefer.com/?https://www.imdb.com/name/nm8690230?ref_=nmbio_mbio\">Danielle Boor</a> is also an actress.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7707203','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMjIwNjgxMTY4MV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMzc1MDIzMDI@._V1_UY317_CR39,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1396,'Fares Boulos',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5010631','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNjc2YzgxNWItOWMyNi00ODcxLTg1MjgtNWY0OGQ4YzEyZWM0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1397,'Marco Brown',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9785850','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzgzNDkwMjMxMF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMDg2NDMwNTM@._V1_UY317_CR272,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1398,'Tahir Burhan',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9391948','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545876001),(1399,'David Charles-Cully',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6373664','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTYzODMxOTA1N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMzIwMDM0NzE@._V1_UY317_CR1,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1400,'Al Clark',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1004396',NULL,0),(1401,'Michael Cobb',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9830988','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMWE4MGFjMTYtODE0Ny00OTllLTgyMTItODdmN2EwMjg4M2RhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODgxNzM4MzY@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1402,'Oliver Conte',NULL,'Oliver Carmelo Conte is a London-born, Anglo-Italian actor, musician and producer. In his younger years he performed for a variety of television and film companies, including ITV, and featured as the lead in a Cannes Film Festival (short) that was nominated for several awards. His attention later turned to being behind the camera and he now works as an aspiring producer and music agent for talent in the entertainment industry.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'3365422','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545877801),(1403,'Tiziana Coste',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1022218',NULL,0),(1404,'Matthew Cox',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1006422',NULL,0),(1405,'Silvia Crastan',NULL,'Born in Switzerland, with German, Swiss and Italian ancestors, Silvia Crastan trained from age 7 as a violinist/musician and performed as a freelance musician (Supported by Pro Helvetia), often together with her sister Eva Crastan (Piano). Her concert activity has led her to many places such as India, Mexico, Palestine ,Italy, UK, Germany, Poland, Russia, Korea etc where she eagerly studied history, social attitudes, cultures and languages, having always had an interest in sociology, gender issues and analyzing human behavior in various settings and situations. Her father, Valentin Crastan (born in Genova) is an engineer and book author (Elektrische Energieversorgung 1,2 and 3) and her German mother Ruth Schmied has been working as a secretary. Classical music, books and the arts (e.g. visiting art galleries and architecture in Italy) have always had high priority in their family. Silvia was educated in Switzerland at Biel/Bienne Grammar School and started her BMus + MMus studies age 17 ( violin, music history, music theory, analysis, chamber music, Alexander Technique, and Reciting/Singing) In 1999, she went on to the Guildhall School of Music & Drama in London to continue her Postgraduate Studies, having won a bursary from Dienemann Stiftung (Luzern). The death of her best friend/partner in 2008 brought a drastic halt and change to her life and after 2 years of depression and doing literally nothing, she took up screen acting, training Drama at City Lit, Central School and Actors\' Temple in London. Silvia has always been a great fan of Fellini\'s and Chaplin\'s movies, James Bond and British comedies and in particular loves the cinematography of Anthony Dod Mantle. Silvia is Violinist at Serpentyne (Symphonic Metal band)<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'4604981','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545877801),(1406,'Grant Crookes',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5103443','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545877801),(1407,'Sabine Crossen',NULL,'Sabine Crossen is a bilingual actress (French mother, American father) who was born in the United States but grew up in NZ. When she was 20 years old she moved to Paris to study acting at the Actorat Dramatic Arts College where she landed her first role playing the Virgin Mary.<br><br>Sabine\'s first role in a feature film was playing an Elf in Lord Of The Rings.<br><br>In 2003 she had her first lead role portraying Kim Lee in the independent feature film Shadow Girl that won several awards; Platinum Award Houston (USA) and Thessaloniki (Greece) Best Image.<br><br>During this time Sabine was also on the prime time Canal+ Hypershow presenting stars like David Bowie, John Malkovitch, The Cranberries and Adrien Brody.<br><br>She has written songs for several compilation albums winning 3 gold discs.<br><br>In 2005 after playing the Rita in Surface Sensible the blockbuster The Brice Man (starring Jean Dujardin star of The Artist) came out where she plays his young mother-in-law.<br><br>During this time Sabine also presented for the Alcatel web TV filming in France and Spain over several years.<br><br>2006 brought In Memoriam II: The Last Ritual (In Memoriam won the 2003 best game award world), which gave her the lead role of Jessica Moses. Filming took place in Canada, USA, Portugal, Scotland and France.<br><br>Then in 2007 Sabine played the lead female part of the alien Dragonfly Fairy in Car Academy, also interpreting the song \"Superman\" for the original soundtrack. The DVD won a double diamond disc in France.<br><br>Sabine then discovered motion capture and had the opportunity to play in several video games; Heavy Rain, Red Steel 2, Lana Del Rey. She then had the privilege of playing June in the game that became the film Hitman with Timothy Olyphant and Olga Kurylenko.<br><br>3 years later she seduces Philippe Lellouche and Franck Dubosc in the movie Bienvenue A Bord (Welcome A Bord)<br><br>In 2012 things start to accelerate for Sabine who flies to Hong Kong and China to film S.O.L.I.I.D a pre-quel for the feature film where she will play the lead of a dangerous android. She then returns to Hong Kong to film the role of Joan in The Borderland starring Seydina Baldé.<br><br>Back in Paris she films Le Grand Méchant Loup (The Big Bad Wolf) playing a naughty dominatrix and then the role of a reporter in Crossing Lines directed by Daniel Percival and finally a Texan facing Pierce Brosnan and Emma Thompson in The Love Punch. Out in 2013.<br><br>2014 saw Sabine travel back to Hong Kong to film as Joan in director Mathieu Weschler\'s debut film Couvert Operation. She also filmed in Rosemary\'s Baby an NBC TV series.<br><br>In 2015 Sabine played the role of Freya in Predator Dark Ages, a fan film which has today 1.9 million vues on YouTube. She learnt how to use a bow and arrow for this role and looks a little like Orlando Blooms character in L.O.T.R, Legolas. Two other short films Spavento and award winning Blue-Eyed Me finished the year.<br><br>Her first role in a horror feature film S.H.C.I.A.W as the bad girl Ana was shot in March/April 2016 written and directed by Simon P. Edward with award winning D.O.P Andrew Martin. This involved on screen fight scenes with a lot of action and FX. Family comedy It\'s All About The Manners shot in 2016 in the UK is a film about the Manners adopting 2 chaotic boys that turn the kingdom of Barland upside down. Sabine plays the role of Jenny Manners.<br><br>Sabine is the brand ambassador for Chablis 2012 alongside Plus Belle La Vie Star Ambroise Michel. Sabine was an official jury member of the International Crime Film Festival in Liège 2013. She has won 10 awards for her short film L\'amour Rend Aveugle (Love Is Blind)<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1644336','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BM2E1OWJlMTctOTdmMy00YzdjLTk1MDctMDJkZjI3NWYwMWM3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDIxNTg2MjE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1408,'Tom Dab',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6426525','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZWFiZjMwMTYtMWEyMS00NDkzLWI2ZmEtMzQ3MjRlYThiZjk0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTE4ODc4ODQ@._V1_UY317_CR38,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1409,'Stuart Daly',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8520696','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZWE3ZTgzN2ItYjA4Ny00YWQyLWJmNTYtOTcwOWI3OGI3YWFhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjg4MzczMjI@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479),(1410,'Nick Davison',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7618414','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/G/01/imdb/images/nopicture/medium/name-2135195744._CB470041852_.png',1545877801),(1411,'Sarah-Jane De Crespigny',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3506359','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOTUxNzBhZmUtNmJkMy00NTZhLTliMTgtMTI0YzIyNzU3NmU5XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDk5OTU5Mzc@._V1_UY317_CR12,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545843479)