oductions. Johns radiant smile, likable personality, unstoppable energy, diverse range and dedication to his craft allow him to also pursue and find success in live television hosting. DiRenzo is also working his way up the acting ladder via parts in commercials. DiRenzo began his professional acting career at age 43 , appearing as a background performer in After Earth (2012) . Since then DiRenzo has worked on hundreds of projects including short films, feature films, television, commercials, print and voice over productions. John also has credits as a producer, assistant director. director, script supervisor, casting associate and other miscellaneous crew positions. DiRenzo has worked on print modeling projects with west coast photographer Brian Kuhlmann and world renown portrait photographer Annie Leibovitz . In early 2016 John began working as a correspondent for Wildfire Radios show Small Bites, a food, hospitality and travel program.<br><br>In October 2017 John became a guest host at QVC and presents products for kitchen and cookware companies. John has found success and his true passion with live television hosting and has plans to continue to look for opportunities in hosting television programs as well as pursuing his acting career. Fall of 2017 DiRenzo closed his brick and mortar business and on-line retail store after 15 years. The acting bug bit DiRenzo hard as he found success almost instantly. It was 2012 when DiRenzo decided to pursue his acting career and not the business world. Over the next few years John merged his retail store on-line allowing him to brake away from the 9-5 grind of retail allowing him the flexibility and availability needed to compete in the entertainment industry. This allowed John to just scrape by financially as this business model provided him with just enough income to peruse his dream and true passions. DiRenzo also began supplementing his income during these lean years working as a rideshare driver.<br><br>John Joseph DiRenzo was born November 9th 1968 in Norristown Pennsylvania . John is of Italian heritage and the last of five children parented by Lena and Nicholas A DiRenzo Sr. John\'s father was a butcher, fresh meat market and multi unit grocery store owner. As a young child and teen John spent the majority of his time working in the family markets. John is a culinary professional with over 35 years in the grocery, produce, fresh meat, restaurant business and is an experienced chef, butcher, bartender and restaurant consultant. DiRenzo grew up in Norristown, in an upper middle class area in the suburbs of Philadelphia. John was a marching, concert band and stage band percussionist at Norristown Area High School . During his adolescent years, DiRenzo remained in school music studies and began performing with local garage bands. In his early 20\'s John worked as night club lighting tech and disc jockey performing at several Philadelphia venues. In his early 20\'s John married Suzanne Clark and together they had a son, John DiRenzo Jr was born on June 5th 1994. John and Suzanne divorced after one year of marriage.<br>\n         ','1968-11-09 00:00:00',NULL,'Norristown, Pennsylvania, USA','5592004','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTk5NjUwNTAyOV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDU3ODM3MjE@._V1_UY317_CR91,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(1997,'S.J. Doss',NULL,'S.J. Doss is a writer and independent filmmaker from The New Jersey/Philadelphia area. S.J. started indulging into the arts at a very young age. Before he could do anything, he would draw made-up characters on any scrap piece of paper he could find. He would record audio movies of his own on tape recorders, and try to get other family and friends involved on the stories. S.J. had a much older half brother who had some video equipment. When S.J. first got the chance to help out at the age of 7 on a short horror film, he was instantly hooked. As time went on, and S.J. was making films with his older brother and then using friend\'s parent\'s home camcorders, the obsession grew even more. His interest grew so strong that most people around him didn\'t share the same passion, and it became hard to continue doing projects and taking them to higher levels. After awhile, when S.J. reached his teens, he was conditioned by everyone around him that making movies was nothing but a dream. It was something that could never be possible. He was taught, that where he came from, he had to go out and get a job with the mentality to conform to the norm and be happy with just a decent paycheck.<br><br>Years went by and S.J. bought some sound recording equipment as a side hobby. He built a bedroom studio and had some major radio success with his personal projects. S.J. liked it but he wasn\'t fulfilled. Not until he got word about how affordable and cinematic DSLR cameras were. He purchased a DSLR and the passion he had as a kid kicked right back in and went into higher gears. S.J. has a strong love for cinematography but came to the realization that you cannot have a good film without a good story. He felt he had great story ideas and fresh concepts, but he wanted to make sure he mastered the craft of story structure and screenwriting, understanding and valuing the importance.<br><br>To this day, S.J. Doss works very hard in developing his story ideas and bringing them to life in his own courageous and unique perspective. S.J. Doss just recently placed second in the horror short script category for The Indie Film Gathering International. It was S.J. Doss\' first script he has ever submitted into a festival or competition.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9093664','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZjY2YjcxYjAtMjZhNi00OTk5LWI5NTAtZWM1ZTE2NzQ1NjQxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzc3NTMxMDM@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(1998,'Lisa Edmondson',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9644012','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTJiN2JiMzUtMmMwZC00NGRjLWJjMTUtODY3ZDM2OTE3YmM2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzkxNjkyMTA@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(1999,'Cole Elliott',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9541072',NULL,0),(2000,'Alexander Emmert',NULL,'Born in London while his parents were living overseas, Alexander Emmert moved to the United States as a young man. A short music career preceded his academic exploits at the University of Oregon and Harvard, after which he began a lucrative tenure as an Executive Recruiter in New York until one of his early loves in life, performing, drew him away from the corporate world.<br><br>Mr. Emmert has performed on stage and in numerous independent and studio films, as well as in television series and specials. He is a Big Four repped screenwriter and independent film producer. Emmert also served as Program Director for Encore Entertainment\'s Creative Theatre Group Summer Camps for Film and Theatre in 2003, prior to incorporating Invictus Films in 2004. He has directed several music videos (most recently for The Replacements/Soul Asylum/Guns N Roses bassist Tommy Stinson), and written and produced numerous historical documentaries for cable television.<br><br>Alexander Emmert wrote, produced and directed \"The Judas Kiss\", which was the Grande Premiere Event at the Monaco International Festival of Film; co-produced and directed \"Between Us, Love\", which is headlining the Urban World 2010 Festival in New York City, and was Assistant Producer and Assistant Director of \"Elle: A Modern Cinderella Tale\", which won Best Family Feature at the Newport Beach Films Festival in 2010. Mr. Emmert and his team have also created several renowned historical documentaries, including \"The Revolution\", \"Rome: Rise and Fall of an Empire\" and the \"Rome: Engineering An Empire\" special, which won two Primetime Emmys and was nominated for two others.<br><br>While continuing to perform in front of the camera and on the stage, Mr. Emmert\'s producing and screenwriting career have taken flight. He works on both US coasts and in Europe, and is hopeful of expanding Invictus Films\' coproductions into Asia and Australia in 2011 and beyond. He lives with his dog Raja in both Los Angeles and Philadelphia at varying times of year.<br>\n         ','1974-10-03 00:00:00',NULL,'London, England, UK','2772986','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTM3Mjk0NTYyOF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwNDg5NTE3Nw@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2001,'Nathan Ferguson',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'5132618','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BN2M4MDZjNDAtNTRiMi00ZjIwLWFmNGUtZTEyM2UwZDYyZDE1XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzU3MDYyNDc@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2002,'Darin Ferraro','Darin Patrick Ferraro','Hello everyone, his name is Darin Patrick Ferraro. His name use to be Darin Patrick Moressi but changed when his mother and father divorced. His mother, His brother and Darin decided to change it back to his mothers parent\'s original last name. Which is Ferraro. His name is Darin Ferraro. Darin was born in Tampa Florida. At the age of 8 years old His mother put Darin in his very first theater play role. He loved theater and acting ever since. He later went on to do over 7,500 Commercials and over 400 Films and Corporate Films. He does all work from Movies to commercials to infomercials to corporate films to Hosting to Costume Characters for well-known charity Organizations. Darin loves acting. Acting is his life.<br><br>Now you will see that Darin just does not acted, He also Sings, Dances, Performs and Hosts but Acting is something that he does a ton of. Darin comes from a wonderful Latin family. Half of Darin\'s family is Italian/Sicilian and his other half of his family is Cuban. He does speak a little bit of Spanish and Fluent in English. What Darin wants is to be one of the best actors ever in the entire world. What Darin wants from the world is peace for all human kind. Darin also wants to be one of the best leaders in charity to help the poor and cure the sick within the entire world.<br><br> Thank you everyone for visiting Darin Ferraro\'s IMDB Page. God Bless you all.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5155353','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZWRhZDdlZGEtZDNjNC00NmJhLTgxNGYtZmRjZDViZTFkNWM1XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODI2NjMzOTA@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2003,'Pedro Flores',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9543259','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMmFiOTQ1ZDctNTMxYi00YmQ2LWJiY2EtMGVhZWJmYjk3YzZhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODMzNTIyNjY@._V1_UY317_CR130,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2004,'Justin Fortmeier',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4328442',NULL,0),(2005,'Sebastian Foxworth',NULL,'Sebastian Foxworth is the writer/creator/artist of America\'s first syndicated interracial/blended family comic strip and animated shorts \"The Family Blend!\" (NNPA, Skanner Publishing, Amazon Prime Video) whose tagline is \"A mixed up family living in a mixed up world\" or their favorite, \"We put the FUN in dysfunctional family.\" The comic strip and cartoon shorts poke fun at; family life, pop culture and the struggle of old school values vs new school ways. His PG13 animated short \"The Family Blend! : Scoobeeman Begins!\" has been featured at San Diego Comic Con 2016/17 and Wonder Con 2016/17 Children\'s Film Festival where he drew large crowds ranging from ages 8-80.<br><br>A student of Cheyney University\'s New Media Design/TV & Film Communications Program, He\'s won numerous awards starting with his first animation \"Soccerdad: The Boy Thinks He\'s Jesus!\" which became the basis for \"The Family Blend!\" comic strip and animated shorts. He\'s also won and has had numerous nominations for his animation short \"The Family Blend X-mas: My Ninja\'s X-mas!\" and various other shorts. Sebastian is always out on the grind of the comic con scene and social media sites bringing the comic strip and animations into the view of the world, meeting his fans and being a guest speaker on panels.<br><br>Sebastian is hitting the film fest circuits with his award winning Documentary Shorts \"The Great American Depression(men)\" and \"The Great American Depression 2 - I\'m Not Crazy\" that deals with men and ethnic communities battling depression and his suspense/dramedy short films \"Unexpalinable\" and \"What\'s The Matter With Mommy\" both which have won multiple awards.<br><br>The awards circuit has been kind to Sebastian as he\'s won multiple awards for: Animation, Writing, Directing, Editing, Composing and has been nominated for the same categories many times over - including two Mid-Atlantic Regional Emmys for variety programming.<br><br>Since 2004, Sebastian has been involved in the media game (television, film, digital, press) and has continued to grow his company Foxworth Media to the respectable and entertaining company that it is today.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'6082148','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZjEyNDAwODItMGExMy00MGFlLTllODItMjJhNDQzMDIxMzlhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDc0MjgyODc@._V1_UY317_CR130,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2006,'Anthony Franzzo',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7897004',NULL,0),(2007,'Mark P Galbraith',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8021738','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYWRlODk2NTMtM2RmMy00Njg0LWI1MzEtYzllOGZkYjMzMzliXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjU5MDYyODc@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2008,'Elizabeth Gaynor',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4972754','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZjFlNDkxMjItYjI4OS00NWRiLWFmNzYtMTc1ZWFiZTlmZDMxXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzI4NzA1OTc@._V1_UY317_CR17,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2009,'Michael P Gennett',NULL,'Michael P Gennett was born on November 9th, 1963 in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, to Catherine(Kitty) (Reilly), a personnel company executive assistant, and John (Jack) Gennett (born John William Gennett), an electronics specialist at RCA. His father was of Scottish and Italian ancestry, while his maternal grandparents were Scottish immigrants from Glasgow, Scotland. Michael was a lackluster student at Cardinal Dougherty High School East in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania (never above a C average, average track athlete and involved in most school drama productions). After high school Michael moved from Philadelphia to Brigantine, NJ. After dropping out of Stockton State College in New Jersey, where he did some acting, Michael worked in Atlantic City as a Casino bartender, and a Craps Dealer. Michael moved to a suburb of Philadelphia and enjoyed a career in Real Estate. A lifelong Philadelphia resident, Michael of course was a huge Rocky fan and crashed the set of Rocky Balboa while it was filming on the 9th St Italian Market in South Philadelphia, scoring a whopping 3 seconds of camera time as unpaid, and probably unwanted, background extra. And so the long lost acting desire was re-awakened and in 2018 Michael submitted for Creed 2 and was cast as a Russian Military Officer, escorting the Drago Entourage and performing security in the Drago corner. Also in 2018 Michael was cast in two roles in Miss Atkins Army, a WWII period piece, first as a OSS Officer (pre-sursor to the CIA), and then as a Officer in The British Royal Air Force. Constant comparisons to Harrison Ford\'s dry humor and reluctant hero rogue acting style and Patrick Dempsey looks, Michael is a actor to keep your eye on for a much bigger story.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9830353','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYjc1MmVmMWMtYjI5Zi00ODBhLWI3MmMtYTYxMDczZjU0ZDRhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODc5OTYzNzA@._V1_UY317_CR6,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2010,'Peter Georgo',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9443519','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYjYxYTdkYjktZjIzMC00NTM2LTkyMTYtODA1N2QyM2ViNGJkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODE5NDE1NDA@._V1_UY317_CR34,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2011,'Linzi Gray','Lindsey Childress','Born in Richmond, Virginia as Lindsey Childress, Linzi insisted at age 5 to attend ballet school, setting her on a performing path in life. She later turned her focus to acting and joined her middle school\'s Drama Club, where she played the supporting role in Cinderella, A Middle School Christmas Carol and The Little Red Riding Hoods. Upon entering high school, she did Theatre and played the lead in A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to the Forum and Much Ado About Nothing. After high school, Linzi starred in a few student films and a web series called Mob Wars. Linzi landed her first American role as one of the Mourners in Homeland Season 7 Episode 5 \"Active Measures\". She worked in background on Creed 2 and House of Cards.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9752272','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZGExYTFjOWItN2MxYy00ZDg2LThkYzktM2M5YTgyOGYzOWNjXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODIxMzIzNDE@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2012,'Cameron Guile',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8894967',NULL,0),(2013,'Xavier Hale',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8745507',NULL,0),(2014,'Lucky Harmon',NULL,'Lucky is a multi-talented SAG-AFTRA ACTOR POP Artist Songwriter, and father of two, originally hailing from Baltimore, Maryland. Now transplanted to Atlanta, Georgia, he is looking to make his mark on the Pop/Dance/EDM scene. Citing Justin Timberlake, Michael Jackson, Calvin Harris, and The Black Eyed Peas as influences, Lucky\'s inspirations for his own music are drawn from both life experience and his constant search for fresh new sounds. When he hears a sound or beat that moves him, he immediately hits the studio and sets to work. Music has always been a part of Lucky\'s life. Throughout his childhood and teen years, he participated in drama,chorus, vocal ensemble, and show choir, performing locally and statewide. This instilled him with stage presence and a sense of showmanship from an early age. His passion for music has only continued to deepen. In 2008, Lucky released his first EP, Welcome to My World, produced by Matthew \"Teezy\" White with More Than Music Productions at the Baker Boyz Entertainment recording studio. He has also recorded with Rufus Blaq, who he met while performing at Packard Music Hall in Warren, Ohio, and has opened for Jae Millz of Young Money. His singles \"Narcissist\" and \"Love Has a Mind of Its Own\" have filled dance floors from Washington, D.C., to Philly to New York City. In 2010, Lucky experienced a tragic setback when he lost his manager and close family friend, Milton Chmielewski, suddenly. During this time, Lucky turned to acting, auditioning for and starring in numerous commercials, television shows, and movies. His resume includes roles in The Vampire Diaries, Drop Dead Divas, House of Cards, Veep, and Fast & Furious 7. He is continuing to nurture his acting career. While he was in Atlanta filming for FF7, he met A&R Executive Rob Medley through a chance encounter in a hotel lobby. Medley heard Lucky sing and soon introduced him to his business partner, Grammy-nominated producer Eric \"88 Fingaz\" Parham. Shortly afterwards, Lucky was signed to Keys2Life Entertainment, LLC, and started laying down tracks like \"Idolize Me\", \"Commodity\", and \"Party Life\" with 88 Fingaz and Rob Medley at Hot Beats Studio in downtown Atlanta. His single \"IDOLIZE ME\" charted billboard top40 number #36 and Party Life was #28 on the top50. Lucky is eager to take his career to the next level and share his passion with the world. He has the looks, talent, and experience to launch the next wave of music and acting he\'s loyal genuine and hard working good actor With his positive spirit and incredible work ethic, he will be creating smash hits far into the future and beyond .<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5991113','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOGRhMDE4ZDAtZWQ4My00Yjc0LWJjMDMtYWYwYTRkNWI2OTc3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2015,'Carla Harnell',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1010691','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZDA5NjUxZDYtNjY1My00MmI1LTg4OGYtMDE5Zjg0NGJlZmViXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyOTIzMDQ5ODI@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545881626),(2016,'Michael Patrick Hart',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9865053',NULL,0),(2017,'Monica Haynes',NULL,'Born and raised in Cincinnati, Ohio, Monica Ellen Scott is the middle of three children. She began her acting career after four years of working as a professional print model. Her \"big break\" came when she landed a recurring background role as a secret service agent on the hit Netflix series \"House of Cards\". Monica is married and a mother of two children. Monica quit her 15-year career in Corporate America to run her health & wellness business WrapMaven.com, and is enjoying life as an entrepreneur/model/actor. Her motto, \"Live Fearlessly\".<br>\n         ','1977-08-25 00:00:00',NULL,'Cincinnati, Ohio, USA','7745519','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYWVmMWFiMDctMzQ5Mi00NzAxLTkwMDEtZjdkOWU0MDI0NGNkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR64,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2018,'Ben Heyman',NULL,'Ben Z. Heyman was born in West Hempstead, NY on January 1st. His mother, Joyce, is a loving and caring nurse. His father, Adam, is an amazing culinary artist. Ben\'s first major accomplishment was graduating second in his middle school class, though many viewed this as a lacking merit, seeing as the class only consisted of two children.<br><br>Before Ben dedicated his life to acting, he was on the path to becoming a \"righteous man.\" After high school, he spent a year and a half in Beit Shemesh, Israel learning religious philosophies, laws and practices. Upon returning to the States, he enrolled in a religious college in New York City to continue his studies. After a year of this schooling, Ben realized something was missing from his life, primarily good grades, so he made the difficult, yet necessary decision to transfer to Brooklyn College.<br><br>Upon entering Brooklyn College, several new opportunities presented themselves to him. Both acting and broadcasting, which before were only minor hobbies, became the focuses of his life. He began to study and craft his own unique style, primarily from trial and error, and was also heavily influenced by Uta Hagen\'s writing. In addition, Ben ran the Brooklyn College Hillel\'s theater department for four years, and in 2011 wrote his first play, \'Through the Fire\', based on his cousin\'s story of surviving a death camp during the Holocaust.<br><br>Throughout his college education, Ben acted in several shows, namely \'Journey\'s End\', \'Newsies\', \'Play On\', \'I Never Saw Another Butterfly\', and \'Angel in the Night\'. However, during this time, Ben struggled with deciding what career path he should ultimately take, since he knew that the path to acting was a decision his family and friends would not fully support. While working at a home for adults with intellectual disabilities, Ben worked with Max, an individual who was severely handicapped. Max couldn\'t speak and could barely walk, yet nothing made him happier than watching Ben act out different scenes from his favorite movies. It was Ben\'s time working with Max that convinced him to pursue acting, so after graduating from Brooklyn College with a Bachelor of Arts degree in TV and Radio Production, he decided to work toward his dream and took acting classes at The Neighborhood Playhouse, before moving to Los Angeles in July 2014.<br><br>While in Los Angeles, Ben worked in multiple productions, including \'Attack of the Killer Donuts\'. After a year of living in Los Angeles, Ben moved back to New York to use what he had learned and experienced in Los Angeles to build upon and further his budding career.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'6407108','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BY2E5YmZjNGItZTkyZi00ZDJkLWI4ZWItMmU1ZTY5YWNjZjdhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjEyNjgzOTM@._V1_UY317_CR131,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2019,'Joseph Horning',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2684628',NULL,0),(2020,'David Hummel',NULL,NULL,'1955-05-05 00:00:00',NULL,'New Brunswick, New Jersey, USA','0401828','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNWQ3ODM2ZWItMjc5Ny00YjE2LWIyNjItY2RhNWUyYzUwNGU3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjMwNzIzNTY@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2021,'Myles Humphus',NULL,'Son to a Delta Project Green Beret turned high school history teacher and a seamstress turned folk dancer and brother to an Army Ranger turned restauranteur, Myles was genetically predisposed to dramatic change. A promising football career turned corporate turned prize fighter turned stuntman turned actor. It is in Acting where Myles found purpose. Having no Arts program that he so greatly desired, in his formative years he constantly rebelled often finding himself in some \'interesting\' situations. Myles found peace and satisfaction in the world of acting. Studying Konstantin Stanislavski\'s Method, Lee Strasburg\'s Method and Sanford Meisner\'s Technique, has helped Myles grow in his appreciation and understanding of the craft of Acting as he continues to strive for greatness. MYLESHUMPHUS.COM<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5151832','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNmRhYmFlODgtMzJkYS00NDAzLWJjMzQtYzhhODYyZGE3Nzg0XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMzQ5NTUxOTk@._V1_UY317_CR3,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2022,'Konstantine James',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8215148','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BODk4YzllYTctNTg2ZC00MTg4LWIzOGMtNDA2ZTdhZGRmMWVkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjc3OTgyMTI@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2023,'Nick Jones',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8177461',NULL,0),(2024,'Frankie Justin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9894821','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTAzNTU0NTAtMGQzNS00NTU1LTgzNDktODZiMDY0MTlhZGQwXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODkxMzUyMTc@._V1_UY317_CR131,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2025,'Toby Kearton','Toby William Kearton','Toby Kearton is a British independent award winning director, screenwriter & producer based in London, England and Los Angeles, California. He is is best known for the independent short film \'Dissonance\' (2018) as well as the short films \'The Little Picture\' (2018) and \'The Dust Child\' (2018). He has recently announced his involvement in his feature film directorial debut.<br><br>Born in Harlow, Essex, UK on June 20th 1997 as a young child, Toby had an infinite number of titles available to him. After realizing filmmaking and storytelling was his passion, he began to make stop motion animation films at the age of 8, borrowing his fathers digital camera and became a member of the BFI (British Film Institute) in 2012. In 2014 Toby was employed as a runner on the British film \'Tulip Fever\' (2017), ultimately starting his film career at the age of 17. After finishing school at the age of 18 and having completed A-levels in Modern History, Archaeology, Politics and Film, Toby attended film school in Burbank, California. Toby graduated from The New York Film Academy in 2018 with a Bachelor of Fine Arts. In his 3 years at film school Toby completed many short films which were entered into various film festivals across the world. Since being situated in California he has directed many short films, including \'Ruthless Satisfaction\' (2015), \'Check The Trunk\' (2016), \'The Solipsist Mind\' (2016), \'Dissonance\' (2018), \'The Dust Child\' (2018), \'Land Mine\' (2018) and \'The Little Picture\' (2018). He has recently announced his involvement in the reality TV show \'Magic Hour with Daniel Annerl (2018) and his feature film directorial debut.<br>\n         ','1997-06-20 00:00:00',NULL,'United Kingdom','7788905','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDhkMmIzNGQtZWEyNC00NzA2LWEwZDAtN2VjMmFkZmMxNDkwXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDU0ODI1NjQ@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2026,'JaQuinley Kerr',NULL,'JaQuinley Kerr is an actress and director, known for Ryan (2016), Trinity (2008) and The Message (video short). In addition, she has toured the U.S. with the Rodney Marsalis Philadelphia Big Brass, narrating and singing for their specialty concerts. She is the author of How the Light Gets In, which juxtaposes some of her poems and photographs. The book is available via her website.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'3094484','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTU2NjE5NzEwMF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjUyNTM0NjE@._V1_UY317_CR130,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545846881),(2027,'Marty Krzywonos',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3801095','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTg2NjYzNzc4NV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwODMyMDk3OQ@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847150),(2028,'Susan Lang',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9381164','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZTdiMGY4MDEtZTlmNi00NzFhLWJjMDQtNGIxOWM1NzUyNTA4XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847150),(2029,'Gina Lerario',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8382109',NULL,0),(2030,'John Wes Lewis',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7862353','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDRiMzBhZGYtZjBkZC00N2NiLWJlZmUtZmRlNmZmMTg1MTY3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjQ3NzMzNTA@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847150),(2031,'Noelle Loizos','Noelle Loizos','Noelle Loizos is originally from Freehold, NJ, and is a bi-coastal theatre, television and film actress, writer, director, and producer. She began her career as a child actor on stages throughout New Jersey and began working in film and television while studying at Rutgers\' Mason Gross School of the Arts. After college, she continued taking advanced acting classes in Manhattan and found herself back on the stage in her first Off-Broadway show, Dress of Fire, starring Austin Pendleton.<br><br>She has worked with industry veterans like Sylvester Stallone and Seth MacFarlane after she was actively sought out during the 2017 Tribeca Film Festival when she met indie producers who were in need of assistance in pitching a $3B revenue company for product placement in the animated feature film. Ms. Loizos used her expertise in sales to create a pitch packet and developed a strategic execution plan to pursue the monies, inevitably launching her production company Nolo Entertainment, while continuing her acting career.<br><br>Ms. Loizos received a full scholarship to Rutgers University where she graduated cum laude with a B.A. in Communication, Film Studies, and Theater. During her undergrad, she was initiated into two honor societies and served on the board of the Hellenic Culture Association. Her acting studies continued post college graduation at James Franco\'s Studio 4, Stella Adler, and The People\'s Improv Theater in New York City. She received a CER from The Professional Program in Producing, modeled after the UCLA M.F.A. Producers Program where she learned from industry heads such as Paul Green, Adam Fogelson, Maggie Murphy, and Sheila Hanahan-Taylor.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5874004','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOTFlMjgzYzMtMGVlNi00NWU4LWEwMjctNzUyYmEyNjA2YjFhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODA4MTE5ODg@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847150),(2032,'April Love',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'9693095','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNzI2ZDcyM2EtNTU3OC00YTEzLWJkMTUtN2JlNTE3NDYyN2VlXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODY3NTg0NTg@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847150),(2033,'Jon Madray',NULL,'Jon Madray (Also known as JonOne) is a Guyanese-American Internet personality. He is an actor most notable for his comedy skits on Instagram and Facebook, as well as an electronic music producer and DJ.<br><br>A fusion of both dance and Caribbean elements in his tracks has brought something totally new to the table. Through 11 years of creating remixes, mixtapes, and now his own original productions and a weekly podcast series, JonOne has slowly been growing to become a household name in today\'s generation of producers.<br><br>In 2011, his tracks were regularly played on NY radio stations and clubs, and over the past few years, he attained bookings at various venues around NYC such as Pacha NYC, Space, the Best Buy Theater, Highline Ballroom, Hudson Terrace, District 36, and System. He has also shared the stage with other acclaimed DJs and artists such as Major Lazer, 3LAU, PartyNextDoor, Dyro, Laidback Luke, and more.<br><br>In 2012, JonOne released his first productions on Beatport and iTunes and did several oversea shows. Later that year, JonOne completed an official collaboration with Grammy nominated producer, Avicii, on his track \"X You\" by winning Avicii\'s remix contest. He also established Sonar Projects as his official management team and performed at the famous Best Buy Theater in Times Square for Bounce Music Festival and in Seaside Heights for Electric Adventure Festival in 2014.<br><br>3 Years later JonOne has still been pushing his music hard and also started to fulfill his interests in film. Along with his friends and brother, Jon started gaining popularity for his short comedy skits on Instagram and Facebook. Several skits have broke over a million views and his most popular skit racked up 10.6 million views on Facebook. Jon has also collaborated with actresses and artists such as Sonna Rele and Melinda Shankar in these skits and plans to continue film along with his music.<br><br>In 2018, Jon got casted in his first TV series (Billions) and first movie. (Creed II) He was also featured on award winning chef Marcus Samuelsson\'s TV series \"No Passport Required\" where he discussed his Guyanese heritage and foods, and how he incorporates his culture into his music.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'9672377','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDg4ZjFkMzQtMGUxNC00OTlmLWEwZWEtN2Y3NmQ2NmVjYjM4XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyODU5MjU0ODA@._V1_UY317_CR27,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847150),(2034,'Mark Marcarian',NULL,'Born in 1963 and raised in Philadelphia until the age of five, Mark came from a creative family. He has keen insight on the lighter side of humanity.<br><br>His father Jéan Marcarian was born in Marseilles, France and came over with his sister Louise. Marks Uncle was also a great artist as well.<br><br>\"My Uncle Mike truly influenced me a great deal as an artistic person.\" In the 1980\'s Mark had a desire to get into television broadcasting. He attended the infamous American School of Broadcasting which was owned by Long John Wade the disc jockey from Philadelphia.<br><br>While attending American Academy of Broadcasting (AAB), Mark migrated back to his \"home base\" in Warminster, PA to live with his best friend Peter Betts for some time.<br><br>Mark worked odd jobs, mostly in retail as he made his way through Bucks County Community College as a communications major.<br><br>Eventually, Mark became a retail manager and moved onto companies such as Pep Boys, Giant and Amerada Hess Corporation; (HESS gas stations)<br><br>Mark was married in April of 1986 but divorced in 1998. He has two children, Brandyn and Ryan. \"Mark was always trying to make people laugh. He had to because his home life growing up was terrible.\"<br><br>\"His outlet was his innate ability make others laugh. To this day, I still think back and chuckle.\" states childhood friend Scott Schubert.<br><br>In the meantime, Mark has enjoyed acting in many films and has stepped up his goals and drive to become a truly awesome actor. His natural talent is in playing all types of roles from a lawyer, doctor, serial killer, father almost any character. Mark has great range be it a comedy, horror, action or drama.<br><br>Says Mark, \"I love acting because it provides me the ability to transcend and actually step into someone\'s life and become that person.\"<br><br>\"I\'m Always seeing life\'s lighter side, trying to make people laugh and truly love to perform, especially in front of a camera.\"<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'4193949','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNjM5NzVmMzYtMmEwMC00YTE4LTg1NTctY2JhODdhN2E5ZTVjXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR16,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847150),(2035,'John Martineau',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0553304',NULL,0),(2036,'Jamie Mattus',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7673438',NULL,0),(2037,'Sumier Mention',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'7276401',NULL,0),(2038,'Mike Miedzinski',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'8969484','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMmQ3MjMzOGMtYWI5My00N2FkLWIwNjMtYjhlYWIxYzVmMTJjXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTU1MjI2MzU@._V1_UY317_CR109,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847150),(2039,'Brian Miller',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1011742',NULL,0),(2040,'Gabrielle Miller',NULL,'Gabrielle Miller is an American born actress who has worked on film, television and music videos. She has been in a Michael Jackson music video as well as host of a travel show called \"Taste the World\". She is an MFA trained stage actress and has performed a one-woman show around the world. She has been scene on stages across America, England in The Netherlands.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'5487799','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDczOWIyOGYtM2Q3OS00ZDc2LWI5OGEtZTM2YmU5YTcwOTAzXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNDAzNzYyNDA@._V1_UY317_CR19,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847150),(2041,'Nicholas Miller',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6636885',NULL,0),(2042,'Mark Montalbano',NULL,'Mark was born to Thomas and Carmela Montalbano (nee Fiduccia) and was raised in the Bushwick section of Brooklyn with his three younger siblings. He is of Sicilian descent, with all four of his Grandparents having come to America through Ellis Island. Mark graduated from St. Angela Hall Academy Elementary School in Brooklyn, where he first caught the acting bug starring as Bernardo in the school\'s 7th grade production of West Side Story. He also played on the basketball team and was his class salutatorian. He went on to attend the prestigious Xavier High School in Manhattan and St. John\'s University in Queens. After highly successful careers in both the real estate and construction industries, he decided to follow his lifelong dream and pursue a career in acting.<br><br>In the short time since embarking on this exciting new career path, Mark has appeared in numerous TV shows, movies and other productions. He has been fortunate enough to have worked with some of the greatest directors and actors of our time, as well as with some of the finest up-and-coming directors and actors. His roles have ranged from the sleazy sex party host in an episode of Evil Lives Here (ID Channel), to the role of an Orthodox Jewish Dad of an Autistic son in 