tor at the Taper theatre in Los Angeles, Sam Malone was well equipped when he entered the New Orleans acting scene in 2010, earning roles in such timeless pieces as HBO\'s Treme and True Detective, while continuing performing onstage such works as August Wilson\'s Jitney and William Shakespeare\'s Titus Andronicus.<br><br>After performing professionally for some time, Sam Malone decided to pursue a master\'s degree, and ultimately enrolled at the University of New Orleans, at which he performed Hamlet as the Prince of Denmark for his thesis.<br><br>He is thankful for the opportunity to continue telling stories about the human condition on stage, on film, and on television...<br>\n         ','1984-02-06 00:00:00',NULL,'USA','4896770','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTk3NzQ4MzE2OV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzY4NTIyODE@._V1_UY317_CR130,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2194,'Floyd Miles',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1026307',NULL,0),(2195,'David Kallaway',NULL,'David Kallaway is an accomplished stage, screen and television actor who embodies the term character actor.<br><br>At 8 years old Kallaway got his start in a string of television commercials, at age eleven he landed his first film role in \"Making The Grade\" opposite Judd Nelson & Gordon Jump.<br><br>He went on to work in a slew of projects filmed in his hometown of Memphis, including \"The Rainmaker\" with Francis Ford Coppola & Matt Damon and \"The People Vs. Larry Flynt\" with Woody Harrelson & Edward Norton. After attending the University of Memphis Theatre Program, Kallaway moved to Los Angeles and soon landed a guest spot on the Sci-Fi series \"Sliders\" and a recurring role on Aaron Spelling\'s hit daytime soap \"Sunset Beach.\"<br><br>Kallaway made an appearance in Adam McKay\'s Academy Award nominated \"Big Short\", and has had recurring roles in the WGN Series \"Underground\" and Amazon\'s \"Sneaky Pete.\" He portrayed the infamous slave breaker \"Edward Covey\" in the TV mini-series \"Roots.\" Kallaway stars opposite Denzel Washington, Chris Pratt, Ethan Hawke & Vincent D\'Onofrio in MGM\'s remake of \"The Magnificent Seven\", directed by Antoine Fuqua and plays opposite Mahershala Ali & Viggo Mortensen in the film \"Green Book\" directed by Peter Farley.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'0436064','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMDRlODk5YzAtNDE5OC00YzM4LWI1N2QtMjdkYzNkYjBkYjVkXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNTMyMjUwMDA@._V1_UY317_CR36,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2196,'James Evermore',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'1026307',NULL,0),(2197,'Harrison Stone',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'6464948','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDVkMzJkZWYtZWQzNy00YzMzLWFkMTQtZWJiODJkMzg5YjhhXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjE5NjU4OTU@._V1_UY317_CR34,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2198,'Ricky Muse',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3239993','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTI3OTEwMDM3OF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwMjQ2NzE3Mg@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2199,'Tom Virtue','Thomas Edwin Virtue Jr.',NULL,'1957-11-19 00:00:00',NULL,'Sherman, Texas, USA','0899487','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTI5MjUxNjY3NF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwNDYwMDkxNA@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2200,'Christina Simpkins',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2459782',NULL,0),(2201,'Kermit Burns III',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3766320','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMGJmMzY3ZTAtY2Q0YS00NTNjLWFlNjUtNDJjYWE1MDY3MDg3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjc3ODgzNDA@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2202,'Lindsay Brice',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2123952','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzhmMmJlODYtNmY1NC00ODc1LWJiN2ItMWZmMTZhNjM3ZTBjXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTA3OTEyMTM@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2203,'Shane Partlow','Shane Tyrone Partlow',NULL,'1965-09-26 00:00:00',NULL,'Moline, Illinois, USA','1018678','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTk0MTIwOTg1MF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNDQ5MjIzNDE@._V1_UY317_CR8,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2204,'Daniel Greene',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0338715','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTY0NTg5MTIzMl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwOTUxNzY2MjE@._V1_UY317_CR20,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2205,'Brian Distance',NULL,'Brian Distance is an American film and television actor known for his portrayals as the \"tough-yet-honest\" law enforcement officer. He has appeared in numerous film, television and off-Broadway productions. Brian Distance is known for his recurring role on NCIS: New Orleans (CBS) as New Orleans Police Department Sergeant Gordon, and co-star appearances on Billions (Showtime), Bull (CBS), Blindspot (NBC), Daredevil (Netflix), The Mysteries of Laura (NBC), House of Cards (Netflix), 30 Rock (NBC), and a host of other movies and television shows.<br><br>Brian Distance was born in Baltimore, Maryland. At a very young age, he cultivated his love for theatre and the performing arts by appearing in several grade school and high school plays.<br><br>After witnessing first-hand the September 11th terrorist attacks in the Financial District in New York City, Brian left his job as an investment bank finance attorney to return to his true passion, acting. To further hone his acting chops, Brian graduated from the prestigious William Esper Studio (NYC) Two-Year Professional Actor Training Program. Since then, Brian has appeared in countless feature films, network and cable television programs, and off-Broadway productions.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'3309592','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNzA0MDUxODEzOV5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwNzc4MjQ0NTE@._V1_UY317_CR131,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2206,'Craig DiFrancia',NULL,'Craig studied at the William Esper Studio in New York City and landed his first role on stage playing Bob Lansky in the off-Broadway production of Beyond Therapy. From that stage appearance, he was cast in his first television role in the mini-series Love Without Borders. Playing a tough yet compassionate police officer, Craig truly shined as an actor and a career was born. He plunged into the independent film world playing diverse characters and challenging himself with each role he embraced. Craig\'s recent credits include playing Marshal Romano on POWER , Dominic in GREEN BOOK directed by Peter Farrelly, THE IRISHMAN directed by Martin Scorsese and Officer Chris Maldonado on Blue Bloods.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1538838','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BN2FkY2E1YmQtMTM3ZC00N2ZjLTk0N2YtMDEyMzRiNGQ1ODE5XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjQwMDg0Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR37,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2207,'Dennis W. Hall',NULL,NULL,'1964-04-18 00:00:00',NULL,'Neptune, New Jersey, USA','1667150','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BODhmZGRkZjItZmRlNy00ZTU1LWIwN2EtYzY0NzFlYzViMmJiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjIwNDk4Nw@@._V1_UY317_CR14,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2208,'Leslie Castay',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4747279','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNzNkZGQyMDAtMDM0Yi00ZTQ0LTk5MjEtYzdiMGMyY2NiMjQ2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjkwOTg5ODg@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2209,'David Simpson',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'4406222',NULL,0),(2210,'Jim Klock',NULL,'President and founder of Code 3 Films, Jim Klock is also a 20-year veteran police officer. A part-time Deputy Sheriff with the Stafford County Sheriff\'s Office in Stafford, VA, Jim is a former narcotics detective who has worked and trained in many areas of law enforcement, including SWAT tactics, hostage negotiations, undercover operations, narcotics interdiction, interviews/interrogations, crime scene processing, and evidence collection. He was also an instructor in the areas of narcotics investigation, community policing, officer survival, and defensive tactics/Krav Maga.<br><br>Since transitioning from law enforcement to filmmaking, Jim has had much success acting in such projects as The Whole Truth, opposite Keanu Reeves and Renee Zellweger; Deepwater Horizon, with Mark Wahlberg; True Detective, with Matthew McConaughey and Woody Harrelson; The Astronaut Wives Club (ABC); and as Detective Chisolm, alongside Jamie Lee Curtis and Emma Roberts on FOX\'s Scream Queens. He most recently starred in Peter Farrelly\'s Green Book, with Mahershala Ali and Viggo Mortensen; the Warner Bros. Feature Film Alex & Me, which starred soccer superstar Alex Morgan; and has a recurring role on Freeform\'s highly-anticipated Marvel series, Cloak & Dagger.<br><br>Jim\'s interests in filmmaking also encompass producing, directing, and creating digital media. Jim has produced several films, including The Trials of Cate McCall, with Kate Beckinsale and Nick Nolte; There\'s Always Woodstock, with Katey Sagal and Brittany Snow; Patient Seven, with Michael Ironside; and A Christmas Arrangement, which will premiere November 2018 on Lifetime. Most recently, Jim produced the half-hour comedy TV pilot for Angels Anonymous. Jim\'s directing credits include Murder Eleven (2013); River Guard (2016); Massacre on Aisle 12 (2016); and 6:66PM: Evil Has an Hour to Kill (2017), which premiered at the Buffalo Dreams Fantastic Film Festival in November 2017 and won the Best Comedy Feature Film Award. He has even created a digital comedic series called Interrogations Gone Wrong, in which Keanu Reeves and Jason O\'Mara have guest starred.<br><br>Jim believes that great filmmaking begins with a passion for great storytelling: It begins with the writing and developing of strong scripts, while simultaneously creating interesting and original characters. Bringing this all to life on screen-surrounded by a great team of people who also believe in this vision-is what Jim loves most about filmmaking. \"Every time we make a film, we are chasing dreams. How blessed are we who get to do it.\"<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1145617','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZWQxZTc0ZDMtYjA5My00ZThiLWI3Y2MtM2YwMTkzY2JjYTRiXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMTcwOTc4Ng@@._V1_UY317_CR130,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2211,'Billy Breed',NULL,'Billy Breed is most recently know for his work in Peter Farrelly\'s \"Green Book\". He began his career in New York starring in an off-broadway production of Sam Shepard\'s Lie of the Mind,\" later deciding to focus on film. Breed is a dynamic performer having written for the CBS Diversity Showcase, constantly preforming at the major stand up comedy venues throughout Los Angeles and New York, as well as continuing to produce original, daily content with his comedy group, the \"20 Something Comedy\".<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'7542469','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYTczNWRlYWQtNjkxNS00OTQ1LWE0MjktNDZmZWYyODNkMzI3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyOTI3NTI2NTk@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2212,'Dane Rhodes',NULL,'Dane is an actor and director in New Orleans La. He has appeared on stages and in films around the world. Some of his favorite experiences have included working on a world premier play called MAcbeth at the Gates with Roy Marsden and his friend David Lumsden and getting to work with John Travolta, Scarlette Johannson, and Shanie Gable on A Love Song for Bobby Long (the movie that launched his journey into film).<br><br>When he isn\'t chasing his career, he is chasing his dog Hunter around the Big Easy... his home away from home.<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'1694797','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTU3NzIyMzIzNl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwNjE0NzcyMQ@@._V1_UY317_CR18,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2213,'Brian Stepanek',NULL,NULL,'1971-02-06 00:00:00',NULL,'Cleveland, Ohio, USA','0826745','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BZDZjZjhlYzItOGZjNC00YWE1LWI0ZjQtZGEyNmVlMTc2MjQ1XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMjMzMTU4NQ@@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2214,'Jon Michael Davis',NULL,'An American stage, film, and television actor born on August 11, 1966 in Kansas City, Missouri to parents Pamela S. Davis and A. Joe Davis. He discovered acting at an early age when he was involved with the Plaza Prime Time Players, a children\'s improv and sketch troupe in Kansas City. The group would do shows at local elementary schools and public libraries. He continued doing theatre 