lm 1998. He is still an active magician. Magnus Krepper has, up till now, appeared in 69 feature films and television productions. He has portrayed Erik Winter in the \"Kommissarie Winter\"-TV-series, Hans Faste in the \"Millennium\" series and Olof Palme in \"Call girl\", He received a Guldbagge for best actor in a supporting role 2005 for \"Mun mot mun\".<br>\n         ','1967-01-10 00:00:00',NULL,'Norrköping, Östergötland, Sweden','0470886','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTkxNzk2NDgxNl5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTcwNjc3MDI1OQ@@._V1_UY317_CR5,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2393,'Henrik Rafaelsen',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Kristiansand, Norway','0706152','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMzE3NjA4NTM4N15BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwMjA1NTYwMjE@._V1_UY317_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2394,'Maria Fahl-Vikander',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3302336',NULL,0),(2395,'Ola Normelli',NULL,'Ola Normelli was born in the rural village of Ödsmål, Sweden, where he also grew up. His early interest in language made him start writing from a very early age, and never stopped. Normelli went to acting school during his high school years in Gothenburg. After graduation and a couple of years of working in a record store, he got bored of Gothenburg and went to Seattle, WA where he studied English, sang with The Total Experience Gospel Choir and fell in love with the city itself. During 2002 through 2007, Normelli went back and forth between Seattle WA, Fresno CA, Brighton UK and his native Gothenburg. Besides a four-months acting course in Brighton (where he studied literature/linguistics), the main passion was writing. Once back on Swedish soil, Normelli wrote poems, pop songs and started working on a novel. In 2014, after a long and stressful separation, he finally went back to acting in the form of improvise under the guidance of acting coach John Pekkari at Improverket. The passion came back quickly and strongly. His first experience on set was as an extra in the biopic \"Borg vs McEnroe\" (starring Shia LaBeouf etc.) where he got to know the casting director Fredrik Fornänger. The experience of being part of a feature film became the starting point of an exponentially growing career. Over the period of less than two years, Normelli went on to be a part of handful movies, a dozen short films, three commercials, two TV-series and a seven-months theater play. In the summer of 2018, Normelli will be publishing a collection of Swedish texts on the theme of relationships as well as doing a couple of big name movies. In July, he will participate in workshops in a renowned acting studio in Los Angeles. More to follow...<br>\n         ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'8989603','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BYjFjYzIzNjUtMmI2MC00NTYzLThhNDUtMTQzNGI2MDExNWJmXkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNzM3ODgwOTE@._V1_UY317_CR131,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2396,'Mads Korsgaard',NULL,'Mads Korsgaard has studied at Stockholm Academy of Dramatic Arts and The Royal College of Music in Stockholm. But he is originally from Copenhagen, Denmark. Mads has worked with films, TV, dubbing, VO, theatre, musicals, opera and as a TV-presenter. He has acted in Danish, Swedish and English. Mads is a registered member of the Danish Actors Union & the Swedish Theatre Union.<br>\n         ','1979-09-02 00:00:00',NULL,'Copenhagen, Denmark','4274669','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BOTI0ODYyNDQ3MF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODk2MDU0ODE@._V1_UY317_CR51,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2397,'Maria Alm Norell',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'3210155',NULL,0),(2398,'Casper Kjær Jensen',NULL,NULL,'1995-05-07 00:00:00',NULL,'Denmark','6079006','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNGVlOTFkNjctMjVkZi00NDUzLTgzNWYtMjA4MDM4MjNiYTQ2XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyNjQwMzQzNDY@._V1_UX214_CR0,0,214,317_AL_.jpg',1545847337),(2399,'Lars Väringer','Lars Erik Väringer',NULL,'1951-08-20 00:00:00',NULL,'Nyköping, Södermanlands län, Sweden','0904880','https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BMTliOTk2OTItODYyYi00MWFiLWI4YTAtZjhjNmExOWNmYTA3XkEyXkFqcGdeQXVyMj